1
00:01:19,604 --> 00:01:22,104
What is it, man?
You called me, right?

2
00:01:22,937 --> 00:01:24,771
-Didn't the work get done?
-No.

3
00:01:25,062 --> 00:01:28,021
You kept saying it every day,
but I paid no attention.

4
00:01:28,354 --> 00:01:30,104
No matter how much I tell him,
he isn't getting it.

5
00:01:31,771 --> 00:01:34,771
He needs to be clear-headed
before he can understand.

6
00:01:36,396 --> 00:01:37,396
I got him to realize.

7
00:01:43,896 --> 00:01:45,104
SECRETARIAT OFFICE

8
00:01:59,479 --> 00:02:00,354
Hello.

9
00:02:06,521 --> 00:02:07,437
Mister!

10
00:02:09,229 --> 00:02:10,104
What is it?

11
00:02:11,437 --> 00:02:13,104
I'm telling you for the last time.

12
00:02:13,271 --> 00:02:14,687
Sign it.

13
00:02:15,562 --> 00:02:16,437
I won't.

14
00:02:17,146 --> 00:02:19,312
Hey, what's your problem?

15
00:02:19,812 --> 00:02:20,937
I've told you many times.

16
00:02:21,812 --> 00:02:24,604
The rules don't allow you to build
another floor on your existing land.

17
00:02:25,896 --> 00:02:28,854
If you proceed with illegal construction,

18
00:02:29,271 --> 00:02:30,979
I'll have to prevent it.

19
00:02:34,104 --> 00:02:35,146
Here, take this…

20
00:02:35,271 --> 00:02:36,229
PANCHAYAT SECRETARY

21
00:02:36,312 --> 00:02:40,854
I'm adding an extra ₹10 thousand
to the ₹25 thousand I promised.

22
00:02:41,646 --> 00:02:43,896
Take it, sign it, and finish the job.

23
00:02:50,187 --> 00:02:51,937
-This isn't about the money.
-What?

24
00:02:52,229 --> 00:02:53,854
Did someone tell you not to?

25
00:02:54,896 --> 00:02:55,979
Who is it?

26
00:02:56,479 --> 00:02:57,771
Ethics and honesty…

27
00:02:57,854 --> 00:03:00,229
they are very dear to me.
They said no.

28
00:03:01,729 --> 00:03:04,354
What's with you? Feeling too arrogant?

29
00:03:04,562 --> 00:03:06,021
You're getting too big for your boots.

30
00:03:06,437 --> 00:03:10,396
I know very well how to make you sign.

31
00:03:10,812 --> 00:03:12,979
What? Is that a threat?

32
00:03:13,187 --> 00:03:14,062
Hey!

33
00:03:14,229 --> 00:03:17,146
Do you know what it's
like to be threatened?

34
00:03:17,312 --> 00:03:18,271
Every day…

35
00:03:18,771 --> 00:03:22,521
your son goes to school
at 9 in the morning.

36
00:03:23,062 --> 00:03:25,479
and at 9:30, you're at the office.

37
00:03:26,271 --> 00:03:30,104
From then on, your
wife is all alone at home.

38
00:03:30,271 --> 00:03:33,146
What? Did you think I'd go after her?

39
00:03:34,312 --> 00:03:38,021
No… first I'll kidnap your son.

40
00:03:38,521 --> 00:03:41,646
And before your wife finds out about it…

41
00:03:41,729 --> 00:03:42,604
How?

42
00:03:43,771 --> 00:03:44,937
Why is he saying that?

43
00:03:45,771 --> 00:03:47,146
What do you mean by “how”?

44
00:03:47,271 --> 00:03:49,062
How will you kidnap him?

45
00:03:49,521 --> 00:03:50,521
What's with this guy?

46
00:03:51,187 --> 00:03:52,229
There's nothing to it.

47
00:03:52,771 --> 00:03:56,646
When your boy is going to school, I'll
wait for him at the Bangaru mettha center.

48
00:03:56,729 --> 00:03:58,146
You…

49
00:03:58,271 --> 00:03:59,687
Who the hell are you man?

50
00:03:59,979 --> 00:04:01,521
Does anyone try to kidnap
someone at public place?

51
00:04:03,521 --> 00:04:05,937
Sit down!
You filthy kidnapper!

52
00:04:07,771 --> 00:04:09,312
-This is my house?
-Okay.

53
00:04:09,771 --> 00:04:11,062
Here is the school.

54
00:04:11,146 --> 00:04:12,437
And this is Bangaru Mettha.

55
00:04:12,521 --> 00:04:15,021
-I'll kidnap him right here.
-But there will be people around, right?

56
00:04:15,771 --> 00:04:17,146
-Right?
-Yes.

57
00:04:17,229 --> 00:04:20,396
Between my house and the
Bangaru Mettha, there's a small alley.

58
00:04:20,479 --> 00:04:21,896
-It's filled with haystacks.
-Right!

59
00:04:22,437 --> 00:04:23,437
There will be no one.

60
00:04:23,521 --> 00:04:24,521
Correct brother.

61
00:04:24,729 --> 00:04:26,021
But he has to come with you, right?

62
00:04:26,229 --> 00:04:28,271
Right. What should I say to make him come?

63
00:04:28,354 --> 00:04:31,604
Show him a phone.
Tell him to make a Reel.

64
00:04:31,729 --> 00:04:33,146
Once he comes…

65
00:04:33,229 --> 00:04:34,396
As soon as he comes in,

66
00:04:34,479 --> 00:04:36,521
just grab him,
throw him in the car

67
00:04:36,604 --> 00:04:37,729
and escape from there.

68
00:04:38,396 --> 00:04:39,354
Look!

69
00:04:40,271 --> 00:04:43,854
You absolutely can't miss my son.

70
00:04:46,604 --> 00:04:47,562
Is the plan okay?

71
00:04:47,812 --> 00:04:49,521
What kind of man are you?

72
00:04:49,812 --> 00:04:53,562
If anyone threaten to kidnap his
wife and kids, He'd be scared to death.

73
00:04:54,146 --> 00:04:55,021
But what are you doing?

74
00:04:55,104 --> 00:04:59,062
Using paper and pen to draw
a sketch and tell me how to kidnap him?

75
00:05:00,646 --> 00:05:04,562
You only know there are two characters,
so you think kidnapping is easy.

76
00:05:05,312 --> 00:05:09,104
I know how cruel they are,
which is why I'm not worried.

77
00:05:09,896 --> 00:05:10,937
I didn't get it.

78
00:05:14,479 --> 00:05:20,521
DRINKING ALCOHOL IS HARMFUL TO HEALTH.

79
00:05:32,312 --> 00:05:34,646
He doesn't know my name.

80
00:05:44,687 --> 00:05:47,646
Not a boy. My name is Mithil.

81
00:05:48,062 --> 00:05:50,771
Son of Sriram. Panchayat Secretary.

82
00:05:50,937 --> 00:05:52,021
Remember the name.

83
00:05:53,437 --> 00:05:54,771
Mithil!

84
00:05:57,812 --> 00:06:00,354
What's going on, Brother?
Your son is hitting him brutally!

85
00:06:01,062 --> 00:06:03,229
He watched KGF last night.

86
00:06:04,271 --> 00:06:05,854
This morning, he ended up
hitting someone… and saw real blood.

87
00:06:08,854 --> 00:06:09,854
Plan changed.

88
00:06:11,187 --> 00:06:12,104
What is it?

89
00:06:12,354 --> 00:06:13,354
Your wife.

90
00:06:13,437 --> 00:06:14,354
No!

91
00:06:14,562 --> 00:06:16,062
You people won't be
satisfied with just promos.

92
00:06:17,229 --> 00:06:18,687
You need a theatrical trailer.

93
00:06:18,854 --> 00:06:19,729
Listen!

94
00:06:55,687 --> 00:06:57,562
Sister, please don't.

95
00:06:58,771 --> 00:06:59,771
Who the hell are you?

96
00:07:00,062 --> 00:07:00,979
A thief.

97
00:07:01,146 --> 00:07:02,104
What did you come for?

98
00:07:02,271 --> 00:07:04,062
What else? I came to steal.

99
00:07:04,521 --> 00:07:05,562
So, what should we do?

100
00:07:06,396 --> 00:07:07,604
You should file a complaint
at the police station.

101
00:07:07,729 --> 00:07:08,646
Right?

102
00:07:08,937 --> 00:07:10,687
Then why did you file the
complaint against on us?

103
00:07:10,771 --> 00:07:12,771
I mean… Sister…

104
00:07:13,062 --> 00:07:15,187
-How dare you complain against my son?
-It's not that.

105
00:07:15,271 --> 00:07:16,187
How dare you

106
00:07:16,271 --> 00:07:17,187
-drag my husband to the police station?
-Sister.

107
00:07:17,521 --> 00:07:18,479
-You…
-sister.

108
00:07:22,729 --> 00:07:24,187
Look at your eyes…
the very eyes of a thief.

109
00:07:24,354 --> 00:07:25,729
Forget your legs…
those eyes deserve the shock first.

110
00:07:25,812 --> 00:07:26,729
Stop, sister.

111
00:07:26,896 --> 00:07:28,812
When there's an attempt to kill, what
choice do we have except to file a case?

112
00:07:29,604 --> 00:07:30,729
Why are you shouting?

113
00:07:32,437 --> 00:07:34,687
Show me even a single scratch
on your body, and I'll agree.

114
00:07:39,521 --> 00:07:40,479
Don't think I'm being vulgar.

115
00:07:40,562 --> 00:07:43,062
But like an elder sister…
please open the back door just once.

116
00:07:43,396 --> 00:07:45,396
-Why?
-Look at what your son has done to me.

117
00:07:45,521 --> 00:07:46,604
Please, sister.

118
00:07:47,562 --> 00:07:48,521
Oh my god!

119
00:07:54,521 --> 00:07:56,312
Who the hell are you? You're cutting
through me like I'm just a watermelon.

120
00:07:58,646 --> 00:08:00,562
Wow, my son's art is amazing.

121
00:08:00,771 --> 00:08:02,937
Don't you know the difference
between art and hurt?

122
00:08:03,104 --> 00:08:04,604
What kind of upbringing is this, sister?

123
00:08:04,854 --> 00:08:06,312
I can bear the pain on my back,

124
00:08:06,479 --> 00:08:07,354
but at the bottom…

125
00:08:07,812 --> 00:08:10,187
I got hit in
a place I can't even mention, sister.

126
00:08:11,146 --> 00:08:12,062
Now tell me, sister.

127
00:08:12,146 --> 00:08:13,229
Isn't this a murder attempt?

128
00:08:13,354 --> 00:08:14,646
Isn't your son a …?

129
00:08:14,812 --> 00:08:16,229
Isn't your family a criminal family?

130
00:08:27,937 --> 00:08:30,062
What a damn life…

131
00:08:30,396 --> 00:08:31,437
Forget it, brother.

132
00:08:31,729 --> 00:08:34,521
I don't want your signature.
I don't want to die.

133
00:08:34,687 --> 00:08:36,104
What kind of family are you?

134
00:08:36,354 --> 00:08:39,521
There's more violence in your
house than in the movies.

135
00:08:41,937 --> 00:08:44,562
No one understands when we say it nicely.

136
00:08:53,646 --> 00:08:57,021
HORSELEY HILLS

137
00:08:59,604 --> 00:09:01,979
Hello!
Is it Bhukailash demolishing company?

138
00:09:02,104 --> 00:09:03,604
Yes.
What can we do for you.

139
00:09:03,687 --> 00:09:05,396
Yes, you need to demolish a building.

140
00:09:05,687 --> 00:09:07,062
Which Building and where is it?

141
00:09:07,354 --> 00:09:08,604
Little flowers high-school.

142
00:09:08,896 --> 00:09:09,812
Horsley hills.

143
00:09:09,896 --> 00:09:11,062
Do you want us to
demolish it or blow it up?

144
00:09:12,562 --> 00:09:13,521
Anything is fine…

145
00:09:13,729 --> 00:09:16,354
but make sure the teachers are
inside the school before you demolish it.

146
00:09:16,521 --> 00:09:17,896
Especially Principal.

147
00:09:18,187 --> 00:09:20,437
It's your choice whether you
demolish it or blow it up.

148
00:09:20,604 --> 00:09:21,604
Okay, bye.

149
00:09:22,771 --> 00:09:23,687
Hi daddy.

150
00:09:23,812 --> 00:09:25,604
Give the phone to mom.
I'll be back.

151
00:09:25,729 --> 00:09:27,021
Tomorrow is holiday.

152
00:09:27,146 --> 00:09:28,812
Bunty, tomorrow holiday for school.

153
00:09:28,979 --> 00:09:31,979
He never disappoints us.

154
00:09:33,479 --> 00:09:34,396
Uttara.

155
00:09:35,437 --> 00:09:36,729
Uttara, coffee!

156
00:09:38,854 --> 00:09:40,312
Why isn't she responding?

157
00:09:40,896 --> 00:09:41,771
Uttara!

158
00:09:48,021 --> 00:09:48,937
What?

159
00:09:49,229 --> 00:09:51,187
Didn't you hear me calling?
Are your ears blocked?

160
00:09:51,271 --> 00:09:52,229
Yours only.

161
00:09:52,521 --> 00:09:54,021
You don't listen no matter
how many times I tell you.

162
00:09:54,229 --> 00:09:55,979
Why did you refuse the money
when he offered it to you?

163
00:09:56,104 --> 00:09:56,979
What the hell are you talking…

164
00:09:57,062 --> 00:09:59,271
That's a bribe.
Not a lottery ticket.

165
00:09:59,521 --> 00:10:00,854
Taking a bribe is a crime.

166
00:10:01,812 --> 00:10:03,187
Who asked you to take a bribe?

167
00:10:03,604 --> 00:10:04,521
Consider it a gift.

168
00:10:07,312 --> 00:10:08,187
Hmm…

169
00:10:08,271 --> 00:10:09,187
That's right.

170
00:10:10,396 --> 00:10:11,729
Hmm, we can consider it a gift, right?

171
00:10:12,604 --> 00:10:16,437
Your father said he would gift
a Yamaha for our wedding.

172
00:10:17,771 --> 00:10:19,521
First, look into that matter.

173
00:10:19,604 --> 00:10:21,354
That's not a gift.
It's dowry.

174
00:10:21,812 --> 00:10:23,437
Taking a dowry is a crime.

175
00:10:23,604 --> 00:10:25,687
Stop your drama and go get me some coffee.

176
00:10:25,812 --> 00:10:26,812
What if I don't?

177
00:10:31,271 --> 00:10:35,271
Don't let my name go down in history
as the husband who killed his wife.

178
00:10:37,021 --> 00:10:38,104
Don't give it to me.

179
00:10:38,979 --> 00:10:41,896
Oh God, what a saga
for just one cup of coffee.

180
00:10:44,437 --> 00:10:45,312
-Dad!
-Yes?

181
00:10:45,396 --> 00:10:46,896
Diwali is coming, right?
Buy firecrackers!

182
00:10:47,021 --> 00:10:48,187
When you light them,
the sound should be huge!

183
00:10:48,271 --> 00:10:51,271
These small firecrackers and bombs
aren't enough for you and your mom.

184
00:10:51,354 --> 00:10:52,771
-Yes daddy.
-Do one thing.

185
00:10:53,479 --> 00:10:55,604
There's a big transformer at the
end of our street, right?

186
00:10:55,896 --> 00:10:57,062
Go blow it up.

187
00:10:57,312 --> 00:10:58,562
The whole town will hear the sound!

188
00:10:59,687 --> 00:11:01,104
Superb, Dad! Okay,
I'll go blow it up then!

189
00:11:01,187 --> 00:11:03,479
Hey! You useless fellow!

190
00:11:03,646 --> 00:11:05,896
If you blow that up,
the police will arrest me!

191
00:11:14,187 --> 00:11:15,187
Hey, Sudheer!

192
00:11:15,729 --> 00:11:17,229
-Uncle!
-What's the matter?

193
00:11:18,146 --> 00:11:19,187
That's not it, uncle.

194
00:11:19,687 --> 00:11:21,312
The new SI has arrived, right?

195
00:11:21,604 --> 00:11:25,146
I thought he'd give us some pending cases,
but he's not even coming to the station.

196
00:11:25,312 --> 00:11:26,562
And here you are, playing games.

197
00:11:26,646 --> 00:11:30,021
Oh, so you're feeling like you're the
only one working sincerely in this PS?

198
00:11:30,687 --> 00:11:32,562
-That's not what I meant, uncle.
-Then what is it?

199
00:11:32,646 --> 00:11:34,062
Actually, our old SI was better.

200
00:11:34,187 --> 00:11:35,396
This guy is a bit weird.

201
00:11:35,562 --> 00:11:38,646
Forget the cases coming to us,
first he has to take them, right?

202
00:11:39,812 --> 00:11:41,271
What do you mean he
doesn't take cases, sir?

203
00:11:41,979 --> 00:11:43,312
Have you ever gone on a raid?

204
00:11:43,771 --> 00:11:45,396
We don't need that in our area, sir.

205
00:11:45,562 --> 00:11:47,562
Go and check, the first
person you'll find is our SI.

206
00:11:47,687 --> 00:11:48,562
Uncle.

207
00:11:48,771 --> 00:11:49,771
He's always on that duty.

208
00:11:49,979 --> 00:11:53,229
How's he supposed to handle cases
when he spends all his time with girls?

209
00:12:20,396 --> 00:12:21,396
Don't come again.

210
00:12:22,229 --> 00:12:23,354
My husband got suspicious about me.

211
00:12:23,437 --> 00:12:26,187
If he gets suspicious, we can take a break
but don't ask me to stop.

212
00:12:26,312 --> 00:12:28,687
Just because he got suspicious,
he put me through hell.

213
00:12:29,021 --> 00:12:31,729
If it's confirmed,
he'll definitely kill me.

214
00:12:31,854 --> 00:12:32,896
That's not it, baby.

215
00:12:33,021 --> 00:12:34,021
Listen to me…

216
00:12:34,979 --> 00:12:36,021
Enough sir…

217
00:12:36,146 --> 00:12:37,521
Go…
Go!

218
00:12:47,396 --> 00:12:48,354
Hey!

219
00:12:50,146 --> 00:12:52,771
What is it? Looks like
Uttara is hiding something.

220
00:12:52,937 --> 00:12:53,896
What's the matter?

221
00:12:53,979 --> 00:12:55,729
Shh! don't shout.

222
00:12:55,896 --> 00:12:56,854
Why?

223
00:12:59,187 --> 00:13:00,062
Money plant.

224
00:13:00,146 --> 00:13:01,479
I stole it from the neighbor's house.

225
00:13:02,021 --> 00:13:03,229
Why did you have to steal it?

226
00:13:04,187 --> 00:13:05,521
Does anyone buy a money plant?

227
00:13:06,062 --> 00:13:07,521
Only if we steal it
without their knowledge

228
00:13:07,604 --> 00:13:09,396
will it bring lots of
money into our house.

229
00:13:09,646 --> 00:13:14,062
So you mean, not just my earnings,
this plant will make money for us too?

230
00:13:14,187 --> 00:13:16,437
We'll get more than what you earn.

231
00:13:16,562 --> 00:13:18,479
More will come?
That's great.

232
00:13:18,812 --> 00:13:20,021
So, where should we put this?

233
00:13:20,646 --> 00:13:21,979
That's what I can't figure out.

234
00:13:24,146 --> 00:13:25,146
Ah, should we put it in the cupboard?

235
00:13:25,271 --> 00:13:26,146
Yes.

236
00:13:26,229 --> 00:13:27,104
Hmm.

237
00:13:27,396 --> 00:13:29,021
But it might die without air.

238
00:13:29,687 --> 00:13:30,687
Right?

239
00:13:31,312 --> 00:13:33,104
Give it to me.

240
00:13:33,521 --> 00:13:36,062
How about this?
I'll throw it just like this.

241
00:13:36,396 --> 00:13:37,354
Why did you throw it like that?

242
00:13:37,437 --> 00:13:38,312
Shut up.

243
00:13:38,771 --> 00:13:40,146
It's theft in the first place,

244
00:13:40,312 --> 00:13:42,271
and now you want to plant it in
the cupboard and get money from it?

245
00:13:42,354 --> 00:13:44,271
-I didn't talk about cupboard.
-That rubbish!

246
00:13:44,354 --> 00:13:46,396
You would have said the same later.
I know you.

247
00:13:46,937 --> 00:13:47,854
You thief!

248
00:13:51,729 --> 00:13:53,646
You don't earn enough,
and you won't let me earn.

249
00:13:53,771 --> 00:13:55,479
So how am I supposed
to buy a necklace now?

250
00:13:56,479 --> 00:13:57,562
What necklace?

251
00:13:57,896 --> 00:13:59,729
I mean… once the plant grows,
it'll bring us money, right?

252
00:13:59,812 --> 00:14:01,562
With that money, I thought
I could buy a necklace.

253
00:14:02,354 --> 00:14:04,562
You threw the plant away…
so now you'll have to buy me a necklace.

254
00:14:05,937 --> 00:14:07,396
Is one enough, or do you want two?

255
00:14:08,729 --> 00:14:10,771
You're making me cry on a festival day.

256
00:14:11,812 --> 00:14:12,812
Point number one.

257
00:14:13,146 --> 00:14:14,271
Today is not festival.

258
00:14:17,562 --> 00:14:18,479
Point number two.

259
00:14:18,646 --> 00:14:19,729
You're not actually crying.

260
00:14:23,687 --> 00:14:24,646
Point number three.

261
00:14:25,604 --> 00:14:29,062
There you go, your father
Gurumurthy is calling. Pick it up.

262
00:14:31,521 --> 00:14:32,396
Hi, Dad.

263
00:14:32,479 --> 00:14:33,687
Hi, dear.

264
00:14:33,937 --> 00:14:35,021
Hi, dear!

265
00:14:37,396 --> 00:14:38,312
What happened, dear?

266
00:14:38,396 --> 00:14:39,979
Did your husband say something?

267
00:14:40,646 --> 00:14:43,396
Yes, Dad. I asked him to buy
me a necklace, but he won't.

268
00:14:43,562 --> 00:14:46,354
Husbands will always
say they can't afford it.

269
00:14:46,604 --> 00:14:49,146
Wives should insist.

270
00:14:51,646 --> 00:14:54,396
If he still doesn't listen, then just
take it from your father's house.

271
00:14:56,854 --> 00:14:58,312
How did I end up with people like you?

272
00:14:58,646 --> 00:15:00,396
He's just like that, Dad.
You tell me.

273
00:15:00,479 --> 00:15:03,479
Nothing much, dear.
Come home for the festival.

274
00:15:03,771 --> 00:15:05,521
-Okay.
-Bye, dear.

275
00:15:05,604 --> 00:15:06,771
Bye, father.

276
00:15:07,646 --> 00:15:09,312
Did you really have to insult
my dad over the phone?

277
00:15:10,312 --> 00:15:11,187
Sorry.

278
00:15:14,687 --> 00:15:16,146
Next time, I'll do it live.

279
00:15:17,729 --> 00:15:19,062
I'm going to the office now.

280
00:15:21,896 --> 00:15:23,729
If you return early, we'll
go to my father's place.

281
00:15:25,646 --> 00:15:26,812
Travel safely.

282
00:15:27,062 --> 00:15:28,312
And don't rush back.

283
00:15:28,771 --> 00:15:29,812
Happy journey!

284
00:15:30,062 --> 00:15:31,312
What? You're not coming with me?

285
00:15:31,646 --> 00:15:33,271
I need some peace of mind, dear.

286
00:15:33,354 --> 00:15:34,229
You mean…

287
00:15:34,312 --> 00:15:36,812
you're indirectly saying you have
no peace of mind because of my family?

288
00:15:39,646 --> 00:15:41,604
I don't think anyone could've
said it more directly than this.

289
00:15:42,479 --> 00:15:46,521
Of course… you think me and
my family aren't good enough.

290
00:15:47,146 --> 00:15:50,187
That's why you left our family
WhatsApp group, right?

291
00:15:50,271 --> 00:15:52,646
Damn!

292
00:15:52,771 --> 00:15:54,354
Why do you cry over everything?

293
00:15:55,021 --> 00:15:56,937
Because you make me cry over everything.

294
00:15:57,854 --> 00:16:01,312
It's better to die than live with you.

295
00:16:01,437 --> 00:16:03,229
Always the same torture.

296
00:16:11,562 --> 00:16:12,812
Stop the fake tears.

297
00:16:14,146 --> 00:16:15,479
Come and give me my clothes.

298
00:16:16,146 --> 00:16:17,062
Go away.

299
00:16:17,229 --> 00:16:19,354
Okay, come.
Come, come.

300
00:16:23,187 --> 00:16:24,229
Sir, response.

301
00:16:24,312 --> 00:16:26,312
The minister is not coming.
The program is canceled.

302
00:16:26,396 --> 00:16:27,271
Alright.

303
00:16:27,354 --> 00:16:29,354
Sir, please. We're running late.
Please, just let us go.

304
00:16:29,437 --> 00:16:30,729
-No way. We'll lose our jobs.
-I'll take care.

305
00:16:30,812 --> 00:16:31,937
Sir, please, sir.

306
00:16:32,104 --> 00:16:35,104
We'll leave without disturbing
the meeting, sir. It's getting late.

307
00:16:35,187 --> 00:16:37,187
Look, I already told you.
I'm telling you, it's not possible!

308
00:16:37,271 --> 00:16:38,437
It's urgent, we have to go, sir.

309
00:16:38,562 --> 00:16:40,354
Please. Please, let us go.

310
00:16:40,521 --> 00:16:43,479
Ugh! How many times do I have
to repeat myself? Don't you get it?

311
00:16:43,562 --> 00:16:44,521
Sir, sir, please sir.

312
00:16:44,604 --> 00:16:45,687
Wait here. Just wait.

313
00:16:46,187 --> 00:16:47,271
-Hey!
-Sir!

314
00:16:50,646 --> 00:16:51,521
Okay sir.

315
00:16:51,604 --> 00:16:52,562
You can go.

316
00:16:56,312 --> 00:16:57,396
-Sir, sir.
-You stop. Wait.

317
00:16:57,479 --> 00:16:59,771
-Just two minutes please…
-It's getting late, sir. We have to go.

318
00:16:59,896 --> 00:17:01,521
Sir, everyone else has stopped,
right, sir? The SI told us to.

319
00:17:01,604 --> 00:17:03,646
What do I care who told you?
No one is coming there.

320
00:17:03,729 --> 00:17:04,687
Let us do our duty.

321
00:17:04,771 --> 00:17:05,646
If you want, you can go the other way.

322
00:17:05,729 --> 00:17:07,187
Our office is right here!
How are we supposed to go that way?

323
00:17:07,687 --> 00:17:08,896
-Hey!
-That's not it, sir. Listen to me…

324
00:17:08,979 --> 00:17:09,896
Sir…

325
00:17:12,812 --> 00:17:13,687
What's the issue?

326
00:17:13,771 --> 00:17:17,812
The minister isn't coming,
so he's asking why we're stopping them.

327
00:17:18,521 --> 00:17:19,396
Why do you care?

328
00:17:21,604 --> 00:17:22,479
Who are you?

329
00:17:23,062 --> 00:17:25,312
Sriram, Panchayat Secretary.

330
00:17:25,729 --> 00:17:27,896
To hell with your panchayat,
you can wait for 10 minutes.

331
00:17:28,229 --> 00:17:29,104
Wait.

332
00:17:29,604 --> 00:17:33,687
My panchayat job is far better
than the panchayats you handle.

333
00:17:34,479 --> 00:17:35,354
Let us go.

334
00:17:36,271 --> 00:17:37,146
Hey, what's with the attitude?

335
00:17:37,229 --> 00:17:38,562
-Are you acting smart?
-Sir, sir.

336
00:17:38,646 --> 00:17:40,062
The public is watching, sir.

337
00:17:45,312 --> 00:17:46,771
Are you special?
Go.

338
00:17:46,937 --> 00:17:48,812
Oh, so she's special to you?

339
00:17:49,396 --> 00:17:50,396
Is that why you let her go?

340
00:17:54,021 --> 00:17:54,896
It's my wish.

341
00:17:55,187 --> 00:17:56,771
Keep your wishes inside your station.

342
00:17:57,937 --> 00:18:00,062
If you show them outside…
I won't sit quietly and watch.

343
00:18:00,562 --> 00:18:02,229
Then, what will you do?

344
00:18:03,479 --> 00:18:04,479
-Hey!
-Sir!

345
00:18:04,562 --> 00:18:06,146
File a weed case against
him and lock him up.

346
00:18:07,521 --> 00:18:11,312
It's not as easy as you think
to file a weed case against me.

347
00:18:15,062 --> 00:18:16,187
-How dare you?
-Sir, sir, sir… please…

348
00:18:16,271 --> 00:18:17,812
He's a government employee, sir.

349
00:18:17,896 --> 00:18:19,021
-Please don't sir.
-What are you getting excited about?

350
00:18:20,729 --> 00:18:21,812
Everyone is recording videos, sir.

351
00:18:21,896 --> 00:18:23,271
It will ruin the department's
reputation, please sir.

352
00:18:23,354 --> 00:18:24,354
Hey, constables tell
them to stop recording.

353
00:18:24,437 --> 00:18:25,312
Please, sir.

354
00:18:25,396 --> 00:18:26,354
-Hey, what's with the videos?
-Hey, Sriram

355
00:18:26,437 --> 00:18:27,562
-Turn them off, all of you.
-calm down.

356
00:18:27,854 --> 00:18:29,062
-Please, sir.
-You can go, sir.

357
00:18:30,271 --> 00:18:31,937
-Find out his address.
-I'll take care of it, sir.

358
00:18:57,521 --> 00:19:00,229
-It is not happening, leave.
-Mister.

359
00:19:00,937 --> 00:19:02,854
We've convinced more than
half the families in the village

360
00:19:02,979 --> 00:19:04,312
and brought them here.

361
00:19:04,396 --> 00:19:06,312
Take their signatures,
and the work will be done.

362
00:19:07,771 --> 00:19:08,854
Not half.

363
00:19:09,937 --> 00:19:11,771
Even if one person
disagrees, I won't sign.

364
00:19:12,604 --> 00:19:14,104
You think there's someone like that?

365
00:19:15,062 --> 00:19:15,979
Hey!

366
00:19:17,104 --> 00:19:20,646
Does anyone in the village have
a problem with signing?

367
00:19:21,396 --> 00:19:22,646
Is there?

368
00:19:36,062 --> 00:19:37,479
Your vote won't be valid.

369
00:19:38,104 --> 00:19:40,896
To keep your job, you have to be generous.

370
00:19:41,104 --> 00:19:44,812
To be generous, I'll even give up my job.

371
00:19:48,521 --> 00:19:49,396
Brother!

372
00:19:49,812 --> 00:19:50,937
Why are you still here?

373
00:19:51,854 --> 00:19:53,437
I'll take care of the cemetery issue.

374
00:19:53,979 --> 00:19:56,604
Why should we build a
cemetery in the MLA's place?

375
00:19:57,312 --> 00:19:58,437
The MLA is on the line.

376
00:19:58,646 --> 00:19:59,562
Speak to him.

377
00:20:00,771 --> 00:20:01,646
Sir.

378
00:20:01,729 --> 00:20:03,729
MLA THIMMAPPA'S HOUSE, MADAMAPALLE

379
00:20:03,812 --> 00:20:04,896
What mister?

380
00:20:05,437 --> 00:20:07,687
I heard you're stopping the villagers
from getting signatures.

381
00:20:09,354 --> 00:20:12,021
I'll send you a package. Sign it.

382
00:20:12,187 --> 00:20:13,396
What's there in a package, sir?

383
00:20:13,896 --> 00:20:15,479
The promise I gave to the
people is more important.

384
00:20:16,437 --> 00:20:20,396
I promised that a cemetery nearby
wouldn't be good for the village.

385
00:20:21,479 --> 00:20:22,896
Let's do it this way this time, sir.

386
00:20:23,354 --> 00:20:24,312
I'm hanging up, sir.

387
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:31,896
-Hey, Prasad.
-Sir?

388
00:20:31,979 --> 00:20:34,021
That Sriram must be
transferred immediately.

389
00:20:34,187 --> 00:20:36,187
Sir, we've already
transferred the RI and VRO.

390
00:20:36,812 --> 00:20:38,021
If we transfer someone who has public
support,

391
00:20:38,271 --> 00:20:39,646
the public will not vote us again.

392
00:20:39,896 --> 00:20:42,729
So let's leave him for now
and find another way, sir.

393
00:20:43,562 --> 00:20:44,854
Dear, get that bag.

394
00:20:52,479 --> 00:20:53,937
-Prasad.
-Sir!

395
00:20:54,146 --> 00:20:56,729
Send this gift bag to the
minister, and as usual,

396
00:20:57,437 --> 00:20:59,729
leave the town without
anyone suspecting anything.

397
00:21:00,312 --> 00:21:01,521
It's very important.

398
00:21:01,687 --> 00:21:02,687
Be careful.

399
00:21:05,354 --> 00:21:07,479
Edukondalu will come at night and take it.

400
00:21:07,729 --> 00:21:09,521
You just pretend you don't know anything.

401
00:21:10,812 --> 00:21:12,187
Go straight, sir, straight.
Straight ahead!

402
00:21:12,271 --> 00:21:14,021
Why are you turning the wheel like that?

403
00:21:14,479 --> 00:21:15,687
Put it in third gear, sir.

404
00:21:16,229 --> 00:21:17,979
It's fine.

405
00:21:19,771 --> 00:21:20,646
Fine?

406
00:21:20,729 --> 00:21:21,646
Hmm!

407
00:21:21,729 --> 00:21:23,604
The car's going to stall!
Put it in third gear.

408
00:21:36,062 --> 00:21:38,646
Oh no! What a man he is!
What the hell is wrong with him?

409
00:21:42,646 --> 00:21:44,812
-Don't you get down?
-If we both get down, who will drive?

410
00:21:45,187 --> 00:21:46,354
Damn!

411
00:21:46,896 --> 00:21:49,979
Please, I kindly request you to get down.

412
00:21:52,062 --> 00:21:54,104
So, you'll drive from here?

413
00:21:54,687 --> 00:21:55,729
Have some shame.

414
00:21:56,437 --> 00:21:59,437
It's been a month, you haven't
gone past second gear or into reverse.

415
00:21:59,604 --> 00:22:02,354
Never before have I seen a teacher
break a student's spirit like this.

416
00:22:02,437 --> 00:22:05,354
Sir, I don't have the
courage to encourage you.

417
00:22:05,437 --> 00:22:08,104
If this car could speak, it would curse…

418
00:22:08,687 --> 00:22:09,562
-I got it! It would curse me, right?
-Leave it.

419
00:22:09,646 --> 00:22:11,021
That's what you mean.

420
00:22:11,479 --> 00:22:12,437
Enough of this.

421
00:22:12,729 --> 00:22:13,854
I don't need your fees.

422
00:22:14,437 --> 00:22:15,896
Just drive in second gear.

423
00:22:17,229 --> 00:22:19,812
Your neighbor Prasad has a car, right?
Convince him to give that to me.

424
00:22:19,896 --> 00:22:21,354
I'll use it for my driving school.

425
00:22:22,562 --> 00:22:23,437
He won't.

426
00:22:23,562 --> 00:22:24,437
That is his sentimental car.

427
00:22:24,521 --> 00:22:26,521
What's the point of being sentimental
about a car that isn't even running?

428
00:22:26,604 --> 00:22:27,937
That's what I'm saying.

429
00:22:28,021 --> 00:22:29,854
Why do you need a car that
doesn't even budge an inch?

430
00:22:29,937 --> 00:22:31,646
You act like a big businessman.

431
00:22:32,896 --> 00:22:35,187
Alright, I'll get down for today.

432
00:22:35,646 --> 00:22:38,646
We will catch up here tomorrow. I'll
definitely drive the car in third gear.

433
00:22:38,937 --> 00:22:41,854
-No doubt at all.
-He's always nagging me. Damn this life.

434
00:22:42,687 --> 00:22:44,021
They're bothering me!

435
00:22:44,646 --> 00:22:45,604
Send me the money!

436
00:22:47,312 --> 00:22:48,229
Hey, Rajendra.

437
00:22:48,562 --> 00:22:49,562
Why aren't you coming to the office?

438
00:22:49,687 --> 00:22:51,062
You know our friend Venkatramana?

439
00:22:51,229 --> 00:22:52,646
Yes, the guy who lives in America, right?

440
00:22:52,812 --> 00:22:54,229
I think his mother passed away.

441
00:22:54,396 --> 00:22:56,271
Exactly. When she passed,
he couldn't make it back,

442
00:22:56,354 --> 00:22:57,979
so I hired some professional
mourners from Vellore.

443
00:22:58,437 --> 00:22:59,896
Professional mourners?
Who are they?

444
00:22:59,979 --> 00:23:02,646
The people who cry for money
when someone dies.

445
00:23:02,729 --> 00:23:03,854
Anyway, the mourners
did their crying and left.

446
00:23:04,229 --> 00:23:05,771
Now he's making me
miserable by refusing to pay up.

447
00:23:06,687 --> 00:23:08,354
-What strange times we live in.
-Okay, let's go have some tea.

448
00:23:08,437 --> 00:23:09,479
-No, no, I can't.
-Brother!

449
00:23:09,687 --> 00:23:10,896
Just came from my driving session.

450
00:23:10,979 --> 00:23:12,271
-Let me freshen up and I'll be back.
-Listen?

451
00:23:13,687 --> 00:23:15,812
I'm the guy who smacks heads just for fun.

452
00:23:16,687 --> 00:23:17,771
You really want to mess with me?

453
00:23:18,062 --> 00:23:18,937
Be careful.

454
00:23:19,062 --> 00:23:22,187
If I call my friends,
they'll smash your head.

455
00:23:22,562 --> 00:23:23,729
Be careful. Bye.

456
00:23:24,479 --> 00:23:26,062
This is how you should make a video!

457
00:23:26,437 --> 00:23:27,312
Just you watch.

458
00:23:27,562 --> 00:23:30,396
I'll make a video
that gets more likes than yours.

459
00:23:30,479 --> 00:23:31,396
Smacking head?

460
00:23:31,479 --> 00:23:33,937
Oh no! He's going to destroy
my peace with those stupid reels.

461
00:23:34,396 --> 00:23:36,896
Hey, Sriram,
why are you messing with the MLA?

462
00:23:36,979 --> 00:23:38,271
He asked you to sign, and you refused?

463
00:23:38,812 --> 00:23:40,312
It's illegal, how can I do it?

464
00:23:40,437 --> 00:23:43,687
But what about you? You opposed our road
construction, now you're supporting him?

465
00:23:43,771 --> 00:23:46,021
What you said is correct,
but he's not as good as you think.

466
00:23:46,104 --> 00:23:49,021
Okay, whatever happens, we'll see later.
By the way, I forgot…

467
00:23:49,104 --> 00:23:51,937
Why is that driving school Govind
asking for your car?

468
00:23:52,021 --> 00:23:52,896
Stupid fellow!

469
00:23:52,979 --> 00:23:54,604
Because of his torture, I kept the
car inside saying it wasn't working,

470
00:23:54,687 --> 00:23:56,104
even though it was perfectly fine.

471
00:23:56,562 --> 00:24:01,271
If I get angry, I'll ram the car into him
and throw him in the trunk. Bloody idiot!

472
00:24:01,437 --> 00:24:02,729
Honey, it's getting late!

473
00:24:02,812 --> 00:24:04,104
Coming!

474
00:24:04,687 --> 00:24:07,479
What? A tour again? Your job is great.

475
00:24:08,021 --> 00:24:09,729
My mother-in-law
invited us for the festival.

476
00:24:10,854 --> 00:24:13,187
Don't shout. If my wife hears,
she'll create a mess.

477
00:24:13,812 --> 00:24:14,812
Right!

478
00:24:15,104 --> 00:24:17,812
Prasad, will you get into the car or not?

479
00:24:20,854 --> 00:24:23,854
You can go.
Otherwise, it'll ride on you.

480
00:24:25,187 --> 00:24:26,521
The car… not her.

481
00:24:28,104 --> 00:24:30,604
If that driving school
guy calls you again…

482
00:24:30,812 --> 00:24:32,312
I'll deal with him, you go.

483
00:24:33,229 --> 00:24:34,479
Let's talk on phone.

484
00:24:35,271 --> 00:24:37,562
There are no signals, right?
How can we talk on the phone?

485
00:24:39,562 --> 00:24:43,146
We shouldn't let her call me 'Hey Prasad'.

486
00:24:43,854 --> 00:24:44,896
You are right.

487
00:24:45,479 --> 00:24:47,062
-She's a tough woman.
-That's it.

488
00:24:47,312 --> 00:24:48,229
Okay, I'm leaving.

489
00:24:48,312 --> 00:24:49,271
Drive safely.

490
00:24:51,312 --> 00:24:52,646
Leaving already?

491
00:24:54,937 --> 00:24:56,187
Just stepping out for a smoke.

492
00:25:20,062 --> 00:25:21,687
-Hello, boss.
-Tell me.

493
00:25:21,854 --> 00:25:24,812
I came for the gift.
It will reach the boss by evening.

494
00:25:24,937 --> 00:25:25,812
Be careful.

495
00:25:37,062 --> 00:25:37,979
Hey!

496
00:25:45,521 --> 00:25:46,396
Hey!

497
00:25:48,312 --> 00:25:49,187
Who are you?

498
00:25:50,312 --> 00:25:51,521
What are you doing here at this time?

499
00:25:52,937 --> 00:25:53,979
And who the hell are you?

500
00:25:54,937 --> 00:25:56,604
KOTHAKOTA POLICE STATION

501
00:25:56,687 --> 00:25:59,062
Leave me, sir.
I didn't do anything.

502
00:26:01,687 --> 00:26:02,604
I'll leave you, man.

503
00:26:02,687 --> 00:26:04,021
Tell me what you were
doing there at night.

504
00:26:04,146 --> 00:26:05,229
I already told you, sir.

505
00:26:05,562 --> 00:26:06,854
I was going to my relatives' house.

506
00:26:07,271 --> 00:26:10,146
I didn't ask you to repeat
what you already said.

507
00:26:10,729 --> 00:26:11,854
Tell me the truth.

508
00:26:11,937 --> 00:26:13,271
What's this, sir?

509
00:26:13,562 --> 00:26:14,979
You were also there at that time.

510
00:26:15,104 --> 00:26:17,229
Did I ask you why you were there
and what you were doing?

511
00:26:17,479 --> 00:26:18,937
Everyone has their own business, sir.

512
00:26:22,479 --> 00:26:23,354
Sorry, sir.

513
00:26:23,437 --> 00:26:25,354
Sir, I'm sorry.
Sir…

514
00:26:25,437 --> 00:26:26,396
-Bloody scoundrel…
-Please, sir.

515
00:26:26,479 --> 00:26:28,812
-Please sir, let me go sir.
-How dare you?

516
00:26:28,896 --> 00:26:30,312
-Speak up!
-Leave me, sir. Please.

517
00:26:30,396 --> 00:26:32,479
-How dare you talking against me? Tell me.
-Sir, please sir.

518
00:26:32,646 --> 00:26:34,021
-Please!
-Get up!

519
00:26:35,104 --> 00:26:36,104
Tell me.

520
00:26:36,687 --> 00:26:37,771
Speak up!

521
00:26:38,187 --> 00:26:39,312
No, sir, don't hit me.

522
00:26:41,312 --> 00:26:42,562
I'll tell you everything, sir.

523
00:26:50,854 --> 00:26:54,021
DIWALI DAY

524
00:27:10,771 --> 00:27:11,729
Who is it?

525
00:27:11,979 --> 00:27:12,979
Is your husband home?

526
00:27:13,312 --> 00:27:14,937
He's not at home. He went out.

527
00:27:15,521 --> 00:27:16,771
-And you?
-Vikram.

528
00:27:17,437 --> 00:27:18,396
I'm the SI of this area.

529
00:27:19,229 --> 00:27:20,896
He'll be back in a while. Come in.

530
00:27:37,104 --> 00:27:38,729
Coffee or tea?

531
00:27:38,854 --> 00:27:40,021
Anything you bring is fine.

532
00:28:54,146 --> 00:28:57,812
You started blowing it up early in the
morning. Bombs will enter the house.

533
00:28:58,979 --> 00:29:02,021
Ugh… what in the world…?
What kinds of children they are

534
00:29:03,229 --> 00:29:04,187
Wait, what's this now?

535
00:29:04,687 --> 00:29:06,729
Is she sulking because I wouldn't
take her to her parents' house?

536
00:29:07,396 --> 00:29:10,396
Oh my god…
I swear, I can't deal with her drama.

537
00:29:14,104 --> 00:29:15,021
Hello?

538
00:29:15,937 --> 00:29:16,812
Hmm?

539
00:29:17,562 --> 00:29:19,979
Hope she's not seriously
planning a trip to Chittoor.

540
00:29:22,771 --> 00:29:24,646
My darling… "stopped breathing"?

541
00:29:24,771 --> 00:29:26,229
Oh God! Are you okay?

542
00:29:28,562 --> 00:29:29,646
Hey!

543
00:29:31,062 --> 00:29:32,312
Who is there…?

544
00:29:49,521 --> 00:29:50,396
Sir!

545
00:29:55,354 --> 00:29:56,354
Sir!

546
00:30:08,146 --> 00:30:09,187
Hands up!

547
00:30:12,437 --> 00:30:13,937
I really didn't do anything, sir.

548
00:30:14,271 --> 00:30:15,646
I don't know anything, sir.

549
00:30:18,479 --> 00:30:20,187
Hi, Dad.
Let's make a Reel now.

550
00:30:20,562 --> 00:30:22,771
Here's the plan. As soon as I shoot,

551
00:30:22,979 --> 00:30:26,479
you have to act exactly like that uncle.

552
00:30:26,562 --> 00:30:27,646
Okay?

553
00:30:29,896 --> 00:30:31,521
-Hey!
-What daddy?

554
00:30:32,479 --> 00:30:33,896
Are you the one who shot him?

555
00:30:41,104 --> 00:30:41,979
Hands up!

556
00:30:48,312 --> 00:30:49,896
Uncle, you're dead.
You're not supposed to get up.

557
00:30:52,646 --> 00:30:54,396
Do you think Diwali gun can kill someone?

558
00:30:57,354 --> 00:30:59,021
This is a real gun.

559
00:31:00,187 --> 00:31:01,604
Uncle, can I touch it once?

560
00:31:03,187 --> 00:31:05,104
-No!
-Please, please, please.

561
00:31:05,312 --> 00:31:07,479
I'll give it back immediately.
Please, uncle…

562
00:31:07,854 --> 00:31:08,812
please…

563
00:31:13,771 --> 00:31:15,646
Goodness! Why is it so heavy?

564
00:31:17,812 --> 00:31:19,812
Is this really a real gun?

565
00:31:35,479 --> 00:31:37,187
I'm the one who shot him, Dad.

566
00:31:37,312 --> 00:31:39,854
You have to act exactly like him
and fall down. Okay?

567
00:31:39,937 --> 00:31:41,271
-What have you done?!
-Mom!

568
00:31:41,521 --> 00:31:43,146
No, Dad!
You're always up to some mischief!

569
00:31:43,646 --> 00:31:44,646
Sorry, Dad.

570
00:31:44,729 --> 00:31:46,146
-I'll kill you.
-No, Dad.

571
00:31:46,229 --> 00:31:47,562
-Dear, Let him go.
-Mom, please!

572
00:31:47,646 --> 00:31:49,062
-Dear, please! Let him go.
-Hey!

573
00:31:50,104 --> 00:31:51,604
He's just a kid!
Are you really going to kill him?

574
00:31:51,687 --> 00:31:53,854
So what?
I should beat you first.

575
00:31:54,229 --> 00:31:56,646
You can hit us any time you want.
See what needs to be done now.

576
00:31:56,771 --> 00:31:57,771
What should I do?

577
00:31:58,646 --> 00:32:00,479
-Let's surrender to the police.
-Mom!

578
00:32:01,354 --> 00:32:02,354
He's just a kid.

579
00:32:03,979 --> 00:32:04,937
Not him.

580
00:32:05,521 --> 00:32:06,437
It's me.

581
00:32:09,521 --> 00:32:10,687
You're surrendering?

582
00:32:11,562 --> 00:32:12,812
Hey, come here…

583
00:32:13,562 --> 00:32:14,437
Come…

584
00:32:16,979 --> 00:32:21,104
Don't you dare come into this
house until I tell you to? I'll kill you.

585
00:32:22,271 --> 00:32:23,146
Go!

586
00:32:24,146 --> 00:32:26,271
Why are you sending him out?
What if he tells someone?

587
00:32:27,437 --> 00:32:28,604
No one will believe him.

588
00:32:28,729 --> 00:32:30,021
If he stays here he'll start live
video on social media.

589
00:32:30,104 --> 00:32:32,604
Forget about him.
Why are you surrendering?

590
00:32:32,896 --> 00:32:34,437
That SI and I had a fight yesterday only.

591
00:32:35,562 --> 00:32:37,312
Do you think people in the village
will believe that Mittu did it?

592
00:32:39,062 --> 00:32:40,312
They'll think I did it.

593
00:32:41,729 --> 00:32:44,271
At least if I surrender,
the punishment might be less.

594
00:32:45,271 --> 00:32:46,187
Let me go.

595
00:32:47,396 --> 00:32:49,312
I won't agree to you going to jail.

596
00:32:49,687 --> 00:32:50,604
Then he has to go.

597
00:32:51,562 --> 00:32:52,729
I won't agree to that either.

598
00:32:53,562 --> 00:32:57,229
Whether you agree or not,
a mistake has been made in our house.

599
00:32:59,312 --> 00:33:02,146
It's a crime if you do it knowingly…
but how is this a crime?

600
00:33:02,437 --> 00:33:04,146
A crime is a crime.

601
00:33:04,979 --> 00:33:05,854
Move…

602
00:33:09,146 --> 00:33:11,687
If you go to jail against my word…

603
00:33:13,854 --> 00:33:17,021
Kill both of us.
then it's your wish.

604
00:33:19,312 --> 00:33:21,854
So what now?
You want me to cover it up?

605
00:33:26,479 --> 00:33:29,104
You should have some common sense.

606
00:33:29,812 --> 00:33:30,771
Let's hide it.

607
00:33:33,271 --> 00:33:34,146
What?

608
00:33:36,646 --> 00:33:37,521
Let's hide it.

609
00:33:39,521 --> 00:33:40,979
-Yes.
-Hey!

610
00:33:41,687 --> 00:33:42,687
Are you crazy?

611
00:33:43,562 --> 00:33:44,979
He made a mistake unknowingly.

612
00:33:46,021 --> 00:33:47,396
And knowingly I won't do any mistake.

613
00:33:50,396 --> 00:33:51,271
Then go.

614
00:33:53,479 --> 00:33:55,312
I'll jump into the well
along with our son.

615
00:33:55,437 --> 00:33:56,812
-I'll hit you…
-Hit me!

616
00:33:58,854 --> 00:34:00,854
Your son's future is less important

617
00:34:01,604 --> 00:34:03,937
than your morality and honesty, right?

618
00:34:04,229 --> 00:34:06,937
You always say we're the problem anyway.

619
00:34:08,062 --> 00:34:09,104
If we're not there,

620
00:34:09,771 --> 00:34:11,937
you can live happily as you wish.

621
00:34:12,812 --> 00:34:13,687
Go.

622
00:34:33,021 --> 00:34:35,771
You always say we're the problem.

623
00:34:40,146 --> 00:34:44,187
Your son's future is less important
than your morality and honesty, right?

624
00:34:51,271 --> 00:34:55,521
If we're not there,
you're free to live happily your way.

625
00:35:12,812 --> 00:35:14,479
I'll listen to you now…

626
00:35:16,771 --> 00:35:18,854
but one day this will become a big issue.

627
00:35:21,021 --> 00:35:22,312
When that time comes…

628
00:35:23,687 --> 00:35:25,021
you'll have to listen to me.

629
00:36:23,604 --> 00:36:24,854
-Your phone?
-No.

630
00:36:25,479 --> 00:36:28,021
I think it's his phone.
He plugged it in some time back.

631
00:36:31,729 --> 00:36:32,979
His wife is calling.

632
00:36:33,062 --> 00:36:34,271
-It's not turning off.
-Oh God, please turn it off.

633
00:36:34,354 --> 00:36:35,854
-It's not turning off.
-Switch off the phone.

634
00:36:48,604 --> 00:36:49,687
Why did you wipe that?

635
00:36:50,062 --> 00:36:51,187
What about the fingerprints?

636
00:36:55,687 --> 00:36:56,604
Hold him.

637
00:37:01,771 --> 00:37:02,646
Carefully.

638
00:37:03,271 --> 00:37:04,271
-This way, this way.
-That way?

639
00:37:04,354 --> 00:37:05,521
Let's put it under the bed.

640
00:37:06,479 --> 00:37:07,729
-Is it okay under the bed?
-Shh!

641
00:37:08,187 --> 00:37:09,396
I'm not shouting.

642
00:37:10,771 --> 00:37:11,812
Okay, okay, let's go.

643
00:37:12,896 --> 00:37:14,312
Gently… calmly…

644
00:37:23,937 --> 00:37:24,812
Namaste, sir.

645
00:37:24,896 --> 00:37:26,062
MR. VAIRA PURUSHOTTAM REDDY

646
00:37:26,146 --> 00:37:28,354
Put your Namaste in the ballot box.

647
00:37:29,896 --> 00:37:30,771
What happened, sir?

648
00:37:31,021 --> 00:37:31,896
Where's the gift?

649
00:37:32,104 --> 00:37:33,187
It should have been here by now.

650
00:37:35,062 --> 00:37:37,937
What is this, sir?
I already sent it last night.

651
00:37:38,312 --> 00:37:43,229
I don't care if you sent it, he stole it,
or the two of you are playing games.

652
00:37:43,312 --> 00:37:45,021
Your work gets done
only when I get the gift.

653
00:37:45,271 --> 00:37:46,729
If not… you're finished.

654
00:37:48,229 --> 00:37:51,437
Nothing is more important to me
than my political future. Got it?

655
00:37:53,896 --> 00:37:55,021
What happened?

656
00:37:56,104 --> 00:37:57,687
Call Prasad.

657
00:38:00,479 --> 00:38:02,854
The number you are trying
to reach is currently busy.

658
00:38:03,021 --> 00:38:05,812
It's not connecting.
There's no signal in the village.

659
00:38:07,312 --> 00:38:08,312
Hey, Madan!

660
00:38:08,771 --> 00:38:10,312
-Hey, Madan!
-Boss!

661
00:38:11,187 --> 00:38:13,812
-What happened?
-The Minister didn't get the gift.

662
00:38:13,896 --> 00:38:14,896
What do you mean? Last night…

663
00:38:15,312 --> 00:38:16,771
Why are you asking us?

664
00:38:17,396 --> 00:38:18,896
You're supposed to ask
Yedukondalu that, right?

665
00:38:20,312 --> 00:38:22,312
Hey, first call that scoundrel.

666
00:38:22,812 --> 00:38:24,771
Did you call us for such a small thing?

667
00:38:25,229 --> 00:38:27,104
You have a phone in your pocket, right?
You could have called him yourself.

668
00:38:27,729 --> 00:38:29,687
-Hey, you duffer!
-Michael!

669
00:38:33,687 --> 00:38:34,771
Get lost.

670
00:38:36,229 --> 00:38:38,729
You're coming to my sister's place
tonight, right? I'll deal with you then.

671
00:38:38,812 --> 00:38:40,687
The number you are
calling is either switched off…

672
00:38:42,479 --> 00:38:44,771
The number you are
calling is either switched off…

673
00:38:44,854 --> 00:38:46,354
Boss, his phone is switched off.

674
00:38:46,479 --> 00:38:49,479
My god, he cheated us.

675
00:38:50,521 --> 00:38:51,646
-Hey!
-Boss!

676
00:38:51,812 --> 00:38:54,562
Tell our men to find him wherever he is.

677
00:38:54,937 --> 00:38:55,812
Okay.

678
00:38:56,062 --> 00:38:57,687
If he's found,

679
00:38:58,437 --> 00:39:01,021
-I'll chop him into pieces
-Okay, boss.

680
00:39:01,437 --> 00:39:02,396
Hey, Madan.

681
00:39:03,729 --> 00:39:08,271
He has been working for us for so long.
Do you think he'd do something like this?

682
00:39:09,479 --> 00:39:10,521
What do you think?

683
00:39:11,812 --> 00:39:12,896
-Hey!
-Boss.

684
00:39:12,979 --> 00:39:16,521
First go to Prasad's house and
check whether our gift is there or not.

685
00:39:17,354 --> 00:39:18,229
Okay, boss.

686
00:39:23,896 --> 00:39:24,896
What's that?

687
00:39:25,896 --> 00:39:27,062
Blood spilled, right?

688
00:39:27,271 --> 00:39:29,521
This prevents dogs
from sensing the smell.

689
00:39:32,646 --> 00:39:33,646
Where are you going?

690
00:39:35,854 --> 00:39:37,437
You asked me to hide the body, right?

691
00:39:38,104 --> 00:39:39,604
If we keep it in the house, it'll stink.

692
00:39:40,354 --> 00:39:42,187
That's why I'm going to
find a place to dump it.

693
00:39:42,312 --> 00:39:45,521
So I should stay alone with the body?

694
00:39:48,062 --> 00:39:49,062
It's difficult.

695
00:39:50,979 --> 00:39:52,646
Call all our neighbors

696
00:39:53,354 --> 00:39:55,104
and arrange the funeral rites.

697
00:39:55,479 --> 00:39:57,062
I'll get a coffin in the meantime.

698
00:41:22,396 --> 00:41:24,312
Why are all these people here?

699
00:41:24,771 --> 00:41:26,271
If we go now, it'll be a problem.

700
00:41:26,437 --> 00:41:28,646
Reverse the car.
First, let's go to Yedukondalu's house.

701
00:41:46,146 --> 00:41:47,979
Call all our neighbors

702
00:41:48,812 --> 00:41:50,521
and arrange the funeral rites.

703
00:42:00,021 --> 00:42:02,562
You're here?
Go, she's over there.

704
00:42:07,146 --> 00:42:08,354
Why is everyone gathered here?

705
00:42:09,062 --> 00:42:11,312
Dear, please give these sweets to them.

706
00:42:11,812 --> 00:42:12,687
What for?

707
00:42:13,062 --> 00:42:14,729
-Well…
-What is it?

708
00:42:15,354 --> 00:42:17,604
After you left, I was all alone, you know.

709
00:42:17,687 --> 00:42:18,604
So?

710
00:42:18,771 --> 00:42:20,062
I was scared.

711
00:42:20,146 --> 00:42:22,396
And so? What have you done?

712
00:42:24,396 --> 00:42:27,021
What's wrong with these chilies?
They've turned all mushy.

713
00:42:27,396 --> 00:42:28,521
The peel won't even come off.

714
00:42:30,479 --> 00:42:31,729
What is it? Why have you come?

715
00:42:31,812 --> 00:42:35,354
Aunty… I'm scared to
be in the house alone.

716
00:42:35,687 --> 00:42:36,771
Will you keep me company?

717
00:42:37,146 --> 00:42:38,229
What is it, dear?

718
00:42:38,312 --> 00:42:39,937
Well…

719
00:42:41,146 --> 00:42:42,396
It's just… I've missed my period.

720
00:42:44,937 --> 00:42:45,854
Dear!

721
00:42:45,979 --> 00:42:46,937
Dear!

722
00:42:48,812 --> 00:42:49,896
You too…

723
00:42:51,187 --> 00:42:53,771
You wouldn't even let
me live in peace, huh?

724
00:42:53,979 --> 00:42:54,979
Ramu!

725
00:42:56,771 --> 00:43:00,146
Having celebrations with a dead body
in the house, you shameless fool!

726
00:43:02,104 --> 00:43:03,937
Enough of your romance…
just get over here.

727
00:43:04,479 --> 00:43:06,437
-What is this, Sweets?
-Yes, Take this Aunty.

728
00:43:10,146 --> 00:43:12,146
Sriram is quite the player.

729
00:43:13,562 --> 00:43:16,729
-Here, girl. He's not a normal player.
-Hey, Sriram!

730
00:43:16,812 --> 00:43:18,979
Are you distributing sweets?
Did you get a promotion?

731
00:43:19,062 --> 00:43:23,687
I know, man. You're a hard worker. You'll
get what you deserve for your hard work.

732
00:43:23,771 --> 00:43:25,396
Promotion? Don't be silly.

733
00:43:25,479 --> 00:43:27,729
Sriram is going to be a father again.

734
00:43:27,937 --> 00:43:29,062
Really?

735
00:43:29,187 --> 00:43:31,604
Oh! I know. You're a hard worker.

736
00:43:31,687 --> 00:43:34,979
You'll get what you deserve for
your hard work. Congratulations!

737
00:43:37,104 --> 00:43:38,354
You taught him a lesson.

738
00:43:42,062 --> 00:43:44,479
The daily exercise has paid off well.

739
00:43:45,521 --> 00:43:48,521
What is it, Sriram? Is it Shilajit?

740
00:43:49,562 --> 00:43:50,687
My foot!

741
00:43:52,312 --> 00:43:53,479
Dear!

742
00:43:56,979 --> 00:43:59,896
-What happened?
-Dear, our Son…

743
00:44:00,271 --> 00:44:01,187
Did he come?

744
00:44:03,437 --> 00:44:04,937
…is not to be seen.

745
00:44:05,271 --> 00:44:06,312
Thank God!

746
00:44:08,604 --> 00:44:10,729
Let's do one thing.
Will file a police complaint.

747
00:44:12,812 --> 00:44:13,687
No!

748
00:44:14,979 --> 00:44:17,937
I mean, why file a police
complaint on a small child?

749
00:44:18,312 --> 00:44:20,021
Not on him, but for him!

750
00:44:20,104 --> 00:44:21,729
Do you have any sense?

751
00:44:22,021 --> 00:44:25,146
Will you make a pregnant woman
climb the stairs of a police station?

752
00:44:26,104 --> 00:44:27,271
Ask them to come here.

753
00:44:28,687 --> 00:44:31,271
-Good idea.
-Hey! Wait a minute, I forgot.

754
00:44:31,354 --> 00:44:35,479
Auntie, Mittu sometimes goes out
and comes back late at night.

755
00:44:35,562 --> 00:44:38,229
He's always pulling pranks.
Dumb! Why didn't you tell them?

756
00:44:40,354 --> 00:44:43,062
Auntie… Yes, auntie, I forgot.

757
00:44:44,146 --> 00:44:45,646
Oh goodness!

758
00:44:45,771 --> 00:44:47,062
-Uttara! What happened?
-Uttara!

759
00:44:47,146 --> 00:44:48,646
At this time, it's normal.
They just fall like that.

760
00:44:48,729 --> 00:44:50,396
Come on, let the air in. Go away.

761
00:44:50,479 --> 00:44:52,062
Why should we stay here? Let's go.

762
00:44:52,812 --> 00:44:54,937
Sriram, let's take her inside. Come on.

763
00:44:56,021 --> 00:44:57,187
Gently.

764
00:45:00,062 --> 00:45:01,437
Don't worry, Sriram.

765
00:45:02,771 --> 00:45:04,687
God knows everything.

766
00:45:04,771 --> 00:45:06,854
Knowing that one would be lost,
He prepared another.

767
00:45:07,354 --> 00:45:09,646
If you need anything, even in the
middle of the night, just call me.

768
00:45:09,771 --> 00:45:11,312
-Okay, auntie?
-Take care of the girl.

769
00:45:11,437 --> 00:45:12,812
-You take care too.
-Be careful.

770
00:45:21,604 --> 00:45:22,687
Oh, thank God! They're gone.

771
00:45:23,229 --> 00:45:26,104
By the way,
did you find a place to dump the body?

772
00:45:29,687 --> 00:45:32,312
Forget about the body. Where is he?

773
00:45:32,687 --> 00:45:34,354
He's eating Boost, sir.

774
00:45:37,146 --> 00:45:38,104
What?

775
00:45:38,312 --> 00:45:40,146
I'm the one who hid Mittu.

776
00:45:40,729 --> 00:45:42,229
How many twists do
you plan to pull this time?

777
00:45:42,437 --> 00:45:45,354
I mean, if the murder is revealed,

778
00:45:45,562 --> 00:45:48,604
we can prove that Mittu wasn't
even in the house today, right?

779
00:45:55,354 --> 00:45:56,229
For the first time,

780
00:45:57,479 --> 00:45:59,062
you've done something useful.

781
00:46:01,604 --> 00:46:02,854
Where is the artist?

782
00:46:07,979 --> 00:46:09,729
Mummy Boost…

783
00:46:18,812 --> 00:46:20,104
Slowly… slowly…

784
00:46:21,521 --> 00:46:22,437
This way…

785
00:46:27,062 --> 00:46:28,687
Why did you stop? Let's go.

786
00:46:30,729 --> 00:46:31,937
These things are always there.

787
00:46:32,062 --> 00:46:33,104
Hold it.

788
00:46:34,979 --> 00:46:36,021
I'll…

789
00:46:36,229 --> 00:46:38,437
After this,
we're performing the ritual, right?

790
00:46:39,854 --> 00:46:43,896
I mean… if we don't do the final rites,
he might turn into a ghost and haunt us.

791
00:46:44,646 --> 00:46:46,562
I've already been dealing with
two ghosts for ten years.

792
00:46:47,146 --> 00:46:48,104
This will be the third.

793
00:46:55,771 --> 00:46:56,729
Why did you switch off the light?

794
00:46:56,812 --> 00:46:58,687
Do people move a dead
body with the lights on?

795
00:46:58,854 --> 00:46:59,812
Go on…

796
00:47:00,521 --> 00:47:02,396
Your criminal thinking has no limits.

797
00:47:10,812 --> 00:47:11,979
Who could it be?

798
00:47:12,437 --> 00:47:13,396
Don't know.

799
00:47:26,729 --> 00:47:28,646
-Who is it?
-The police.

800
00:47:34,354 --> 00:47:36,354
What brings you here at this hour, sir?

801
00:47:36,604 --> 00:47:38,062
Some rogue boys from the next street

802
00:47:38,146 --> 00:47:39,812
were fighting in a group,
causing a big ruckus.

803
00:47:40,396 --> 00:47:41,854
To prevent further fights at night,

804
00:47:41,979 --> 00:47:43,437
we're placing two
policemen on each street.

805
00:47:43,521 --> 00:47:45,854
Our SI is also not on duty.

806
00:47:46,104 --> 00:47:47,562
We're managing somehow.

807
00:47:47,646 --> 00:47:49,896
It's nothing, sir. You
just switched off the light,

808
00:47:50,021 --> 00:47:52,104
so you must be awake. I
came to ask for some tea.

809
00:47:53,354 --> 00:47:55,062
You can come anytime, no problem.

810
00:47:55,146 --> 00:47:57,729
Look, wake up your wife
and ask her to make some tea.

811
00:47:57,812 --> 00:47:59,312
The ASI sir asked
for it, it won't be good.

812
00:47:59,437 --> 00:48:01,271
-Otherwise, we'll make it ourselves.
-No, no, no, no.

813
00:48:01,354 --> 00:48:03,479
-Come, he agreed.
-Come.

814
00:48:03,646 --> 00:48:05,062
What's the matter?

815
00:48:05,604 --> 00:48:06,812
Nothing sir…
Come in.

816
00:48:07,312 --> 00:48:08,187
Come here…

817
00:48:08,271 --> 00:48:09,771
Let's go and sit there at dining table.

818
00:48:09,854 --> 00:48:10,812
Uttara!

819
00:48:12,146 --> 00:48:13,021
Uttara!

820
00:48:13,812 --> 00:48:16,479
What is it, asking for tea
in the middle of the night?

821
00:48:19,104 --> 00:48:24,146
Well, when I wake her up in the
middle of the night, and asks for tea.

822
00:48:24,229 --> 00:48:25,146
Oh!

823
00:48:26,562 --> 00:48:27,771
Why he sits there?

824
00:48:38,146 --> 00:48:39,021
Well…

825
00:48:39,937 --> 00:48:42,396
The sofa springs are damaged.

826
00:48:42,562 --> 00:48:46,229
That's why she's worried.
Isn't it right?

827
00:48:47,312 --> 00:48:48,521
Go make some tea, will you?

828
00:48:51,146 --> 00:48:54,687
-Subramayam, where has this SI gone?
-Who knows, sir.

829
00:49:06,896 --> 00:49:08,312
You'll fall down.

830
00:49:09,354 --> 00:49:10,312
What?

831
00:49:10,729 --> 00:49:13,937
It's dark here… you
might fall and get hurt.

832
00:49:14,021 --> 00:49:16,104
Come on, let's go sit over there.

833
00:49:16,229 --> 00:49:17,229
Come…

834
00:49:25,896 --> 00:49:29,437
What's wrong, sir? You seem
tense and worried.

835
00:49:29,521 --> 00:49:30,646
-What's the matter?
-What the hell is he talking?

836
00:49:30,729 --> 00:49:31,604
Is this
how you treat a government officer?

837
00:49:31,687 --> 00:49:33,854
Did I come to your station,
or are you in my house?

838
00:49:34,021 --> 00:49:35,687
Leave it man, leave it.

839
00:49:35,771 --> 00:49:36,896
-What is this sir?
-That…

840
00:49:37,271 --> 00:49:38,771
Is that your son's photo?

841
00:49:39,396 --> 00:49:40,979
-Yes, sir.
-He looks like a bullet.

842
00:49:41,479 --> 00:49:44,312
Not like an ordinary bullet.
He'll be a six-round bullet.

843
00:49:45,312 --> 00:49:46,229
Its nice?

844
00:49:46,937 --> 00:49:48,021
Hey, won't you come?

845
00:49:48,562 --> 00:49:50,896
By the way, what's the issue
between you and the SI?

846
00:49:50,979 --> 00:49:52,396
He is the one who grabbed my collar

847
00:49:52,479 --> 00:49:53,979
-and insulted me.
-Yes.

848
00:49:54,062 --> 00:49:55,021
Give me, Madam.

849
00:49:55,187 --> 00:49:56,062
Thank you.

850
00:49:57,396 --> 00:49:58,562
The house is nice, though.

851
00:49:59,312 --> 00:50:01,229
-You've done it up well.
-What are you staring at my face for?

852
00:50:01,396 --> 00:50:02,437
I just thought they might want some Upma.

853
00:50:02,521 --> 00:50:03,937
-Upma?
-Hey, what are you saying, man?

854
00:50:04,021 --> 00:50:06,062
-You're all still sitting here?
-We had our dinner just now.

855
00:50:06,146 --> 00:50:07,771
-We just came for tea. Thanks, Madam.
-Thanks, Madam.

856
00:50:07,854 --> 00:50:08,854
Thanks, Sriram.

857
00:50:08,937 --> 00:50:10,021
Don't hesitate, sir. If you want
some tiffin, go ahead, eat.

858
00:50:10,104 --> 00:50:12,687
-Sorry for bothering you at night.
-I'll give it to you in the morning, sir.

859
00:50:13,021 --> 00:50:14,229
Anyway, we won't let it go.

860
00:50:17,271 --> 00:50:18,979
Hey! Stop it.
There are cops over there!

861
00:50:19,896 --> 00:50:21,229
Reverse it, reverse it!

862
00:50:21,562 --> 00:50:22,562
Quickly.

863
00:50:22,646 --> 00:50:25,062
Why are they sitting here
instead of doing their duty?

864
00:50:26,979 --> 00:50:28,229
Hey, stop here.

865
00:50:28,979 --> 00:50:30,104
Hey, turn off the light.

866
00:50:36,812 --> 00:50:37,812
Yes, tell me, duffer.

867
00:50:37,896 --> 00:50:38,979
We're right at the
corner of Prasad's street.

868
00:50:39,062 --> 00:50:41,479
Why are you calling
me instead of going in?

869
00:50:42,021 --> 00:50:44,354
How do we go? The police
are in the middle of the street.

870
00:50:45,021 --> 00:50:46,104
What are the police doing there?

871
00:50:49,146 --> 00:50:50,396
Shall I go and ask them?

872
00:50:50,604 --> 00:50:52,729
Shut up and give the phone to Madan.

873
00:50:54,437 --> 00:50:56,062
-Boss!
-You stay there

874
00:50:57,104 --> 00:50:58,896
and check after they leave.

875
00:50:59,687 --> 00:51:02,312
-There shouldn't be any doubt.
-Okay.

876
00:51:02,521 --> 00:51:07,312
That SI has an eye on us because
we aren't giving him commission.

877
00:51:07,562 --> 00:51:08,646
-Be careful.
-Okay.

878
00:51:09,646 --> 00:51:12,604
Did you find out anything
about that Yedukondalu?

879
00:51:12,729 --> 00:51:14,396
I said to our men. They'll find him.

880
00:51:32,479 --> 00:51:34,437
We must have to take the body out
tomorrow morning, right?

881
00:51:34,562 --> 00:51:35,562
Is the bike okay?

882
00:51:36,312 --> 00:51:38,937
Your neighbor Prasad has a car, right?
Convince him to give that to me.

883
00:51:39,062 --> 00:51:39,979
Because of his torture,

884
00:51:40,062 --> 00:51:42,271
I kept the car inside
saying not working even in good condition.

885
00:53:48,437 --> 00:53:50,187
302, go and check that side.

886
00:53:58,896 --> 00:53:59,812
-Hey, Mahi.
-Sir?

887
00:53:59,896 --> 00:54:02,354
-Go and inform the sniffer dog team. Go.
-Okay, sir.

888
00:54:03,562 --> 00:54:05,854
Sir, what happened?

889
00:54:05,937 --> 00:54:09,271
Some guy got drunk last night
and jumped from here.

890
00:54:09,396 --> 00:54:11,729
They're investigating whether
it's a suicide or a murder.

891
00:54:15,521 --> 00:54:17,771
Oh god! Police are here.

892
00:54:18,062 --> 00:54:19,104
Is he saw me?

893
00:54:19,187 --> 00:54:20,729
Sir, please give me the paper.

894
00:54:21,187 --> 00:54:22,354
He looks like Sriram.

895
00:54:22,979 --> 00:54:23,854
Sir!

896
00:54:27,979 --> 00:54:28,937
Sir… Sriram!

897
00:54:32,229 --> 00:54:33,187
Sir, I'm calling you, sir.

898
00:54:34,104 --> 00:54:37,021
Shit! He saw me.

899
00:54:37,937 --> 00:54:39,354
Why aren't you responding when I call?

900
00:54:39,979 --> 00:54:40,937
Well…

901
00:54:42,187 --> 00:54:43,271
But why are you here?

902
00:54:43,604 --> 00:54:47,271
My wife told me not to come home
without the flask, so I came.

903
00:54:47,562 --> 00:54:49,396
You came to a crime scene for this?

904
00:54:50,187 --> 00:54:52,687
If I don't take this home,
it'll be an even bigger crime.

905
00:54:57,396 --> 00:55:01,312
Early in the morning, just for a flask?
Something's not right.

906
00:55:13,521 --> 00:55:15,396
My loving sports car!

907
00:55:16,854 --> 00:55:18,896
-Sir, you…?
-Yes, its me.

908
00:55:18,979 --> 00:55:22,312
I know how to drive.
I'll drive the way I want.

909
00:55:31,437 --> 00:55:32,771
Damn the fate…

910
00:55:34,062 --> 00:55:36,437
In the very place I
planned to dump the body,

911
00:55:36,771 --> 00:55:38,771
someone else has committed suicide.

912
00:55:39,104 --> 00:55:41,146
Damn!

913
00:55:59,729 --> 00:56:05,729
NGO helping cremate unclaimed bodies,
showing humanity -Chittoor News Today.

914
00:56:21,729 --> 00:56:22,604
-Yes, sir.
-Uncle.

915
00:56:22,687 --> 00:56:23,687
-I'm checking that file only, sir.
-Uncle.

916
00:56:23,771 --> 00:56:24,896
-I'm right here at your desk, sir.
-Uncle.

917
00:56:25,146 --> 00:56:26,437
Okay, sir.
I'll do it right away.

918
00:56:26,812 --> 00:56:27,896
What is it?

919
00:56:28,062 --> 00:56:29,187
Why are you coming from that room?

920
00:56:29,271 --> 00:56:30,146
Uncle, forget that.

921
00:56:30,229 --> 00:56:32,187
This case has been pending
for a long time. I'll solve it.

922
00:56:32,271 --> 00:56:33,396
How many times do I have to tell you?

923
00:56:33,479 --> 00:56:35,354
If the SI finds out, it'll
be a problem. Leave it.

924
00:56:35,437 --> 00:56:37,146
Uncle, you can manage without him knowing.

925
00:56:37,229 --> 00:56:38,354
-Hey, will you listen to me?
-That…

926
00:56:38,937 --> 00:56:39,937
-Greetings, Madam.
-Greetings, sir.

927
00:56:40,021 --> 00:56:41,021
-Greetings.
-Sit.

928
00:56:42,437 --> 00:56:43,896
Tell them to get coffee or tea.

929
00:56:44,021 --> 00:56:44,896
I don't want anything.

930
00:56:45,479 --> 00:56:47,604
What is it, Madam?
Why did you come to the station so early?

931
00:56:48,104 --> 00:56:50,521
Vikram hasn't been
home for two days, uncle.

932
00:56:54,937 --> 00:56:56,479
And his phone is also not connecting.

933
00:56:56,562 --> 00:56:58,396
So, I came thinking he
might be at the station.

934
00:56:58,521 --> 00:57:02,062
He set out to handle a case.
Where did he go?

935
00:57:02,187 --> 00:57:03,562
-Tamballapalle.
-Yes,

936
00:57:03,646 --> 00:57:05,187
he headed to Tamballapalle
regarding a case.

937
00:57:05,271 --> 00:57:06,896
He'll be back.
Don't worry.

938
00:57:06,979 --> 00:57:07,854
Okay, uncle.

939
00:57:07,937 --> 00:57:08,854
-Don't forget to tell him.
-Okay.

940
00:57:08,937 --> 00:57:09,937
-It's a bit urgent.
-Sure.

941
00:57:10,021 --> 00:57:11,354
-Fine, uncle.
-Take care.

942
00:57:15,729 --> 00:57:17,271
Why are you laughing?

943
00:57:17,354 --> 00:57:19,646
What do you want me to do, sir?
You know about him.

944
00:57:19,729 --> 00:57:20,771
-So?
-What sir?

945
00:57:20,854 --> 00:57:21,812
You wait brother.

946
00:57:21,896 --> 00:57:24,021
Uncle, I'll solve this case.

947
00:57:24,104 --> 00:57:26,771
Hey, don't you listen?
Don't get into these cases.

948
00:57:28,312 --> 00:57:29,229
Hey!

949
00:57:29,437 --> 00:57:30,437
Madam came, right?

950
00:57:30,646 --> 00:57:34,312
Go find out where sir is and tell her.
She'll recommend you.

951
00:57:34,396 --> 00:57:35,271
And you'll get a promotion.

952
00:57:35,396 --> 00:57:36,396
What do you say?

953
00:57:42,437 --> 00:57:44,187
Shit!

954
00:57:44,562 --> 00:57:48,271
Who said yoga cures everything?

955
00:57:57,562 --> 00:57:59,271
Why are you calling, man?

956
00:57:59,562 --> 00:58:00,646
He's in shock…

957
00:58:00,854 --> 00:58:01,896
how can he talk?

958
00:58:01,979 --> 00:58:03,687
Shock? Why?

959
00:58:03,771 --> 00:58:05,021
Won't he be shocked if there's no gift?

960
00:58:05,437 --> 00:58:06,729
What do you mean, there's no gift?

961
00:58:06,812 --> 00:58:09,271
Do you know something?
There's no car here.

962
00:58:11,521 --> 00:58:15,562
There is no car?
Who took it?

963
00:58:18,812 --> 00:58:21,562
If we were aware of that,
we would've reached out to him.

964
00:58:21,771 --> 00:58:24,021
Why would I call you
about the missing car?

965
00:58:24,104 --> 00:58:28,146
Under any circumstances,
I need that car and the gift inside.

966
00:58:28,937 --> 00:58:31,187
Otherwise, both of you will be dead.

967
00:58:31,896 --> 00:58:33,062
You will be the first one.

968
00:58:34,271 --> 00:58:35,354
Remember that.

969
00:58:37,729 --> 00:58:40,437
So we'll mix this body
with the unclaimed ones

970
00:58:40,521 --> 00:58:43,062
and go to our parents' house
without anyone suspecting us.

971
00:58:46,354 --> 00:58:49,687
I'm the guy who smashes heads just for
fun. You really want to mess with me?

972
00:58:49,854 --> 00:58:50,729
Be careful.

973
00:58:50,979 --> 00:58:54,104
If I call my friends,
they'll smash your head too.

974
00:58:54,312 --> 00:58:55,271
Be careful.

975
00:58:55,521 --> 00:58:58,396
Did you see this reel?
Mittu has acted so well.

976
00:58:58,687 --> 00:59:00,229
Let's make him an actor.

977
00:59:00,521 --> 00:59:01,896
He committed a murder.

978
00:59:02,562 --> 00:59:04,021
What's acting to him?

979
00:59:05,479 --> 00:59:09,104
Besides, the film industry has been making
heroes out of villains for a long time.

980
00:59:09,604 --> 00:59:10,854
My son is not a villain.

981
00:59:12,187 --> 00:59:13,187
You're right.

982
00:59:14,854 --> 00:59:16,646
He's not a villain.
He's juts a henchman.

983
00:59:16,979 --> 00:59:18,521
-The main villain is you, right?
-What?

984
00:59:18,687 --> 00:59:19,646
Yes.

985
00:59:19,937 --> 00:59:20,854
Cut it… cut it…

986
00:59:20,937 --> 00:59:22,437
-cut the hen.
-Sleep my dear.

987
00:59:22,521 --> 00:59:23,396
Cut!

988
00:59:23,479 --> 00:59:25,146
First cut yourself,
then cut your mother's.

989
00:59:25,229 --> 00:59:26,104
That would be better.

990
00:59:26,187 --> 00:59:27,479
You scolding us is nothing new.

991
00:59:27,604 --> 00:59:29,854
-Just look ahead.
-And what if I don't?

992
00:59:35,562 --> 00:59:39,187
You could have told
me instead of screaming.

993
00:59:39,312 --> 00:59:41,604
Instead of shouting at me,
why don't you go and check?

994
00:59:43,562 --> 00:59:45,604
I'm this slow…
and you still dashed into my car?

995
00:59:46,021 --> 00:59:47,104
Is he alive… or not?

996
00:59:47,229 --> 00:59:48,229
Who the hell is this guy?

997
00:59:52,062 --> 00:59:53,062
Sir…

998
00:59:53,729 --> 00:59:54,646
Sir…

999
01:00:05,479 --> 01:00:06,604
What happened, dear?

1000
01:00:06,771 --> 01:00:08,062
-I think he's dead.
-What?

1001
01:00:08,271 --> 01:00:09,146
He's dead?

1002
01:00:09,437 --> 01:00:10,646
I hope no one is watching this.

1003
01:00:11,021 --> 01:00:12,771
Did this wretched man have
to fall under our car and die?

1004
01:00:14,812 --> 01:00:15,687
What do we do now?

1005
01:00:15,771 --> 01:00:16,646
Now…

1006
01:00:17,562 --> 01:00:20,062
Fourteen years for that murder.
Fourteen more for the accidental killing.

1007
01:00:20,146 --> 01:00:22,354
-What's wrong with him?
-And seven for hiding the truth.

1008
01:00:22,812 --> 01:00:24,646
-That's thirty-five years total.
-Dear.

1009
01:00:24,729 --> 01:00:26,479
-A lifetime behind bars.
-Dear.

1010
01:00:26,854 --> 01:00:28,104
Why are you whispering
to yourself like that?

1011
01:00:28,187 --> 01:00:29,604
Pack all the gold.

1012
01:00:30,729 --> 01:00:32,062
The chit fund money has to come, right?

1013
01:00:32,479 --> 01:00:33,562
Collect that too.

1014
01:00:34,312 --> 01:00:38,062
There are three acres in the village,
right? Transfer them to Mittu's name.

1015
01:00:39,771 --> 01:00:42,479
Also buy a sewing machine.
It'll take care of your monthly expenses.

1016
01:00:42,562 --> 01:00:44,646
Why are you talking irrelevantly, honey?

1017
01:00:45,187 --> 01:00:46,062
What about him?

1018
01:00:46,146 --> 01:00:47,437
We have no connection with him.

1019
01:00:47,562 --> 01:00:48,562
Let's just leave him here.

1020
01:00:51,062 --> 01:00:55,062
I mean, we can even put him in the trunk.
He'll keep him company.

1021
01:00:55,687 --> 01:00:56,604
Dad!

1022
01:00:56,687 --> 01:00:57,979
You are making reel without me.

1023
01:00:58,104 --> 01:00:59,521
The connection is established.

1024
01:01:00,104 --> 01:01:01,354
Did you cause an accident?

1025
01:01:02,562 --> 01:01:04,604
Darn it!
I missed it, Dad!

1026
01:01:04,979 --> 01:01:06,271
What did you miss, sir?

1027
01:01:06,354 --> 01:01:09,812
I just saw a live accident video.
Do you know how many views it got?

1028
01:01:09,979 --> 01:01:12,354
If people knew you were in an accident,
I could have made a video.

1029
01:01:12,437 --> 01:01:13,521
It would have gotten a million views.

1030
01:01:16,854 --> 01:01:17,729
I have an idea.

1031
01:01:18,104 --> 01:01:19,771
Let's place the body straight,

1032
01:01:19,937 --> 01:01:23,646
take the car to that corner,
and drive at 120 speed. Okay?

1033
01:01:24,437 --> 01:01:28,729
I'll record a video from a low angle.
And then we'll smash him.

1034
01:01:29,146 --> 01:01:30,646
It'll be a complete mess.

1035
01:01:30,729 --> 01:01:33,854
Okay? A million views.

1036
01:01:37,396 --> 01:01:39,812
You… what are you looking at?

1037
01:01:40,312 --> 01:01:41,562
Hey, Mittu!

1038
01:01:41,729 --> 01:01:43,271
Get into the car, quietly.

1039
01:01:43,479 --> 01:01:45,854
Please, Mom!
Just one video. Let's smash him.

1040
01:01:47,104 --> 01:01:50,104
-If I come, I'll beat you up. Get in!
-Just agree, Madam.

1041
01:01:50,479 --> 01:01:51,354
What?

1042
01:01:56,937 --> 01:01:58,812
Your son is just having fun… right?

1043
01:01:59,229 --> 01:02:01,687
Sir, are you not dead?

1044
01:02:01,771 --> 01:02:02,812
Of course not, sir.

1045
01:02:04,062 --> 01:02:06,146
Your family seems to
be planning something.

1046
01:02:06,937 --> 01:02:10,062
Do one thing.
Take the car back and smash it

1047
01:02:10,146 --> 01:02:11,562
-from the center at high speed.
-Super idea.

1048
01:02:11,646 --> 01:02:13,062
Sorry, sir.

1049
01:02:13,146 --> 01:02:14,896
-He says, "Run me over with the car,"
-Right uncle.

1050
01:02:14,979 --> 01:02:16,604
and she says, "Put me in the trunk."

1051
01:02:17,479 --> 01:02:22,396
I've never seen a family
this terrifying before.

1052
01:02:24,521 --> 01:02:25,729
What are you staring at?

1053
01:02:25,812 --> 01:02:26,896
Go and get in the car.

1054
01:02:27,521 --> 01:02:28,396
Sir! Sir! Sir!

1055
01:02:28,479 --> 01:02:30,104
-Great, man!
-Please sir.

1056
01:02:30,187 --> 01:02:31,062
Sorry, sir.

1057
01:02:31,146 --> 01:02:32,104
-Okay, okay, okay.
-Sorry sir.

1058
01:02:32,187 --> 01:02:33,271
-No need to touch my feet.
-Sir--

1059
01:02:34,354 --> 01:02:35,437
Please keep it sir.

1060
01:02:36,062 --> 01:02:37,229
This is fine for me.

1061
01:02:37,896 --> 01:02:39,354
But what about the vehicle?

1062
01:02:41,021 --> 01:02:43,146
Yours is a big car, right?
Let's get in that.

1063
01:02:45,729 --> 01:02:48,437
-You've seen enough, come on.
-Oh my God, what is this torture?

1064
01:02:52,437 --> 01:02:55,562
Hey, don't talk anything over with him.

1065
01:02:55,979 --> 01:02:59,229
-Now, It'll be fun.
-Please come, sir.

1066
01:02:59,812 --> 01:03:00,854
Let's go.

1067
01:03:01,104 --> 01:03:02,979
Ma'am, don't worry.

1068
01:03:03,271 --> 01:03:05,062
If your husband hits anyone again,

1069
01:03:05,312 --> 01:03:07,271
we'll throw him in the trunk.
There's enough space, right?

1070
01:03:21,312 --> 01:03:22,187
Not you!

1071
01:03:23,146 --> 01:03:24,604
Hey!
You fool…

1072
01:03:24,729 --> 01:03:25,604
Come here.

1073
01:03:25,937 --> 01:03:26,812
Come here.

1074
01:03:27,104 --> 01:03:28,021
Hey!

1075
01:03:28,604 --> 01:03:32,104
So you thought you could betray us
and hide in jail, and we wouldn't notice?

1076
01:03:33,146 --> 01:03:35,104
We have informers everywhere.

1077
01:03:35,229 --> 01:03:36,354
Hell with them.

1078
01:03:36,521 --> 01:03:38,104
It was me who made the
constable call you,

1079
01:03:38,187 --> 01:03:39,896
-you duffer!
-Michael!

1080
01:03:40,021 --> 01:03:43,896
Do you think anyone would
go to jail to hide? You dumb!

1081
01:03:44,312 --> 01:03:45,229
Enough of this.

1082
01:03:45,729 --> 01:03:46,604
Where's the gift?

1083
01:03:49,104 --> 01:03:51,437
-The other night, I…
-I didn't ask your whereabouts.

1084
01:03:51,854 --> 01:03:53,021
I asked you where's the gift?

1085
01:03:57,146 --> 01:03:59,021
Will you move,
or do I have to make you?

1086
01:04:02,062 --> 01:04:02,937
You tell me.

1087
01:04:03,479 --> 01:04:04,896
Last night when I went for the gift,

1088
01:04:04,979 --> 01:04:06,896
the SI suspected me of
being a thief and locked me up.

1089
01:04:07,187 --> 01:04:08,396
I've been here ever since.

1090
01:04:09,062 --> 01:04:10,437
So you didn't take the gift.

1091
01:04:10,562 --> 01:04:11,521
Then how did you take out the car?

1092
01:04:16,104 --> 01:04:17,146
You…

1093
01:04:17,604 --> 01:04:19,979
The Salar Prabhas has arrived.

1094
01:04:26,104 --> 01:04:27,062
Now tell me.

1095
01:04:27,312 --> 01:04:28,979
If it's not you, then who did it?

1096
01:04:35,521 --> 01:04:36,521
-Please sir…
-Tell me the truth.

1097
01:04:36,604 --> 01:04:37,937
-Let me go, sir.
-You…

1098
01:04:38,021 --> 01:04:39,354
I'll tell you everything, sir.

1099
01:04:39,604 --> 01:04:42,437
MLA Thimmappa regularly
sends a bag to the Minister.

1100
01:04:42,729 --> 01:04:44,062
It's in the PA's car.

1101
01:04:44,437 --> 01:04:46,979
I was on my way to pick it up
when you arrested me.

1102
01:04:49,146 --> 01:04:50,937
Bloody scoundrel!

1103
01:04:51,437 --> 01:04:52,646
He got us at just the right moment.

1104
01:04:54,104 --> 01:04:54,979
Hey!

1105
01:04:55,562 --> 01:04:57,521
Under any circumstances,
SI should not be missed.

1106
01:04:58,937 --> 01:04:59,937
Search everywhere for him.

1107
01:05:00,187 --> 01:05:01,104
Okay, brother.

1108
01:05:05,937 --> 01:05:07,437
Does it not go beyond this speed?

1109
01:05:07,562 --> 01:05:09,729
It will, but not him.

1110
01:05:10,062 --> 01:05:11,437
Second gear…

1111
01:05:11,937 --> 01:05:12,812
Look over there.

1112
01:05:12,896 --> 01:05:14,521
What a strange family.

1113
01:05:14,896 --> 01:05:15,896
Hello, respond.

1114
01:05:16,604 --> 01:05:17,479
No.

1115
01:05:17,562 --> 01:05:18,479
Thank you.

1116
01:05:24,646 --> 01:05:28,062
-Sir, are you a policeman?
-No.

1117
01:05:28,771 --> 01:05:29,646
This belongs to the police.

1118
01:05:29,729 --> 01:05:30,979
Then why do you have it?

1119
01:05:31,062 --> 01:05:32,646
I need to know how much I've drunk, right?

1120
01:05:32,729 --> 01:05:36,437
Oh! Why do you need a test for
that? It's obvious from looking at you.

1121
01:05:37,312 --> 01:05:38,187
Hey!

1122
01:05:38,354 --> 01:05:40,729
Don't talk without knowing
the reason why I was drunk…

1123
01:05:41,271 --> 01:05:43,771
I only drink
when I'm doing something important.

1124
01:05:44,062 --> 01:05:47,021
He's not the important one.
What does he have that matters so much?

1125
01:05:47,812 --> 01:05:50,021
Is there anything…

1126
01:05:52,729 --> 01:05:54,646
…more important…
…than a missing SI?

1127
01:06:02,312 --> 01:06:07,437
You look like a nice, cute, small family.

1128
01:06:07,604 --> 01:06:11,687
But I'm the only one who
knows your true colors.

1129
01:06:12,729 --> 01:06:15,604
-You took him and…
-Don't talk…

1130
01:06:15,687 --> 01:06:17,271
did something to him.
That's what I suspect.

1131
01:06:17,354 --> 01:06:19,646
-No, we didn't take him.
-He came on his own.

1132
01:06:20,479 --> 01:06:22,687
Didn't I tell you not to talk?

1133
01:06:24,479 --> 01:06:25,646
So he came, did he?

1134
01:06:25,729 --> 01:06:28,187
Yes, he did.
Uncle and I played together too.

1135
01:06:31,521 --> 01:06:32,854
What did you do with
him when he came home?

1136
01:06:34,396 --> 01:06:35,562
We didn't do anything, sir.

1137
01:06:36,229 --> 01:06:37,146
Tell me!

1138
01:06:37,562 --> 01:06:41,062
Tell me! Are you alone,
or is your whole family involved?

1139
01:06:41,354 --> 01:06:42,979
What are you looking around for?

1140
01:06:43,104 --> 01:06:45,062
-I'm a bigger artist than you.
-Please sir…

1141
01:06:45,146 --> 01:06:46,729
-Did you kill him? Tell me!
-No sir.

1142
01:06:46,854 --> 01:06:48,937
Did you kill him and put him in the trunk?

1143
01:06:50,896 --> 01:06:52,771
Super shot, mom.
You hit him well.

1144
01:06:56,354 --> 01:06:57,604
Why did you hit him?

1145
01:06:57,937 --> 01:06:59,437
I didn't know what else to do.

1146
01:07:00,062 --> 01:07:01,187
You do something.

1147
01:07:02,187 --> 01:07:03,354
Damn!

1148
01:07:08,187 --> 01:07:10,146
-Yes, Sudheer. Tell me.
-It's nothing, man.

1149
01:07:10,229 --> 01:07:12,479
I'll send you a number.

1150
01:07:12,687 --> 01:07:14,521
Can you track it and send
me the location details?

1151
01:07:14,979 --> 01:07:16,562
Sure. Is it official or unofficial?

1152
01:07:17,562 --> 01:07:19,146
It's a family matter,
maintain confidentiality.

1153
01:07:19,312 --> 01:07:21,146
Okay, WhatsApp me the number.

1154
01:07:24,312 --> 01:07:27,312
If you find out where the sir is and tell
the madam, she will recommend you…

1155
01:07:27,396 --> 01:07:28,521
and you will get a promotion.

1156
01:07:38,646 --> 01:07:40,687
MINISTER IS ASKING ABOUT GIFT

1157
01:08:06,562 --> 01:08:08,396
-Hi, Dad.
-Hi dear.

1158
01:08:08,521 --> 01:08:09,979
What's this?
You seem to be in a lot of tension.

1159
01:08:10,146 --> 01:08:11,354
I deal with this kind
of tension all the time.

1160
01:08:11,479 --> 01:08:13,229
Sir, good morning.

1161
01:08:14,812 --> 01:08:15,937
-Sir.
-What is it?

1162
01:08:16,646 --> 01:08:19,354
-Your daughter drives really well, sir.
-Good.

1163
01:08:20,854 --> 01:08:22,562
-Sir…
-What again?

1164
01:08:22,896 --> 01:08:27,104
You said you'd give me a car if I
teach your daughter to drive, right, sir?

1165
01:08:27,187 --> 01:08:29,854
I'll check and arrange you
some random car. Go now.

1166
01:08:30,187 --> 01:08:31,562
Not just some random car, sir.

1167
01:08:31,812 --> 01:08:34,937
Your PA Prasad has one, right?
That sports car.

1168
01:08:35,229 --> 01:08:36,146
Get me that, sir.

1169
01:08:36,271 --> 01:08:38,146
It would be a great addition
to my driving school, sir.

1170
01:08:38,604 --> 01:08:41,187
He always used to say
it was sentimental and didn't work.

1171
01:08:41,396 --> 01:08:44,604
I saw it this morning, sir.
It's working very well, sir.

1172
01:08:44,979 --> 01:08:46,729
-Did you see it this morning?
-Yes, sir.

1173
01:08:46,896 --> 01:08:48,312
-Where?
-At Horsley hills.

1174
01:08:48,479 --> 01:08:51,021
That village's Panchayat Secretary
Sriram was driving it.

1175
01:08:57,146 --> 01:08:59,812
Bring our gift bag.

1176
01:08:59,896 --> 01:09:01,687
Hey, you filthy swine!

1177
01:09:03,562 --> 01:09:05,062
Who are you?
Why are you climbing up the wall?

1178
01:09:05,229 --> 01:09:06,146
Hey, old woman!

1179
01:09:06,604 --> 01:09:07,521
Sriram isn't at home?

1180
01:09:07,604 --> 01:09:08,479
You…duffer.

1181
01:09:09,229 --> 01:09:10,937
Are your eyes blind?

1182
01:09:11,229 --> 01:09:12,646
The door is locked,
so he's not here, right?

1183
01:09:12,729 --> 01:09:15,437
-You old fool!
-Where did he go?

1184
01:09:15,521 --> 01:09:18,604
Who does he have in this town
except his in-laws in Chittoor?

1185
01:09:30,812 --> 01:09:31,937
What is this, Dear?

1186
01:09:32,146 --> 01:09:34,604
There are so many good restaurants
on the way, why did you bring us here?

1187
01:09:35,271 --> 01:09:37,771
-Not good at all.
-I can't take a risk with both of you.

1188
01:09:39,062 --> 01:09:40,229
You've seen enough.

1189
01:09:40,646 --> 01:09:41,771
You know about my driving, right?

1190
01:09:42,479 --> 01:09:43,646
It's a long way to go.

1191
01:09:43,896 --> 01:09:44,771
Make it fast.

1192
01:09:50,479 --> 01:09:51,354
Tell me, Sandeep.

1193
01:09:51,437 --> 01:09:52,937
You sent SI Venkat's number, right?

1194
01:09:53,187 --> 01:09:55,146
The tower location is
showing Horsley Hills.

1195
01:09:55,812 --> 01:09:56,771
Thank you, Sandeep.

1196
01:09:58,396 --> 01:09:59,729
Sriram is not at home, boss.

1197
01:10:00,354 --> 01:10:01,896
It seems he's gone to his
relatives' house in Chittoor.

1198
01:10:02,146 --> 01:10:03,771
I don't need information!

1199
01:10:04,062 --> 01:10:05,396
I need confirmation!

1200
01:10:06,521 --> 01:10:07,562
NAGRAJ HOTEL
TEA TIFFINS PREPARATION

1201
01:10:07,646 --> 01:10:09,396
Where's your father?
Where did he go?

1202
01:10:09,479 --> 01:10:10,979
I went to the washroom.
Did you pay the bill?

1203
01:10:11,562 --> 01:10:12,437
Yes.

1204
01:10:17,312 --> 01:10:19,562
Uncle, did our SI come this way?

1205
01:10:19,646 --> 01:10:21,729
I saw him going toward
Panchayat Secretary Sriram's house.

1206
01:10:29,771 --> 01:10:31,396
-Hello?
-Hey, Sriram.

1207
01:10:31,854 --> 01:10:35,646
You interfered and stopped the villagers
from signing the documents.

1208
01:10:36,521 --> 01:10:38,729
Then I found out you're an honest officer,

1209
01:10:39,187 --> 01:10:41,146
and I knew I couldn't get my work done
with you around.

1210
01:10:41,687 --> 01:10:43,187
So, I changed my route.

1211
01:10:43,271 --> 01:10:46,396
But you turned into a speed bump
on that route as well.

1212
01:10:48,521 --> 01:10:51,396
So now, I'm going to destroy
the whole damn road.

1213
01:10:52,271 --> 01:10:53,271
Mark my words.

1214
01:10:54,271 --> 01:10:56,646
In the graveyard I'm about to build…

1215
01:10:58,437 --> 01:11:02,187
your grave will be the first.

1216
01:11:05,229 --> 01:11:06,396
You scoundrel.

1217
01:11:19,062 --> 01:11:20,562
Hey auto, stop aside.

1218
01:11:34,896 --> 01:11:36,479
Yo! Go check out that vehicle.

1219
01:11:36,604 --> 01:11:37,854
You! Pull it over! Right here!

1220
01:11:37,937 --> 01:11:39,687
Hey! Get out.
I said, Get out!

1221
01:11:39,812 --> 01:11:41,812
-Sir… please, sir.
-Are you dealing ganja?

1222
01:11:41,979 --> 01:11:43,562
-Are you dealing ganja?
-Sir… please, sir.

1223
01:11:57,979 --> 01:11:58,979
Sir, open the trunk.

1224
01:12:57,104 --> 01:12:58,146
Sir, open the trunk.

1225
01:13:03,521 --> 01:13:05,396
We are going on a vacation with my family.

1226
01:13:05,896 --> 01:13:07,396
-It's just luggage, nothing else.
-Hey!

1227
01:13:07,479 --> 01:13:09,312
-Okay, madam. First, open the trunk.
-Look into it.

1228
01:13:11,771 --> 01:13:12,854
Who do you think we are?

1229
01:13:12,979 --> 01:13:14,896
My husband is the Panchayat
Secretary, do you know that?

1230
01:13:15,229 --> 01:13:16,104
Sir!

1231
01:13:16,687 --> 01:13:18,021
Sir, they refused to open the car trunk.

1232
01:13:18,729 --> 01:13:19,771
Keep quiet for a while.

1233
01:13:20,896 --> 01:13:22,312
He is asking you to open it.

1234
01:13:22,771 --> 01:13:23,771
We will sir.

1235
01:13:23,937 --> 01:13:24,937
Open it.

1236
01:13:27,229 --> 01:13:28,187
Who is he?

1237
01:13:28,437 --> 01:13:30,604
He's my brother-in-law, sir.
He's not well.

1238
01:13:30,812 --> 01:13:31,771
Go open the trunk.

1239
01:13:34,062 --> 01:13:35,271
There's nothing, sir.
It's luggage.

1240
01:13:35,354 --> 01:13:36,354
Alright, madam.
Let me check.

1241
01:13:55,812 --> 01:13:56,896
Did he chop the body into pieces?

1242
01:14:07,562 --> 01:14:08,437
What is it?

1243
01:14:09,187 --> 01:14:10,062
Nothing, sir.

1244
01:14:13,354 --> 01:14:14,354
It seems there's nothing.

1245
01:14:15,312 --> 01:14:17,729
-Why waste our time on that? Go, go, go.
-Sir.

1246
01:14:18,437 --> 01:14:19,312
Get in.

1247
01:14:21,396 --> 01:14:22,604
Hi, uncle.

1248
01:14:23,187 --> 01:14:25,354
Do you also do a soft
search like movie cops?

1249
01:14:26,062 --> 01:14:27,062
Didn't you check the box
on top of the car?

1250
01:14:29,396 --> 01:14:30,521
-Hey Sanjay!
-Sir!

1251
01:14:30,604 --> 01:14:32,021
There's another box on top.

1252
01:14:32,354 --> 01:14:34,979
They already knows.
You get inside.

1253
01:14:59,687 --> 01:15:01,021
Sir! Gun.

1254
01:15:05,812 --> 01:15:07,021
Hey, It's a toy gun.

1255
01:15:11,021 --> 01:15:12,604
That's my gun.
Give it to me.

1256
01:15:12,687 --> 01:15:13,562
Okay, okay.
Keep it with you.

1257
01:15:13,646 --> 01:15:14,854
Give that to him.

1258
01:15:15,021 --> 01:15:16,271
-Place the box on top of the car.
-Okay sir.

1259
01:15:21,187 --> 01:15:22,104
Uncle!

1260
01:15:22,187 --> 01:15:23,229
Your gun is nice.

1261
01:15:25,604 --> 01:15:27,521
-Shall we exchange our guns?
-Hey!

1262
01:15:27,604 --> 01:15:29,479
I can't give this to you. It's not safe.

1263
01:15:29,854 --> 01:15:30,771
It's nothing.

1264
01:15:30,854 --> 01:15:33,562
I even played with a police uncle
using a gun like this.

1265
01:15:34,021 --> 01:15:35,104
I already shot him.

1266
01:15:35,437 --> 01:15:39,021
I mean, I have a friend
who works as an SI.

1267
01:15:39,104 --> 01:15:41,187
He's saying he played
'cops and robbers' with him.

1268
01:15:41,437 --> 01:15:42,729
-Please uncle, will you give it once?
-No dear.

1269
01:15:42,812 --> 01:15:44,062
Sir, sir! No, sir.

1270
01:15:44,312 --> 01:15:46,479
We know how to be careful.
How can I give this to a kid?

1271
01:15:46,812 --> 01:15:47,729
Go, go.

1272
01:16:02,771 --> 01:16:03,812
Where's the body?

1273
01:16:04,187 --> 01:16:05,312
Why aren't you answering when I ask?

1274
01:16:05,687 --> 01:16:06,771
Where's the body?

1275
01:16:11,187 --> 01:16:13,437
Kid, take this parcel

1276
01:16:13,521 --> 01:16:14,771
and give it to the
police at the checkpost.

1277
01:16:14,854 --> 01:16:16,854
-Okay.
-No profit for us…

1278
01:16:16,937 --> 01:16:18,521
all we do is serve them.

1279
01:16:18,771 --> 01:16:20,729
-Hey, wait. Wait.
-What?

1280
01:16:20,812 --> 01:16:22,437
Take the cigarettes for the CI.

1281
01:16:22,521 --> 01:16:23,854
Otherwise, he'll bother us in the evening.

1282
01:16:23,937 --> 01:16:25,729
-Hey, Khan, give him the cigarettes.
-Give it to me.

1283
01:16:32,896 --> 01:16:33,854
Kid!

1284
01:16:34,104 --> 01:16:35,812
Is there a checkpost nearby?

1285
01:16:36,062 --> 01:16:39,021
Yes, brother.
It's at the corner after that turn.

1286
01:16:39,312 --> 01:16:40,604
It wasn't there before, right?

1287
01:16:40,937 --> 01:16:44,312
They set it up recently because ganja
smuggling has gone up, brother.

1288
01:16:44,396 --> 01:16:45,437
Is that so?

1289
01:16:45,604 --> 01:16:46,604
Okay, go.

1290
01:17:10,562 --> 01:17:14,271
When she died and he couldn't make it,
I called the paid mourners from Vellore.

1291
01:17:17,896 --> 01:17:19,812
-Rajendra.
-Sriram, tell me.

1292
01:17:19,896 --> 01:17:22,396
You told me about the
paid mourners recently, right?

1293
01:17:23,062 --> 01:17:26,104
-Do they live only in Vellore?
-No, you can find them here as well.

1294
01:17:26,229 --> 01:17:27,354
Why do you ask?

1295
01:17:29,937 --> 01:17:31,979
I came to other village for work.

1296
01:17:32,354 --> 01:17:34,062
There's an unidentified body
on the road here.

1297
01:17:34,146 --> 01:17:35,771
-I felt like helping.
-Oh no!

1298
01:17:35,896 --> 01:17:37,729
Alright, okay, okay.
I'm sending their number.

1299
01:17:39,187 --> 01:17:40,896
Hey, told them about the work?

1300
01:17:40,979 --> 01:17:42,271
No, they're not even listening.

1301
01:17:42,354 --> 01:17:43,354
It's not about drinking,
you have to work.

1302
01:17:43,437 --> 01:17:45,229
Brother, I need a favor from you.

1303
01:17:45,562 --> 01:17:46,937
Rajendra already told me.

1304
01:17:47,354 --> 01:17:48,937
We'll do it.
What's the payment?

1305
01:17:58,229 --> 01:18:00,396
Sanjay, let them go.

1306
01:18:10,604 --> 01:18:11,812
-Hey! Hey!
-Mittu!

1307
01:18:21,562 --> 01:18:23,229
-Thank you.
-Thank you sir.

1308
01:18:33,104 --> 01:18:34,021
Dad!

1309
01:18:34,229 --> 01:18:35,229
That uncle is…

1310
01:18:37,312 --> 01:18:38,479
Police uncle. Hi!

1311
01:18:38,646 --> 01:18:39,771
But what is he doing here?

1312
01:18:40,687 --> 01:18:42,937
The police uncle is making a reel

1313
01:18:43,021 --> 01:18:44,479
about
what it's like to peep from the trunk.

1314
01:18:44,562 --> 01:18:45,646
I'll do it, I'll do it.

1315
01:18:45,729 --> 01:18:46,854
-Will you?
-I don't.

1316
01:18:46,937 --> 01:18:47,812
-Will you?
-I don't.

1317
01:18:47,896 --> 01:18:49,062
-Will you?
-Leave me.

1318
01:18:49,187 --> 01:18:50,062
Go and sit.

1319
01:18:50,521 --> 01:18:51,479
Go!

1320
01:18:51,729 --> 01:18:52,812
I'll sit here.

1321
01:18:56,646 --> 01:18:58,896
He's growing in age, but not in sense?

1322
01:19:00,271 --> 01:19:03,021
So, you overacted this much
knowing there was no body in the car?

1323
01:19:03,312 --> 01:19:05,479
Do you know how tense I was?
Why did you do that?

1324
01:19:06,812 --> 01:19:08,562
Even with all my caution,

1325
01:19:08,896 --> 01:19:11,896
Our son was about to reveal the
information to the police.

1326
01:19:11,979 --> 01:19:14,771
And if you knew I was
covering all this,

1327
01:19:15,146 --> 01:19:17,146
how many more things would
you two have leaked?

1328
01:19:18,187 --> 01:19:19,354
Enough! Anyway, those people did so much,

1329
01:19:19,937 --> 01:19:22,229
you could have just asked them
to cremate the body, right?

1330
01:19:23,062 --> 01:19:23,937
You don't know anything.

1331
01:19:24,021 --> 01:19:25,979
Then we can directly
go to the police station.

1332
01:19:26,062 --> 01:19:29,229
You fool! To cremate a body
in another village,

1333
01:19:29,312 --> 01:19:31,271
you need permission from the Sarpanch,
the Panchayat Secretary,

1334
01:19:31,354 --> 01:19:32,812
and the villagers.

1335
01:19:33,021 --> 01:19:35,937
Now, it's not him,
the procession will be for us.

1336
01:19:37,521 --> 01:19:38,479
Please…

1337
01:19:38,729 --> 01:19:39,979
You stick to that witty mind of yours.

1338
01:19:40,187 --> 01:19:41,396
Just don't think like a criminal, please.

1339
01:19:41,479 --> 01:19:42,437
I can't.

1340
01:19:42,937 --> 01:19:45,146
That's enough seeing.
Get in, it's getting late.

1341
01:19:46,062 --> 01:19:47,062
You know my driving, right?

1342
01:19:47,229 --> 01:19:48,479
I don't know, sir.

1343
01:19:48,979 --> 01:19:49,854
They were here yesterday…

1344
01:19:49,937 --> 01:19:51,937
but by morning, the house was locked.

1345
01:19:55,062 --> 01:19:56,437
Can you call him once?

1346
01:20:01,646 --> 01:20:03,021
Why is he calling now?

1347
01:20:05,729 --> 01:20:07,312
-Hello.
-Hello, Sriram.

1348
01:20:07,396 --> 01:20:08,646
Yes, Mr. Murali, tell me.

1349
01:20:08,854 --> 01:20:10,521
Where did you go?
The house is locked.

1350
01:20:12,354 --> 01:20:15,896
We are going to my in-laws' house
in Chittoor for the festival.

1351
01:20:16,187 --> 01:20:17,854
That's the matter.
He went to Chittoor.

1352
01:20:20,271 --> 01:20:22,271
Going before the festival makes sense,

1353
01:20:22,812 --> 01:20:24,104
but what's with going after the festival?

1354
01:20:28,354 --> 01:20:29,354
Chittoor?

1355
01:20:29,437 --> 01:20:31,354
HINDU CEMENTERY - CHITTOOR

1356
01:20:31,437 --> 01:20:33,479
ELECTRIC CREMATORIUM

1357
01:20:33,562 --> 01:20:35,646
Hey, why are you throwing
all the weight on me?

1358
01:20:36,021 --> 01:20:37,687
Otherwise, should I
carry it all by myself?

1359
01:20:37,979 --> 01:20:38,854
Hold it.

1360
01:20:39,687 --> 01:20:40,562
Turn it.

1361
01:20:41,812 --> 01:20:42,687
Place it.

1362
01:20:46,021 --> 01:20:48,229
Hey! I have a small errand.
I'll be back after finishing it.

1363
01:20:48,312 --> 01:20:50,146
It's okay even if you're late.
Finish all your work and come.

1364
01:20:50,229 --> 01:20:51,354
In this gap, my work will also be done.

1365
01:20:51,437 --> 01:20:53,062
What, man?
Hey, are you bluffing?

1366
01:20:53,146 --> 01:20:54,104
What did I do?

1367
01:20:54,187 --> 01:20:58,062
Last week, because of your negligence,
wild boars tore apart and ate a corpse.

1368
01:20:58,562 --> 01:21:01,604
It was just a corpse they ate.
You're acting like they ate you.

1369
01:21:01,937 --> 01:21:02,979
This is what I don't want.

1370
01:21:03,354 --> 01:21:05,479
Because of your grace,
we made it to all the newspapers.

1371
01:21:05,604 --> 01:21:08,312
Officers can come for inspection anytime.
Understood?

1372
01:21:08,437 --> 01:21:10,479
So, shut up and stay quiet.
Be careful.

1373
01:21:12,812 --> 01:21:14,312
Let's see who has come.

1374
01:21:17,146 --> 01:21:18,062
Have you seen him?

1375
01:21:19,854 --> 01:21:20,729
He came there.

1376
01:21:21,396 --> 01:21:22,271
Which way did he go?

1377
01:21:22,354 --> 01:21:24,187
This way, towards Chittoor.

1378
01:21:25,729 --> 01:21:26,604
How long has it been?

1379
01:21:27,729 --> 01:21:29,479
How long…

1380
01:21:29,687 --> 01:21:31,062
It must have been about half an hour.

1381
01:21:32,729 --> 01:21:35,854
If it's been half an hour,
he wouldn't have gone far.

1382
01:21:38,479 --> 01:21:39,396
Hey, where are you?

1383
01:21:39,479 --> 01:21:40,687
I'm sending you a photo.

1384
01:21:40,812 --> 01:21:42,687
Some of their relatives are in Chittoor.

1385
01:21:43,187 --> 01:21:45,354
Find out all the address
details and call me.

1386
01:21:50,437 --> 01:21:52,562
PALAMANERU 06
CHITTOOR 48

1387
01:21:52,687 --> 01:21:56,354
You're driving very fast.
Can you slow down a bit?

1388
01:21:59,396 --> 01:22:01,646
If we had known this,
we would have started yesterday itself.

1389
01:22:02,354 --> 01:22:03,229
Right?

1390
01:22:03,312 --> 01:22:04,312
Don't irritate me.

1391
01:22:05,312 --> 01:22:06,562
Your dad is changing the gear.

1392
01:22:11,771 --> 01:22:14,187
The vehicle didn't stall.
Dad has learned to drive in third gear.

1393
01:22:14,937 --> 01:22:16,854
I haven't put into second gear yet.

1394
01:22:26,104 --> 01:22:27,021
Tell me.

1395
01:22:36,062 --> 01:22:36,937
Okay.

1396
01:22:44,062 --> 01:22:44,937
Okay.

1397
01:22:45,062 --> 01:22:46,021
I'll take care of it.

1398
01:22:54,937 --> 01:22:57,354
Why are you still here?
Go fast.

1399
01:22:59,437 --> 01:23:00,396
Actually sir…

1400
01:23:00,604 --> 01:23:02,062
Without knowing who you are…

1401
01:23:02,604 --> 01:23:04,521
I…
It was unintentional…

1402
01:23:07,354 --> 01:23:08,562
I forgot to tell you.

1403
01:23:08,687 --> 01:23:11,562
By the way, my name is Raghava.

1404
01:23:11,937 --> 01:23:13,604
I am a drama artist.

1405
01:23:14,354 --> 01:23:16,396
-Drama artist.
-You…

1406
01:23:18,937 --> 01:23:20,312
Is your family full of brake inspectors?

1407
01:23:20,687 --> 01:23:22,354
You hit the brakes for everything?
Hello.

1408
01:23:23,937 --> 01:23:24,854
Let's go.

1409
01:23:26,854 --> 01:23:27,854
Uncle.

1410
01:23:27,937 --> 01:23:29,021
That…

1411
01:23:29,104 --> 01:23:30,479
You said you were a reporter earlier?

1412
01:23:30,812 --> 01:23:32,521
A reporter?
Who is he?

1413
01:23:32,604 --> 01:23:33,979
You said you were doing
a sting operation on us?

1414
01:23:34,271 --> 01:23:35,562
A sting operation?

1415
01:23:35,979 --> 01:23:38,021
What did you do to
warrant a sting operation?

1416
01:23:38,271 --> 01:23:41,146
You said the police uncle
who came to our house is missing, right?

1417
01:23:42,812 --> 01:23:44,312
Police missing?

1418
01:23:44,437 --> 01:23:45,354
Yes.

1419
01:23:48,062 --> 01:23:49,062
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

1420
01:23:49,812 --> 01:23:50,937
One second.

1421
01:23:58,646 --> 01:23:59,812
Sir, I remember now.

1422
01:23:59,896 --> 01:24:01,271
A small clarification.

1423
01:24:02,062 --> 01:24:07,104
Before I got into the car,
did I have a small drink?

1424
01:24:08,146 --> 01:24:09,146
Yes, you had a small one, sir.

1425
01:24:09,229 --> 01:24:10,437
That's the reason.

1426
01:24:10,521 --> 01:24:11,437
Don't talk for sometime.

1427
01:24:11,521 --> 01:24:13,937
One peg is enough.
My body language changes.

1428
01:24:14,479 --> 01:24:15,479
What's that, sir?

1429
01:24:16,646 --> 01:24:19,062
I mean, I'm performing
a stage play tonight.

1430
01:24:19,146 --> 01:24:22,562
It's a character who catches the culprit
when a police officer goes missing.

1431
01:24:23,312 --> 01:24:25,521
Whatever I do, I do it naturally, right?

1432
01:24:26,229 --> 01:24:28,271
That's why you all got involved.

1433
01:24:28,979 --> 01:24:32,479
Well, ours is a family of artists.

1434
01:24:32,937 --> 01:24:35,729
If someone acts in front of us,
we naturally get involved with them.

1435
01:24:35,812 --> 01:24:37,187
-Oh!
-Interesting.

1436
01:24:37,271 --> 01:24:39,396
So, you didn't know
uncle was in the trunk.

1437
01:24:40,021 --> 01:24:41,062
Hey, shut up.

1438
01:24:41,437 --> 01:24:42,312
In a trunk?

1439
01:24:42,521 --> 01:24:44,021
-What do you mean?
-It's…

1440
01:24:45,021 --> 01:24:47,187
-Shut up and sit. Open your mouth,
-The thing is…

1441
01:24:47,312 --> 01:24:48,187
and I'll delete your Instagram.

1442
01:24:48,271 --> 01:24:49,979
I mean… now that he
knows you're an artist…

1443
01:24:50,062 --> 01:24:51,312
He's a child artist.

1444
01:24:51,396 --> 01:24:52,687
He's trying to outdo you.

1445
01:24:53,187 --> 01:24:54,229
Really?

1446
01:24:55,312 --> 01:24:56,437
Cute boy.

1447
01:24:56,521 --> 01:24:57,687
Same to you.

1448
01:24:58,937 --> 01:25:01,437
I have arrived at my destination,
can you pull over a bit?

1449
01:25:01,646 --> 01:25:03,396
Many VIPs are waiting for me.

1450
01:25:03,687 --> 01:25:05,562
I reached on time because of you.

1451
01:25:08,021 --> 01:25:09,021
-Okay sir.
-Okay, sir.

1452
01:25:09,104 --> 01:25:10,396
-Thank you, Madam.
-Bye, little one.

1453
01:25:10,479 --> 01:25:11,854
-Bye.
-Bye-bye.

1454
01:25:13,312 --> 01:25:14,354
Happy journey, sir.

1455
01:25:15,146 --> 01:25:16,562
Thank God, he got off.

1456
01:25:16,854 --> 01:25:19,521
Hey, shall we visit Tirupati
after this work is done?

1457
01:25:19,687 --> 01:25:20,687
Is the road closed?

1458
01:25:20,896 --> 01:25:22,104
I just made a vow, right?

1459
01:25:22,229 --> 01:25:23,687
What's the connection between the two?

1460
01:25:24,562 --> 01:25:25,562
Oh no!

1461
01:25:29,021 --> 01:25:30,354
How do we go now?

1462
01:25:30,812 --> 01:25:31,937
We don't even know the route.

1463
01:25:34,021 --> 01:25:34,896
Hello, sir.

1464
01:25:35,437 --> 01:25:36,354
Hello.

1465
01:25:36,812 --> 01:25:37,979
Wait a minute, sir.

1466
01:25:38,562 --> 01:25:39,479
Excuse me…

1467
01:25:40,146 --> 01:25:42,479
Sir, the road is closed there.
Which way should we go?

1468
01:25:42,812 --> 01:25:45,271
If you go straight, there's a village…
You should go through that village.

1469
01:25:45,604 --> 01:25:47,146
-So, is there no other way?
-No sir.

1470
01:25:47,437 --> 01:25:48,979
-This is the only way.
-Okay thank you.

1471
01:25:50,229 --> 01:25:51,187
Turn the volume down.

1472
01:25:58,437 --> 01:26:00,187
Salam Alaikum.

1473
01:26:00,354 --> 01:26:02,229
Welcome to Jam with Azam.

1474
01:26:02,354 --> 01:26:05,354
Do you know what
new reel we're making today?

1475
01:26:05,687 --> 01:26:07,937
Our Gun's circumcision festival.

1476
01:26:08,021 --> 01:26:10,062
Meaning, the circumcision ceremony.

1477
01:26:11,771 --> 01:26:12,646
Oh, brother.

1478
01:26:12,896 --> 01:26:14,646
Don't, brother.

1479
01:26:15,479 --> 01:26:16,521
Don't, man.

1480
01:26:16,604 --> 01:26:18,979
I won't let you go this time
without the cut.

1481
01:26:19,562 --> 01:26:20,604
Don't, man.

1482
01:26:25,729 --> 01:26:26,646
-Oh no.
-Put up another tent here.

1483
01:26:26,729 --> 01:26:28,437
What's this? They've
blocked the road here too?

1484
01:26:28,646 --> 01:26:29,521
Don't worry.

1485
01:26:29,604 --> 01:26:30,521
-What now?
-Let's see.

1486
01:26:30,604 --> 01:26:31,646
Inside, the chairs and tables
are all ready for the meal, right?

1487
01:26:31,937 --> 01:26:33,437
Yes, take care of everything.

1488
01:26:33,729 --> 01:26:34,604
Understood?

1489
01:26:35,437 --> 01:26:36,812
-Hello!
-It's getting very humid.

1490
01:26:36,896 --> 01:26:37,771
Why did you set this up blocking the road?

1491
01:26:37,854 --> 01:26:38,771
Do one thing…

1492
01:26:38,854 --> 01:26:40,146
Don't people need to pass through?

1493
01:26:40,229 --> 01:26:42,312
-Place the fans on both sides.
-Hello!

1494
01:26:43,062 --> 01:26:44,062
Hey, I'm talking to you.

1495
01:26:44,187 --> 01:26:45,646
Why have you set this
up blocking the road?

1496
01:26:45,854 --> 01:26:46,812
Mittu, Go inside.

1497
01:26:46,979 --> 01:26:48,271
What are you staring at, sir?

1498
01:26:48,729 --> 01:26:51,271
You… Sir! Sriram sir!

1499
01:26:51,354 --> 01:26:53,021
Greetings, sir! Greetings, Madam!

1500
01:26:53,104 --> 01:26:54,271
Meeravali! What are you doing here?

1501
01:26:54,396 --> 01:26:55,646
This is my village, sir.

1502
01:26:55,771 --> 01:26:56,979
Yes, but what are you doing here?

1503
01:26:57,146 --> 01:26:58,521
They're building a bridge
on that main road, right?

1504
01:26:58,604 --> 01:26:59,937
-Yes.
-I came this way

1505
01:27:00,021 --> 01:27:02,521
to go through the village.
And you're blocking the road here.

1506
01:27:02,604 --> 01:27:05,396
Well… today is my little boy's
Vadugu ceremony, sir.

1507
01:27:05,521 --> 01:27:06,812
You've come as an unexpected guest.

1508
01:27:06,896 --> 01:27:08,896
We'd all be happy if you came too.
Come, madam.

1509
01:27:09,062 --> 01:27:11,396
Meeravali, I'm going for some urgent work.

1510
01:27:11,562 --> 01:27:12,771
Please, can you have this removed?

1511
01:27:12,854 --> 01:27:13,812
That's not possible, sir.

1512
01:27:13,937 --> 01:27:15,854
That day, when you
registered all my lands,

1513
01:27:15,937 --> 01:27:17,354
you didn't take any bribe.

1514
01:27:17,437 --> 01:27:18,729
Today, you both must eat a few bites.

1515
01:27:18,812 --> 01:27:19,729
-Don't say no, sir.
-Won't be possible.

1516
01:27:19,812 --> 01:27:21,812
I won't listen to anything you say, sir.
Madam, you tell him at least.

1517
01:27:21,979 --> 01:27:23,604
Please we have to go.
This is very important work.

1518
01:27:23,687 --> 01:27:24,854
Dad dad!

1519
01:27:24,937 --> 01:27:26,729
Did you think of escaping again?

1520
01:27:26,812 --> 01:27:28,437
-Madam, come! Sir, come, sir!
-No dad!

1521
01:27:28,521 --> 01:27:30,146
-Why are they making that poor kid cry?
-No dad!

1522
01:27:30,229 --> 01:27:32,354
Let's go quickly.

1523
01:27:32,896 --> 01:27:33,812
Quick.

1524
01:27:37,354 --> 01:27:38,312
Oh God.

1525
01:27:50,729 --> 01:27:53,312
We've come to a function here.
Let's act like we don't know anything.

1526
01:28:01,937 --> 01:28:02,896
Hmm…

1527
01:28:04,021 --> 01:28:04,937
This is it.

1528
01:28:05,646 --> 01:28:06,646
Got it.

1529
01:28:09,729 --> 01:28:11,729
Why is he walking around the car?

1530
01:28:12,396 --> 01:28:14,521
Did the police get
suspicious, by any chance?

1531
01:28:15,104 --> 01:28:16,479
Do you want me to manage him?

1532
01:28:16,937 --> 01:28:18,062
What, are you scared?

1533
01:28:19,604 --> 01:28:20,479
I'll crush you.

1534
01:28:20,687 --> 01:28:21,562
Hello.

1535
01:28:22,229 --> 01:28:23,187
Whose car is this?

1536
01:28:23,479 --> 01:28:24,562
It's ours, sir.

1537
01:28:24,937 --> 01:28:25,854
Hmm.

1538
01:28:26,312 --> 01:28:28,521
-I didn't expect to find it so quickly.
-What?

1539
01:28:28,604 --> 01:28:29,479
What do you mean 'found'?

1540
01:28:29,562 --> 01:28:30,437
What's that, sir?

1541
01:28:30,646 --> 01:28:31,896
Why are you getting tense?

1542
01:28:32,729 --> 01:28:34,937
Why would we be tense?
We aren't tense at all.

1543
01:28:35,104 --> 01:28:38,479
This is a 2007 model, I think. Back
then, they stopped production in a year.

1544
01:28:38,604 --> 01:28:39,771
-He's talking about the car.
-I didn't have the money at the time,

1545
01:28:41,479 --> 01:28:43,604
By the way, its trunk
must be pretty big too.

1546
01:28:43,729 --> 01:28:45,354
Yes uncle, you'll fit too.

1547
01:28:45,562 --> 01:28:48,562
Hey, I'll kill you. Shut
up and stand still.

1548
01:28:49,146 --> 01:28:51,104
Who is this kid?
He's a young chap but very sharp.

1549
01:28:51,312 --> 01:28:52,187
He's my son, sir.

1550
01:28:52,312 --> 01:28:53,646
Is that so? Open the trunk.

1551
01:28:54,937 --> 01:28:57,104
How is that possible?
There's a lot of luggage.

1552
01:28:57,229 --> 01:28:58,812
I stuffed it all in. It will fall out.

1553
01:28:58,896 --> 01:29:00,854
My constable will arrange
it, but you open it, sir.

1554
01:29:00,937 --> 01:29:02,812
-It took two hours to arrange this, sir.
-You open it, sir.

1555
01:29:02,896 --> 01:29:03,771
Sriram sir!

1556
01:29:03,854 --> 01:29:06,812
Sriram sir! You're here too!
Food is ready, sir. Come, sir, come.

1557
01:29:07,229 --> 01:29:10,021
Hey, SI sir, why are you late too, sir?

1558
01:29:10,104 --> 01:29:12,771
Not late, bro. I got a message
that the Kothakota SI is missing.

1559
01:29:12,937 --> 01:29:14,979
Police get missing too? So?

1560
01:29:15,062 --> 01:29:16,729
I got late returning from that work.

1561
01:29:16,812 --> 01:29:20,187
Aha, that's fine, but do you have to come
to functions in your police uniform too?

1562
01:29:20,271 --> 01:29:21,812
This is the latest trend now, bro.

1563
01:29:21,937 --> 01:29:24,771
Oh! Nice, nice! Police shirt
on top, dhoti on the bottom.

1564
01:29:24,854 --> 01:29:26,812
-Oh my god, where's my gun?
-What are you searching for, sir?

1565
01:29:26,896 --> 01:29:28,312
-I can't find my gun.
-A gun?

1566
01:29:28,396 --> 01:29:30,187
Mittu isn't seen either.

1567
01:29:33,646 --> 01:29:36,062
I'm begging you! If that gun's gone,
I'm finished… I'll lose my job!

1568
01:29:36,354 --> 01:29:37,479
Please someone find him.

1569
01:29:38,146 --> 01:29:41,104
Sir, SI sir, a boy is
taking away your gun.

1570
01:29:41,187 --> 01:29:42,062
What! A kid?

1571
01:29:42,146 --> 01:29:43,062
Who is he?

1572
01:29:43,146 --> 01:29:44,562
Once he sees the gun,
there's no stopping him.

1573
01:29:44,646 --> 01:29:46,229
I'll take care of him.
Now shut up and sit inside.

1574
01:29:46,312 --> 01:29:47,354
Come quickly!

1575
01:29:47,562 --> 01:29:48,521
Catch him.

1576
01:29:52,562 --> 01:29:53,646
There! That way!

1577
01:29:55,521 --> 01:29:56,562
O goodness!

1578
01:29:59,271 --> 01:30:01,562
My heart nearly stopped.
I thought my gun had fired.

1579
01:30:01,896 --> 01:30:02,937
Did you pop a balloon?

1580
01:30:03,812 --> 01:30:04,937
By the way, where is he?

1581
01:30:05,354 --> 01:30:06,479
Myself Mithil.

1582
01:30:06,646 --> 01:30:07,521
Nice name.

1583
01:30:07,604 --> 01:30:09,146
Insta ID… Mental Mass Mithil.

1584
01:30:09,229 --> 01:30:10,979
-Oh, I see.
-I'm a big fan of yours, sir.

1585
01:30:11,062 --> 01:30:12,021
Thank you.

1586
01:30:12,312 --> 01:30:13,687
-Shall we make a reel?
-Sure, why not?

1587
01:30:13,771 --> 01:30:14,646
One second.

1588
01:30:14,729 --> 01:30:16,271
-Properties…
-Hmm.

1589
01:30:17,687 --> 01:30:19,771
-Oh, a Diwali gun.
-Yes.

1590
01:30:19,854 --> 01:30:22,187
-Yeah, one million views for sure.
-No, two million views.

1591
01:30:22,771 --> 01:30:24,229
-I'll give you the narration.
-Okay…

1592
01:30:24,312 --> 01:30:26,187
I'll hold the gun like this and shoot you.

1593
01:30:26,312 --> 01:30:28,021
You have to act like
you've fallen. That's it.

1594
01:30:28,104 --> 01:30:30,104
This is my novelty!
These are the kind of people we need.

1595
01:30:30,187 --> 01:30:31,604
-Proceed, proceed, proceed!
-Thank you.

1596
01:30:31,687 --> 01:30:33,771
Ah… but the placement…

1597
01:30:33,854 --> 01:30:36,312
-Where should I shoot him?
-Placement… here?

1598
01:30:36,687 --> 01:30:38,146
Oh, there? Not good.

1599
01:30:38,396 --> 01:30:39,437
Oh, here?

1600
01:30:39,604 --> 01:30:40,604
I already shot someone there.

1601
01:30:40,812 --> 01:30:42,479
Oh, better shoot here.

1602
01:30:42,687 --> 01:30:43,562
Here!

1603
01:30:43,937 --> 01:30:46,896
Then the bullet will go like this.
We can add it in graphics.

1604
01:30:46,979 --> 01:30:48,396
Oh my god! Mind-blowing, yeah!

1605
01:30:48,646 --> 01:30:50,312
-You sit down. Hey, you start.
-Shoot!

1606
01:30:50,396 --> 01:30:51,271
Yeah.

1607
01:30:51,354 --> 01:30:53,187
Hmm… turn your
face a little to the right.

1608
01:30:55,521 --> 01:30:57,812
Sir, you search inside,

1609
01:30:58,146 --> 01:30:59,729
-I'll search outside the house.
-Okay.

1610
01:30:59,812 --> 01:31:00,771
-Hey!
-Let's go.

1611
01:31:01,437 --> 01:31:03,521
Yeah, this is the heights of emotion.

1612
01:31:03,729 --> 01:31:04,771
Is the profile okay?

1613
01:31:05,354 --> 01:31:06,396
Don't move, uncle.

1614
01:31:06,479 --> 01:31:09,312
-Make sure the gun doesn't move.
-Wow, what an expression, uncle!

1615
01:31:09,437 --> 01:31:11,271
-I just did this much…
-Move aside!

1616
01:31:11,396 --> 01:31:12,271
Hey, focus.

1617
01:31:12,354 --> 01:31:13,687
Oh no!

1618
01:31:13,854 --> 01:31:14,729
Super uncle.

1619
01:31:14,812 --> 01:31:15,812
Hey, Azam!

1620
01:31:16,312 --> 01:31:19,104
Shh… a reel is being filmed here.
Don't disturb in the middle.

1621
01:31:19,229 --> 01:31:20,604
-Shoot.
-Hey, you fool!

1622
01:31:20,812 --> 01:31:22,437
That's a real gun,
you'll die if it goes off!

1623
01:31:23,146 --> 01:31:25,104
-Please don't shoot me.
-take it easy uncle. It's just a dummy.

1624
01:31:25,187 --> 01:31:26,104
Please tell.

1625
01:31:26,187 --> 01:31:28,354
-Don't listen to them.
-What should I tell?

1626
01:31:28,437 --> 01:31:29,312
Tel him not to shoot.

1627
01:31:29,396 --> 01:31:30,646
He's got the gun.
If he starts shooting, we're all dead.

1628
01:31:30,729 --> 01:31:32,437
They are just blabbering uncle.

1629
01:31:32,521 --> 01:31:33,854
-Don't listen them.
-I beg you.

1630
01:31:33,937 --> 01:31:35,146
-Just one bullet… let me shoot.
-Shoot him.

1631
01:31:35,229 --> 01:31:36,229
-Don't, don't.
-Shoot him.

1632
01:31:36,312 --> 01:31:37,271
They are lying.

1633
01:31:40,771 --> 01:31:43,312
Dad, I don't know anything!
I just found the gun there.

1634
01:31:43,604 --> 01:31:44,562
Oh my god!

1635
01:31:44,771 --> 01:31:46,312
Why he's taking the gun?

1636
01:31:48,146 --> 01:31:49,104
Hey, that's a real gun,
why are you laughing?

1637
01:31:49,187 --> 01:31:50,437
-Listen to me, son.
-Statue!

1638
01:31:50,521 --> 01:31:51,479
Hey!

1639
01:31:51,562 --> 01:31:52,729
-Dad!
-What is it?

1640
01:31:52,896 --> 01:31:56,687
Will you stop this program,
or should I finish it?

1641
01:31:56,771 --> 01:31:57,729
-Ah…
-son…

1642
01:31:57,812 --> 01:31:58,729
Shall I shoot?

1643
01:31:59,771 --> 01:32:01,479
-Thank god, you're back?
-Get in.

1644
01:32:01,562 --> 01:32:03,104
Hey Mittu, what are
you looking at over there?

1645
01:32:03,187 --> 01:32:04,062
The circumcision…

1646
01:32:04,354 --> 01:32:05,437
What does "circumcision" mean, Dad?

1647
01:32:06,479 --> 01:32:08,437
Will you shut up and get in or not?

1648
01:32:08,854 --> 01:32:10,812
Come on, tell me, Dad.
You know everything, right?

1649
01:32:11,479 --> 01:32:12,521
Do I have to tell you?

1650
01:32:12,687 --> 01:32:13,562
Come closer.

1651
01:32:14,062 --> 01:32:14,937
Now…

1652
01:32:15,646 --> 01:32:17,437
No, no, no, I don't want it!

1653
01:32:17,604 --> 01:32:19,062
-I have to tell you.
-Dad, sweetie.

1654
01:32:19,146 --> 01:32:20,271
Wait, wait, wait.

1655
01:32:20,687 --> 01:32:24,854
My dear… I won't let anyone do something
to you that you don't like.

1656
01:32:25,104 --> 01:32:26,062
Can I trust you?

1657
01:32:26,437 --> 01:32:27,521
Absolutely!

1658
01:32:28,062 --> 01:32:30,062
I swear on your gun,
will you give me my gun?

1659
01:32:30,354 --> 01:32:31,937
-For sure?
-100%.

1660
01:32:32,146 --> 01:32:34,021
-Here you go.
-Very good.

1661
01:32:34,104 --> 01:32:35,021
Take care of the gun.

1662
01:32:35,104 --> 01:32:36,937
Where are you going,
you little rascal? Come sit.

1663
01:32:39,354 --> 01:32:40,646
-Meeravali!
-Sir!

1664
01:32:40,729 --> 01:32:41,687
Get the things ready.

1665
01:32:41,812 --> 01:32:42,771
Everything is ready.

1666
01:32:43,479 --> 01:32:45,729
Basheer, sharpen it well.

1667
01:32:45,937 --> 01:32:47,479
It should be done in a single strike.

1668
01:32:48,354 --> 01:32:49,854
You tricked me!

1669
01:32:49,937 --> 01:32:52,396
Listen to me, dear. This is our tradition.

1670
01:32:52,479 --> 01:32:54,146
Hell with your traditions.

1671
01:32:54,396 --> 01:32:55,771
If you want, you get it
done, then you'll know.

1672
01:32:55,854 --> 01:32:57,521
He can't get it done at that age, son.

1673
01:32:58,521 --> 01:33:00,229
Anyway, I won't get it
done in front of my dad.

1674
01:33:00,312 --> 01:33:01,812
Hey Meeravali, go outside for a while.

1675
01:33:01,979 --> 01:33:04,646
Sir, you don't know about him, sir. He's
been escaping like this for five years.

1676
01:33:04,729 --> 01:33:06,646
-Hey, I'll take care of it, you go.
-Go.

1677
01:33:06,729 --> 01:33:07,604
It's your fate, man.

1678
01:33:07,687 --> 01:33:09,562
Okay, dear? You'll get it done, right?

1679
01:33:09,771 --> 01:33:13,396
You've been troubling us since morning.
You're going to get it today, son.

1680
01:33:14,521 --> 01:33:17,437
-Oh god, I'm scared even looking at him.
-Okay, you stay.

1681
01:33:17,521 --> 01:33:20,646
Hey, don't gawk like a villain.
The kid is getting scared.

1682
01:33:20,979 --> 01:33:22,521
Tell him to do it with his eyes closed.

1683
01:33:23,187 --> 01:33:24,771
How can he do it with eyes closed?

1684
01:33:24,854 --> 01:33:26,687
I don't know, tell him to do it.

1685
01:33:26,771 --> 01:33:27,812
Sir, shall I turn off the light?

1686
01:33:27,896 --> 01:33:29,854
How will you do it with
the lights off, you fool?

1687
01:33:29,937 --> 01:33:32,271
Sir, we've done many things
in this kind of darkness, sir.

1688
01:33:32,354 --> 01:33:33,854
-Are you sure?
-Sure sir.

1689
01:33:34,021 --> 01:33:35,437
-Then turn off the lights.
-Okay, sir.

1690
01:33:36,146 --> 01:33:37,062
Don't be scared, son.

1691
01:33:37,229 --> 01:33:38,896
-It'll be over soon.
-It'll be over.

1692
01:33:38,979 --> 01:33:40,521
-Hey, are you coming?
-Sir!

1693
01:33:40,604 --> 01:33:42,896
-Coming, sir.
-I'm on the left, the kid is on the right.

1694
01:33:42,979 --> 01:33:44,979
-No problem, sir, right to left.
-Left…

1695
01:33:45,104 --> 01:33:46,771
-Right…
-It's done.

1696
01:33:46,854 --> 01:33:48,812
Oh no! You killed me!

1697
01:33:48,896 --> 01:33:49,771
He didn't get it done this year either.

1698
01:33:49,854 --> 01:33:51,854
Oh god!

1699
01:33:52,354 --> 01:33:54,312
Oh god!

1700
01:33:55,354 --> 01:33:56,229
I'm finished… completely doomed.

1701
01:33:56,312 --> 01:33:58,187
Sir, will you give a
reward for the job done?

1702
01:33:58,562 --> 01:34:00,562
After all you've done,
you're asking for a reward?

1703
01:34:00,854 --> 01:34:01,979
Hey!

1704
01:34:04,604 --> 01:34:05,937
Oh god!

1705
01:34:12,687 --> 01:34:13,604
It's not that, uncle.

1706
01:34:13,812 --> 01:34:16,354
For some reason, I'm doubting
that Panchayat Secretary Sriram.

1707
01:34:17,146 --> 01:34:18,146
Have you started again?

1708
01:34:18,229 --> 01:34:19,104
Listen to me.

1709
01:34:19,229 --> 01:34:21,021
Yesterday our SI went to his house.

1710
01:34:21,104 --> 01:34:22,271
And they left the village.

1711
01:34:22,354 --> 01:34:23,979
The dots are connecting somewhere, uncle.

1712
01:34:24,062 --> 01:34:26,104
No, you shouldn't
suspect everything like that.

1713
01:34:26,312 --> 01:34:28,187
Then do one thing.
Try talking to them.

1714
01:34:28,479 --> 01:34:30,979
If they say no,
I'll never get involved in this again.

1715
01:34:31,104 --> 01:34:32,979
If you say you won't,
I will go to any extent.

1716
01:34:33,354 --> 01:34:34,312
Connect the call.

1717
01:34:37,937 --> 01:34:39,729
-Hello.
-Hey, Sriram.

1718
01:34:39,937 --> 01:34:42,187
-Who is it?
-It's me, Head Constable Subramanyam.

1719
01:34:47,479 --> 01:34:48,896
-Sriram?
-Yes, sir.

1720
01:34:49,854 --> 01:34:51,187
-Tell me, sir.
-Nothing, man.

1721
01:34:51,271 --> 01:34:52,896
Did our SI come to your house?

1722
01:34:54,896 --> 01:34:55,854
Your…

1723
01:34:56,104 --> 01:34:57,812
Your SI, to my house?

1724
01:34:58,229 --> 01:34:59,604
Why would he come to my house, sir?

1725
01:35:00,146 --> 01:35:02,771
Besides, you know we had a fight, right?

1726
01:35:02,854 --> 01:35:03,896
I know that.

1727
01:35:03,979 --> 01:35:06,729
But someone from your colony
said he came that way. That's why I asked.

1728
01:35:07,812 --> 01:35:09,521
I mean…

1729
01:35:10,229 --> 01:35:11,354
there's the house next to mine, sir.

1730
01:35:11,437 --> 01:35:13,937
That's where the MLA's PA, Prasad, lives.

1731
01:35:14,521 --> 01:35:16,229
He probably came to meet him, sir.

1732
01:35:16,937 --> 01:35:18,562
Maybe.
Alright, I'll check.

1733
01:35:18,687 --> 01:35:19,812
Okay, sir.
I'll take your leave.

1734
01:35:21,687 --> 01:35:23,104
-Did you see, uncle?
-I heard.

1735
01:35:23,312 --> 01:35:24,312
He's stuttering.

1736
01:35:24,396 --> 01:35:25,937
If he stutters, does it
mean something's wrong?

1737
01:35:26,021 --> 01:35:28,021
Hey!
He's a middle-class person.

1738
01:35:28,104 --> 01:35:29,354
Won't he have that
much fear of the police?

1739
01:35:29,437 --> 01:35:30,937
Especially when I'm talking…

1740
01:35:32,354 --> 01:35:33,312
Who is it on the phone?

1741
01:35:33,854 --> 01:35:34,896
The police…

1742
01:35:36,437 --> 01:35:37,437
Police?

1743
01:35:37,854 --> 01:35:39,896
-Why?
-I think they're suspicious of us.

1744
01:35:41,479 --> 01:35:43,021
-How?
-But it's okay.

1745
01:35:43,146 --> 01:35:44,229
It is not confirm. just a doubt.

1746
01:35:50,854 --> 01:35:51,854
What happened?

1747
01:35:54,562 --> 01:35:55,437
Damn!

1748
01:35:55,521 --> 01:35:56,812
My car ran out of fuel.

1749
01:35:59,479 --> 01:36:00,687
Why did you stop here?

1750
01:36:04,854 --> 01:36:06,104
The car's out of fuel.

1751
01:36:06,479 --> 01:36:07,687
I'll go and get it.

1752
01:36:08,854 --> 01:36:10,312
How can we be alone on the road?

1753
01:36:10,562 --> 01:36:12,229
There are so many vehicles
moving on the road, right?

1754
01:36:12,646 --> 01:36:13,771
I'll be back quickly.

1755
01:36:14,354 --> 01:36:15,312
Don't be scared.

1756
01:36:25,479 --> 01:36:27,271
Hey Madan.
It's our car.

1757
01:36:27,896 --> 01:36:30,062
Caught the idiot.
Go, go, go.

1758
01:36:31,021 --> 01:36:32,521
Hey, let's take the bag
and leave right away.

1759
01:36:32,771 --> 01:36:35,854
Is that car his own or what? If we
take the car, the bag will come with it.

1760
01:36:38,896 --> 01:36:41,021
Hey!
Why is there no one in the car?

1761
01:36:41,146 --> 01:36:43,979
So what if they're there or not?
We found the car. Take the car.

1762
01:36:44,187 --> 01:36:47,146
No one here means it's not locked.

1763
01:36:50,146 --> 01:36:51,229
Mom, it's over.

1764
01:36:53,771 --> 01:36:54,687
Mom!

1765
01:36:55,021 --> 01:36:56,521
Someone is near the car.

1766
01:36:57,396 --> 01:36:59,646
Why did he bring the car from
there just to park it here?

1767
01:37:05,229 --> 01:37:06,104
Who are you?

1768
01:37:06,396 --> 01:37:07,687
What are you doing near our car?

1769
01:37:07,937 --> 01:37:08,896
Goodness!

1770
01:37:09,312 --> 01:37:10,896
You're acting more than the owner.

1771
01:37:12,229 --> 01:37:14,479
Looks like you have a PhD in theft.

1772
01:37:14,896 --> 01:37:16,896
Who are you? Why do you care what we do?

1773
01:37:24,812 --> 01:37:26,562
Did you think I took it out
because it was poking me?

1774
01:37:27,437 --> 01:37:28,646
I took it out to stab you.

1775
01:37:29,812 --> 01:37:30,812
Give me the car keys.

1776
01:37:31,229 --> 01:37:32,146
I won't give them.

1777
01:37:37,271 --> 01:37:38,146
Is he your son?

1778
01:37:39,812 --> 01:37:41,187
Can he bear a stab?

1779
01:37:41,479 --> 01:37:43,479
Don't be such a sadist.

1780
01:37:43,896 --> 01:37:45,271
Who puts a knife to a kid?

1781
01:37:45,687 --> 01:37:46,896
You should give him an electric shock.

1782
01:37:47,979 --> 01:37:49,771
What, madam? Is it okay?

1783
01:37:51,104 --> 01:37:51,979
Please!

1784
01:37:52,604 --> 01:37:53,562
Don't hurt him.

1785
01:37:53,896 --> 01:37:54,812
Then give the keys.

1786
01:37:57,521 --> 01:37:58,812
You should have given this earlier.

1787
01:38:00,896 --> 01:38:02,396
You gave it as soon as I asked.

1788
01:38:03,562 --> 01:38:05,979
What about your husband?
He doesn't do anything we ask for.

1789
01:38:06,812 --> 01:38:09,104
Hey!
The car isn't starting.

1790
01:38:09,271 --> 01:38:10,604
The car is out of petrol.

1791
01:38:11,104 --> 01:38:12,354
Dad went to get it.

1792
01:38:12,437 --> 01:38:13,396
Hey!

1793
01:38:13,979 --> 01:38:15,187
We have it in our car.

1794
01:38:24,437 --> 01:38:25,854
-Tell me.
-Boss, we found the car.

1795
01:38:26,104 --> 01:38:27,229
We are on our way.

1796
01:38:29,729 --> 01:38:31,229
-Come soon.
-Okay, brother.

1797
01:38:41,937 --> 01:38:42,854
Where's the car?

1798
01:38:48,187 --> 01:38:49,854
Why don't you answer when I ask?
Where's the car?

1799
01:38:51,479 --> 01:38:52,354
I am asking to you…

1800
01:38:52,437 --> 01:38:55,271
Dad, two uncles came and took it.

1801
01:38:57,979 --> 01:38:58,896
Who came?

1802
01:38:59,271 --> 01:39:00,562
Can't you do one thing properly?

1803
01:39:01,271 --> 01:39:04,146
I told you when you were leaving,
not to leave us on the road and go.

1804
01:39:04,646 --> 01:39:07,021
Hey, why are you blabbering
without telling me what happened?

1805
01:39:08,021 --> 01:39:09,812
Are you waiting for
something more to happen?

1806
01:39:11,771 --> 01:39:15,354
Hey, if you talk nonsense
when I'm tense, I'll hit you.

1807
01:39:15,437 --> 01:39:16,562
Yes, hit me.

1808
01:39:17,146 --> 01:39:18,562
You argued with that SI the same way.

1809
01:39:18,646 --> 01:39:20,146
He came to our house and argued.

1810
01:39:20,479 --> 01:39:23,437
Now, someone else came saying
they'll kill us and took the car.

1811
01:39:25,646 --> 01:39:26,729
Did anything happen to you?

1812
01:39:26,854 --> 01:39:28,812
Nothing happened, for now.

1813
01:39:30,021 --> 01:39:31,312
If you bring all the fights

1814
01:39:31,396 --> 01:39:33,354
from the road to our house in
the name of morals and honesty,

1815
01:39:33,437 --> 01:39:35,062
we'll also end up on the road like this.

1816
01:39:36,896 --> 01:39:40,021
So, are you saying all this
happened because of me?

1817
01:39:40,604 --> 01:39:41,604
Yes.

1818
01:39:46,312 --> 01:39:47,271
Okay.

1819
01:39:48,979 --> 01:39:49,937
Fine.

1820
01:39:56,771 --> 01:39:57,896
Where are you going?

1821
01:39:59,604 --> 01:40:00,479
I'm asking you.

1822
01:40:01,021 --> 01:40:01,937
Stop.

1823
01:40:02,604 --> 01:40:03,562
Why don't you answer when I call?

1824
01:40:04,521 --> 01:40:06,604
All these days, I thought
I was the strength of the family.

1825
01:40:07,271 --> 01:40:08,729
Only now I realized
I'm the weakness.

1826
01:40:11,062 --> 01:40:13,521
You two, take the next
bus and go to Chittoor.

1827
01:40:15,021 --> 01:40:15,979
What?

1828
01:40:16,562 --> 01:40:17,604
I've been pleading, haven't I?

1829
01:40:18,021 --> 01:40:19,104
That I'll surrender.

1830
01:40:19,937 --> 01:40:21,479
I'm going to the nearby police station.

1831
01:40:22,562 --> 01:40:24,437
Have you gone mad?
What are you talking about?

1832
01:40:25,396 --> 01:40:26,646
I told you then itself.

1833
01:40:27,521 --> 01:40:28,937
That on the day we face a problem,

1834
01:40:29,396 --> 01:40:30,562
you must listen to me.

1835
01:40:31,771 --> 01:40:34,229
So, will you say whatever
comes to your mind?

1836
01:40:35,104 --> 01:40:36,187
I don't agree.

1837
01:40:43,187 --> 01:40:44,812
If you don't listen to me now…

1838
01:40:47,979 --> 01:40:49,979
This will be the last time I speak to you.

1839
01:40:57,854 --> 01:40:59,562
If we go, we'll all go together.

1840
01:41:00,604 --> 01:41:01,604
Anywhere.

1841
01:41:15,271 --> 01:41:17,521
Dad, the car.

1842
01:41:17,937 --> 01:41:19,562
Our car is arriving, dad.

1843
01:41:34,396 --> 01:41:35,562
Sir!

1844
01:41:36,396 --> 01:41:37,312
Raghava!

1845
01:41:37,396 --> 01:41:38,854
Greetings, sir, greetings, sir.

1846
01:41:39,021 --> 01:41:40,062
Ladies!

1847
01:41:40,146 --> 01:41:41,062
Hey!

1848
01:41:41,396 --> 01:41:42,937
Get down and greet sir.

1849
01:41:43,521 --> 01:41:44,396
Good morning, sir.

1850
01:41:45,812 --> 01:41:46,812
Raghava?

1851
01:41:47,146 --> 01:41:48,812
How did you bring this car here?

1852
01:41:50,604 --> 01:41:53,062
Sorry Mr. Raghava,
today's program is canceled.

1853
01:41:53,312 --> 01:41:54,479
The chief guest didn't come.

1854
01:41:57,146 --> 01:41:58,312
You…

1855
01:41:58,687 --> 01:42:01,604
Will you cancel my program just because
some chief guest didn't show up?

1856
01:42:01,812 --> 01:42:03,562
-We'll have it next week.
-I don't want anything.

1857
01:42:03,854 --> 01:42:07,146
-You do it yourself. I'm leaving.
-Mr Raghava, our vehicle is there for you.

1858
01:42:07,437 --> 01:42:09,396
I don't want your vehicle
or anything, go away.

1859
01:42:11,646 --> 01:42:13,062
Hey, who is he blocking the road?

1860
01:42:13,271 --> 01:42:14,604
-Hey, my fan's car.
-Step aside!

1861
01:42:14,687 --> 01:42:15,854
Hold on, hold on, hold on.

1862
01:42:18,062 --> 01:42:19,229
Sir, greetings.

1863
01:42:20,979 --> 01:42:21,854
Hey!

1864
01:42:22,187 --> 01:42:24,896
-Who are you?
-You block my way and ask me who I am?

1865
01:42:24,979 --> 01:42:25,979
You bloody drunkard.

1866
01:42:26,562 --> 01:42:28,771
-This is my fan's car.
-Fan?

1867
01:42:28,854 --> 01:42:30,187
You snatched it away.

1868
01:42:30,271 --> 01:42:31,437
Where are they?

1869
01:42:31,854 --> 01:42:35,479
Tell me, or I'll see your end.

1870
01:42:36,104 --> 01:42:37,021
Look at this…

1871
01:42:37,104 --> 01:42:38,187
I will stab you.

1872
01:42:38,271 --> 01:42:39,187
Oh, really?

1873
01:42:40,437 --> 01:42:42,021
Look that way, man.

1874
01:42:44,854 --> 01:42:46,896
-Get down.
-I'm getting down.

1875
01:42:49,271 --> 01:42:50,146
What happened?

1876
01:42:50,229 --> 01:42:52,729
-What's the commotion?
-He came drunk to hit the car, sir.

1877
01:42:52,854 --> 01:42:56,021
Sir, this is my fan's car, sir.

1878
01:42:56,771 --> 01:42:59,021
-He snatched it.
-Why would I need to steal it, sir?

1879
01:42:59,229 --> 01:43:00,187
Do you know who I am?

1880
01:43:00,271 --> 01:43:01,479
I'm MLA Thimmappa's man.

1881
01:43:01,562 --> 01:43:03,187
Hey, do you know who I am?

1882
01:43:03,687 --> 01:43:04,937
I'm the Deputy CM's man.

1883
01:43:05,187 --> 01:43:07,687
Every criminal who gets caught
says the same thing.

1884
01:43:07,812 --> 01:43:08,937
He's a thief, sir.

1885
01:43:10,437 --> 01:43:11,437
Sir!

1886
01:43:14,146 --> 01:43:18,896
Sir, I must say, our artists'
performance was mind-blowing, sir.

1887
01:43:19,479 --> 01:43:21,021
So, they weren't real policemen?

1888
01:43:21,104 --> 01:43:23,729
Why are you making noise?
I'll make you clean the whole place.

1889
01:43:23,812 --> 01:43:25,062
Idiot!

1890
01:43:25,146 --> 01:43:26,021
Thank you very much, Raghava.

1891
01:43:26,104 --> 01:43:27,146
Hey, that's okay sir.

1892
01:43:27,396 --> 01:43:31,354
We might forget ourselves,
but we'll never forget our fans, sir.

1893
01:43:33,687 --> 01:43:34,896
Hey, what are you looking at?

1894
01:43:35,062 --> 01:43:37,479
Go get the car keys,
put them in sir's hand,

1895
01:43:37,562 --> 01:43:39,604
pay respects to him, and go.

1896
01:43:39,687 --> 01:43:40,562
Leave!

1897
01:43:40,812 --> 01:43:42,312
-Uncle.
-What, dear?

1898
01:43:42,396 --> 01:43:44,729
That blackie stole my phone too.

1899
01:43:44,812 --> 01:43:47,104
Is that so? I'm here.
I'll get it to you back.

1900
01:43:48,021 --> 01:43:48,979
Take it.

1901
01:43:49,646 --> 01:43:50,521
Hey!

1902
01:43:51,021 --> 01:43:52,229
Did you take the kid's phone?

1903
01:43:53,729 --> 01:43:54,854
Why are you nodding?
Bend down!

1904
01:43:55,521 --> 01:43:56,937
Bend more.

1905
01:43:57,021 --> 01:43:58,521
Now take the position.

1906
01:44:02,229 --> 01:44:04,187
I will give it if you ask, sir.
Why do you hit?

1907
01:44:04,604 --> 01:44:05,521
You take it.

1908
01:44:06,312 --> 01:44:08,646
That car is ours. They stole it.

1909
01:44:09,854 --> 01:44:12,312
How dare you call my fans thieves?

1910
01:44:12,396 --> 01:44:14,896
-You…
-Uncle, uncle, uncle, uncle, uncle.

1911
01:44:15,271 --> 01:44:18,021
You have to stab many times
with this knife. We have a gun.

1912
01:44:19,646 --> 01:44:21,146
Only one bullet. Bang!

1913
01:44:27,271 --> 01:44:28,146
Can't you keep your mouth shut?

1914
01:44:28,229 --> 01:44:29,771
He's a child artist, right?

1915
01:44:30,021 --> 01:44:32,729
He's trying to outdo you and win an award.

1916
01:44:32,812 --> 01:44:34,562
He's an artist, right?

1917
01:44:35,687 --> 01:44:36,562
-Award!
-Yes!

1918
01:44:36,937 --> 01:44:39,146
You did a big favor, Raghava.

1919
01:44:39,271 --> 01:44:41,979
-We have work, we'll leave.
-It's okay, sir. You go.

1920
01:44:42,062 --> 01:44:43,729
My bag is inside the car.
Please ask him to give it.

1921
01:44:43,812 --> 01:44:45,187
-Happy journey.
-Hey, my bag.

1922
01:44:45,271 --> 01:44:46,604
Hey, my bag… my gift bag.

1923
01:44:48,562 --> 01:44:51,312
Reddy, we finally found the car.
Madan just called.

1924
01:44:53,937 --> 01:44:54,812
Here he's calling.

1925
01:44:55,354 --> 01:44:56,354
-Tell me.
-Boss,

1926
01:44:56,437 --> 01:44:59,896
that Sriram guy tricked our Michael
and took the car again.

1927
01:45:00,521 --> 01:45:04,604
Hey, first kill that duffer.
The misfortune will go away.

1928
01:45:04,771 --> 01:45:06,521
That's not it, boss.
Sriram is the one behind all this.

1929
01:45:06,604 --> 01:45:08,979
I thought I could forgive him somewhere.

1930
01:45:10,271 --> 01:45:11,896
But I won't spare him.

1931
01:45:12,604 --> 01:45:13,687
-Hey!
-Boss!

1932
01:45:14,396 --> 01:45:16,146
I'm not sure what you'll do…

1933
01:45:17,271 --> 01:45:19,021
but I want him.

1934
01:45:21,271 --> 01:45:24,229
He must die at my hands.

1935
01:45:24,437 --> 01:45:25,312
Okay, brother.

1936
01:45:25,396 --> 01:45:27,437
The upcoming left is the cemetery.

1937
01:45:27,521 --> 01:45:30,062
I'm getting scared
as we get closer to the cemetery.

1938
01:45:30,146 --> 01:45:31,271
Should we go back then?

1939
01:45:31,354 --> 01:45:33,437
No, it's okay. Let's go.

1940
01:45:33,521 --> 01:45:37,021
Don't cause any trouble here.
Just do what I told you, okay?

1941
01:45:37,104 --> 01:45:38,021
Let him sleep like that.

1942
01:45:43,437 --> 01:45:45,687
I'll go check if anyone's there.
You stay here.

1943
01:45:48,604 --> 01:45:50,771
ELECTRIC CREMATORIUM
CHITTOOR

1944
01:45:51,396 --> 01:45:52,854
Brother, where are you?

1945
01:45:53,312 --> 01:45:54,854
Time is running out.
We have to burn the bodies.

1946
01:45:54,937 --> 01:45:55,937
Are you coming or not?

1947
01:45:57,812 --> 01:45:59,937
Hey, I told you I was
going out for some work.

1948
01:46:00,021 --> 01:46:01,062
I'll be there in a little while.

1949
01:46:01,146 --> 01:46:02,854
Alright, fine. I'm starting.

1950
01:46:03,021 --> 01:46:05,229
Hey, at least listen to me just this once.

1951
01:46:05,312 --> 01:46:06,229
Forget it, man!

1952
01:46:06,312 --> 01:46:07,812
If we get late, you'll end up blaming me!

1953
01:46:07,896 --> 01:46:08,937
I'll be here alone.

1954
01:46:09,104 --> 01:46:10,271
I'm going to burn the body.

1955
01:46:10,354 --> 01:46:11,562
Hey, Chandra! Listen--

1956
01:46:17,687 --> 01:46:18,729
Is anyone there?

1957
01:46:19,437 --> 01:46:20,562
There's just one guy.

1958
01:46:21,312 --> 01:46:23,146
If we can deal with him, that's enough.

1959
01:46:24,021 --> 01:46:25,062
How do we deal with him?

1960
01:47:04,312 --> 01:47:05,521
Brother!

1961
01:47:06,562 --> 01:47:08,854
-What happened, dear?
-My brother…

1962
01:47:09,437 --> 01:47:11,812
I couldn't even see him for the last time.

1963
01:47:13,021 --> 01:47:16,604
O brother! My brother.

1964
01:47:16,937 --> 01:47:18,062
If you have a chance, what will you do?

1965
01:47:19,229 --> 01:47:20,646
I would have been happy, brother.

1966
01:47:20,729 --> 01:47:21,604
Then?

1967
01:47:22,021 --> 01:47:25,771
What else could I do?
I would've just cried… you fool.

1968
01:47:26,354 --> 01:47:27,812
What are you doing now? The same.

1969
01:47:28,521 --> 01:47:29,979
What's the point of this much performance?

1970
01:47:30,146 --> 01:47:33,062
Brother… that's not it, brother. Well…

1971
01:47:33,396 --> 01:47:34,479
It's not that, brother.

1972
01:47:34,771 --> 01:47:37,187
It's been so long since I saw my brother.

1973
01:47:37,521 --> 01:47:39,771
Why did your brother become
an orphan in the first place?

1974
01:47:40,229 --> 01:47:43,479
-One day, my father and I had a big fight.
-Okay fine.

1975
01:47:43,979 --> 01:47:45,271
My brother involved in between…

1976
01:47:45,562 --> 01:47:47,937
I left the house in anger.

1977
01:47:48,062 --> 01:47:49,312
But then, you would be the orphan, right?

1978
01:47:49,937 --> 01:47:52,937
Brother, my father also came with me.

1979
01:47:53,021 --> 01:47:55,687
That's it, my brother became an orphan.

1980
01:47:58,687 --> 01:48:00,479
Who told you that's your brother's body?

1981
01:48:00,729 --> 01:48:01,937
Don't irritate me… just go from here.

1982
01:48:03,646 --> 01:48:04,521
Brother!

1983
01:48:07,271 --> 01:48:08,187
What is it?

1984
01:48:08,271 --> 01:48:09,312
Did he stop breathing, sir?

1985
01:48:09,479 --> 01:48:10,896
Is he not responding?

1986
01:48:11,646 --> 01:48:13,687
-Does he smell?
-Yes.

1987
01:48:14,479 --> 01:48:17,937
Then what else?
That's my brother's body.

1988
01:48:18,604 --> 01:48:19,771
Oh brother…

1989
01:48:19,896 --> 01:48:21,437
You've matched everything well.

1990
01:48:22,146 --> 01:48:23,646
But it's a deceased woman
who's being burned there.

1991
01:48:25,937 --> 01:48:26,937
This doesn't match.

1992
01:48:31,979 --> 01:48:35,396
Bye bye. I'll be going. Okay.

1993
01:48:35,812 --> 01:48:38,771
No one comes when someone alive. It's only
after death that everyone comes rushing.

1994
01:48:49,437 --> 01:48:51,437
Dear, why did you stop the car?

1995
01:48:52,479 --> 01:48:53,354
I'm talking to you.

1996
01:48:57,521 --> 01:48:58,854
Why aren't you saying anything?

1997
01:49:00,771 --> 01:49:02,187
Why did you stop here?

1998
01:49:03,521 --> 01:49:04,521
It's nothing.

1999
01:49:04,812 --> 01:49:07,479
I'm just scared… wondering if I can
carry this burden for the rest of my life.

2000
01:49:08,646 --> 01:49:09,562
Dad…

2001
01:49:13,271 --> 01:49:14,604
I'm hungry.

2002
01:49:15,521 --> 01:49:17,021
There should be a dhaba nearby.

2003
01:49:17,104 --> 01:49:19,562
Let's eat there and then go
to your mother's home. Okay?

2004
01:49:19,646 --> 01:49:20,521
Okay.

2005
01:49:22,437 --> 01:49:24,271
Shawarma Dhaba Chittoor presents…

2006
01:49:24,812 --> 01:49:26,562
on the occasion of Diwali…

2007
01:49:27,104 --> 01:49:29,771
the Hyderabad Food
Festival, on its final day,

2008
01:49:29,854 --> 01:49:32,021
featuring the special attraction… Paya!

2009
01:51:56,937 --> 01:51:58,146
Did Trump wake up?

2010
01:51:58,229 --> 01:52:01,104
Again he became president
that is the magic of paya.

2011
01:54:01,604 --> 01:54:03,104
What are you still thinking?

2012
01:54:04,479 --> 01:54:05,854
I was very scared.

2013
01:54:06,187 --> 01:54:07,562
About what would happen to his life.

2014
01:54:08,896 --> 01:54:10,437
Even though the panchayat secretary

2015
01:54:10,896 --> 01:54:12,437
outside felt what he
was doing was wrong…

2016
01:54:14,104 --> 01:54:16,979
the father inside
felt it was inevitable.

2017
01:54:20,896 --> 01:54:22,479
Why are you overthinking?

2018
01:54:22,604 --> 01:54:23,562
And more thing…

2019
01:54:24,771 --> 01:54:26,021
Sorry.

2020
01:54:26,104 --> 01:54:28,312
I got scared when you
mentioned the police station.

2021
01:54:29,187 --> 01:54:31,146
I spoke a bit harshly,

2022
01:54:32,021 --> 01:54:33,604
worrying that we might get into trouble.

2023
01:54:34,312 --> 01:54:35,187
Sorry.

2024
01:54:40,771 --> 01:54:41,937
You're also emotional, right?

2025
01:54:42,062 --> 01:54:43,354
I can't be like you.

2026
01:54:44,729 --> 01:54:46,396
You can't stay without scolding me, right?

2027
01:54:47,479 --> 01:54:49,312
-Dad!
-Yes son?

2028
01:54:49,396 --> 01:54:50,896
We've been traveling since morning.

2029
01:54:51,062 --> 01:54:52,854
Why haven't we reached
grandpa's house yet?

2030
01:54:52,937 --> 01:54:54,396
-Here it is.
-Where?

2031
01:54:54,521 --> 01:54:56,812
I know. You took a wrong route somewhere.

2032
01:54:57,229 --> 01:54:58,229
Yes,

2033
01:54:58,729 --> 01:55:01,604
you two are always right.

2034
01:55:02,521 --> 01:55:03,854
Isn't it right?

2035
01:55:16,479 --> 01:55:17,396
Hello.

2036
01:55:17,979 --> 01:55:19,729
Panchayat Secretary Sriram speaking.

2037
01:55:19,937 --> 01:55:21,771
Can you give the phone to criminal Sriram?

2038
01:55:27,229 --> 01:55:29,271
-What?
-Ok fine, Killer.

2039
01:55:31,854 --> 01:55:32,729
Who is it?

2040
01:55:33,062 --> 01:55:35,562
Is your partner in crime also besides you?

2041
01:55:35,646 --> 01:55:36,521
Hello.

2042
01:55:37,437 --> 01:55:38,979
I can't hear you.
One minute…

2043
01:55:39,354 --> 01:55:40,354
There's no signal here.

2044
01:55:45,562 --> 01:55:46,646
Who are you?

2045
01:55:49,812 --> 01:55:51,604
You don't get scared
unless someone tells you to.

2046
01:55:52,312 --> 01:55:57,604
Killing a policeman and trying
to make the body disappear…

2047
01:55:58,271 --> 01:55:59,354
Hats off!

2048
01:56:01,312 --> 01:56:04,271
We'll have your family's
felicitation ceremony later,

2049
01:56:04,937 --> 01:56:09,562
but I have all the evidence of your crime.

2050
01:56:11,979 --> 01:56:14,479
If you don't want this
to reach the police,

2051
01:56:15,396 --> 01:56:17,604
50 lakh rupees should reach me.

2052
01:56:22,437 --> 01:56:23,312
Sir. Sir…

2053
01:56:24,229 --> 01:56:25,729
Can you give me a minute?

2054
01:56:25,896 --> 01:56:29,729
What is this?
You're making demands where I should be.

2055
01:56:30,396 --> 01:56:32,062
Okay, so be it.

2056
01:56:32,437 --> 01:56:33,396
Thank you sir.

2057
01:56:49,979 --> 01:56:51,146
Eat slowly, dear.

2058
01:56:52,812 --> 01:56:53,896
Who was on the phone?

2059
01:56:54,396 --> 01:56:55,479
That…

2060
01:56:55,771 --> 01:56:57,187
A friend of mine called.

2061
01:56:57,687 --> 01:56:59,479
You do one thing.
I can't come now.

2062
01:56:59,812 --> 01:57:00,979
You take an auto and go home.

2063
01:57:01,062 --> 01:57:02,271
I'll finish my work and come.

2064
01:57:03,229 --> 01:57:04,187
What happened?

2065
01:57:04,604 --> 01:57:06,187
Why do you worry about everything?

2066
01:57:07,104 --> 01:57:08,521
Will I let anything happen when I'm here?

2067
01:57:09,104 --> 01:57:11,979
He has some personal problem.
I'll take a look and be back immediately.

2068
01:57:13,104 --> 01:57:13,979
Okay then.

2069
01:57:14,062 --> 01:57:15,021
-Hey Mittu.
-Yes.

2070
01:57:15,146 --> 01:57:16,229
-Go with mom.
-Okay.

2071
01:57:16,312 --> 01:57:17,229
-Alright?
-Take care.

2072
01:57:17,312 --> 01:57:18,229
Let's go.

2073
01:57:22,521 --> 01:57:23,396
Watch out!

2074
01:57:23,479 --> 01:57:24,646
Will you come to Greamspet?

2075
01:57:26,062 --> 01:57:27,354
-Uttara.
-Yes.

2076
01:57:39,479 --> 01:57:40,396
What happened?

2077
01:57:41,479 --> 01:57:42,937
My wife, my wish.

2078
01:57:50,854 --> 01:57:51,979
Then what about me?

2079
01:57:54,854 --> 01:57:55,812
Come.

2080
01:58:17,896 --> 01:58:19,271
-Bye.
-Okay.

2081
01:58:22,979 --> 01:58:24,146
Is everything okay?

2082
01:58:25,229 --> 01:58:26,187
Bye dad.

2083
01:58:26,312 --> 01:58:27,187
-Bye.
-Bye.

2084
01:58:49,854 --> 01:58:50,896
Hello!

2085
01:58:51,396 --> 01:58:52,687
What were you saying earlier?

2086
01:58:52,854 --> 01:58:54,562
Why the change in tone?

2087
01:58:55,354 --> 01:58:57,437
Put that aside and come to the point.

2088
01:58:58,479 --> 01:59:00,104
What will you do if I
don't give you the money?

2089
01:59:00,562 --> 01:59:01,479
What else?

2090
01:59:01,604 --> 01:59:04,604
I'll give the police all
the evidence I have.

2091
01:59:04,729 --> 01:59:06,021
Tell me which station are you going to,

2092
01:59:06,312 --> 01:59:08,271
I'll come too, we'll both go.

2093
01:59:09,479 --> 01:59:10,354
What?

2094
01:59:10,437 --> 01:59:13,521
I did all this for my family,
without anyone knowing.

2095
01:59:14,729 --> 01:59:16,646
After everything is out in the open,

2096
01:59:17,312 --> 01:59:19,062
what is there to be afraid of?

2097
01:59:20,479 --> 01:59:22,854
I myself will go to the
police station and surrender.

2098
01:59:23,646 --> 01:59:24,937
What more can you do to me?

2099
01:59:31,854 --> 01:59:32,812
Wow.

2100
01:59:33,646 --> 01:59:34,521
Claps, man.

2101
01:59:35,437 --> 01:59:36,479
You're a clever one.

2102
01:59:37,354 --> 01:59:38,229
But…

2103
01:59:38,396 --> 01:59:40,729
This might have happened
if you had committed the murder.

2104
01:59:43,646 --> 01:59:44,979
It was your son

2105
01:59:47,562 --> 01:59:48,604
who committed the murder, right?

2106
01:59:53,521 --> 01:59:55,979
Shall we go to the station now?

2107
01:59:57,937 --> 01:59:58,854
Sorry sir.

2108
01:59:59,104 --> 02:00:01,646
Get one crore ready by tomorrow morning.

2109
02:00:05,396 --> 02:00:06,729
Are you in shock?

2110
02:00:06,896 --> 02:00:09,229
Your tone has changed,
so my price has changed.

2111
02:00:10,146 --> 02:00:12,396
Besides, I don't think this
amount is a big deal for you.

2112
02:00:12,604 --> 02:00:14,396
If you get along with the MLA…

2113
02:00:14,646 --> 02:00:17,396
You'll keep getting any amount.

2114
02:00:18,187 --> 02:00:20,146
I'm off then, bye.

2115
02:00:39,604 --> 02:00:41,521
G. GURU MURTHY

2116
02:00:42,771 --> 02:00:43,646
Hey, Jiguru Murthy!

2117
02:00:44,104 --> 02:00:45,354
Hey, Jiguru Murthy!

2118
02:00:53,604 --> 02:00:55,521
Hello… Hello…

2119
02:00:56,646 --> 02:00:57,562
Babu…

2120
02:00:59,687 --> 02:01:02,062
Not Jiguru Murthy, not Chiguru Murthy.

2121
02:01:02,562 --> 02:01:04,271
It's G. Guru Murthy.

2122
02:01:04,521 --> 02:01:05,979
What's your name?

2123
02:01:06,687 --> 02:01:07,604
Michael.

2124
02:01:07,979 --> 02:01:09,354
What do you want, son?

2125
02:01:09,479 --> 02:01:10,979
Your son-in-law.
Call him.

2126
02:01:11,229 --> 02:01:14,812
They are not at a shouting
distance to come when you call.

2127
02:01:15,146 --> 02:01:16,729
They are kilometers away.

2128
02:01:16,812 --> 02:01:18,687
Hey, call him.

2129
02:01:20,146 --> 02:01:21,979
A person who calls might have love,

2130
02:01:22,687 --> 02:01:24,646
but the person who comes
must have time, right, son?

2131
02:01:25,396 --> 02:01:27,229
So, they haven't come here yet?

2132
02:01:27,771 --> 02:01:29,771
If he says he'll come, I won't say no.

2133
02:01:29,854 --> 02:01:31,646
If he says he'll leave,
I won't say go away.

2134
02:01:31,979 --> 02:01:33,312
It's their wish.

2135
02:01:34,354 --> 02:01:35,771
It's their problem.

2136
02:01:36,479 --> 02:01:39,479
Hey, can you please speak in Telugu, sir?

2137
02:01:40,979 --> 02:01:42,604
There is no caste for hardship,

2138
02:01:42,812 --> 02:01:44,521
no language for pain.

2139
02:01:44,646 --> 02:01:45,896
Om Tatsat.

2140
02:01:46,646 --> 02:01:47,771
What's your problem, man?

2141
02:01:48,854 --> 02:01:49,771
Who is this guy?

2142
02:01:50,187 --> 02:01:51,479
My son Prakash.

2143
02:01:52,062 --> 02:01:54,729
-He's been missing for three days.
-Oh!

2144
02:01:55,146 --> 02:01:57,146
Whoever I ask says they don't know.

2145
02:01:58,062 --> 02:02:00,354
If I ask the police,
they say they'll find out.

2146
02:02:00,479 --> 02:02:02,479
Did you tell your daughter
and Son-in-law about this?

2147
02:02:04,062 --> 02:02:05,979
You can share happiness.

2148
02:02:06,854 --> 02:02:08,354
But you have to bear the sadness.

2149
02:02:10,646 --> 02:02:12,146
Did you tell them or not?

2150
02:02:13,062 --> 02:02:15,104
Even if It is easy to say,

2151
02:02:15,187 --> 02:02:17,104
I can't say it easily, right, son?

2152
02:02:18,396 --> 02:02:19,396
What's your problem, man?

2153
02:02:19,729 --> 02:02:20,646
He's like that, bro.

2154
02:02:20,729 --> 02:02:22,104
Whenever he's down,
he ends up tormenting everyone around him.

2155
02:02:22,437 --> 02:02:23,729
Huh? Huh?

2156
02:02:25,354 --> 02:02:27,937
Hey! This is all happening
because of you, right?

2157
02:02:28,312 --> 02:02:29,562
What are you doing here?

2158
02:02:30,062 --> 02:02:31,937
Bro, Am I visible to you?

2159
02:02:32,562 --> 02:02:34,229
What do you think you are?
Kamal Haasan from Kalki?

2160
02:02:34,437 --> 02:02:36,104
Hiding in the complex like that!

2161
02:02:36,646 --> 02:02:38,562
With whom are you talking?

2162
02:02:39,521 --> 02:02:41,229
You should go to the eye hospital,

2163
02:02:41,312 --> 02:02:42,271
not the police station.

2164
02:02:42,354 --> 02:02:43,312
You are asking 'who
are you talking to'?

2165
02:02:43,396 --> 02:02:44,729
Your son is right in front of you.

2166
02:02:45,937 --> 02:02:46,896
Where?

2167
02:02:47,979 --> 02:02:49,271
Where is my son, Babu?

2168
02:02:49,521 --> 02:02:51,812
Hey, you're here, right? Then tell him.

2169
02:02:51,979 --> 02:02:54,271
I haven't been seen by
anyone since I died, bro.

2170
02:02:54,771 --> 02:02:56,021
If I want to tell someone about this,

2171
02:02:56,146 --> 02:02:57,854
they can't see or hear me.

2172
02:02:58,104 --> 02:02:59,479
Finally, I found you.

2173
02:02:59,604 --> 02:03:01,854
I can be seen and heard by you.
Tell him I'm here, bro.

2174
02:03:02,021 --> 02:03:03,521
Dear!
Come quickly!

2175
02:03:03,604 --> 02:03:05,479
Our son has appeared, come quickly!

2176
02:03:06,271 --> 02:03:07,146
Oh my God!

2177
02:03:07,396 --> 02:03:09,062
Where is my son? Tell me, Babu.

2178
02:03:09,229 --> 02:03:11,104
I will offer 100 coconuts
in your name, Babu.

2179
02:03:11,187 --> 02:03:13,062
-Tell me, where is he?
-Tell me son.

2180
02:03:13,271 --> 02:03:14,187
Tell him, bro.

2181
02:03:14,312 --> 02:03:15,187
Where?

2182
02:03:15,271 --> 02:03:16,479
-Tell him I'm here, bro.
-Where?

2183
02:03:16,562 --> 02:03:17,896
-Where?
-Tell me.

2184
02:03:18,104 --> 02:03:19,229
-I'm here.
-Where?

2185
02:03:19,312 --> 02:03:20,229
-I'm here.
-Where?

2186
02:03:20,312 --> 02:03:21,229
-Where?
-Where?

2187
02:03:21,729 --> 02:03:22,687
I'm here.

2188
02:03:23,187 --> 02:03:24,479
Ghost! Oh my God! Ghost!

2189
02:03:26,021 --> 02:03:28,646
Okay, we reached the location you shared.
If I need anything, I'll call you.

2190
02:03:28,729 --> 02:03:31,354
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!
What happened, man?

2191
02:03:32,104 --> 02:03:34,021
-A ghost!
-A ghost? Where?

2192
02:03:34,479 --> 02:03:35,396
There!

2193
02:03:36,271 --> 02:03:37,146
Come, man!

2194
02:03:37,229 --> 02:03:38,729
I won't come, you go if you want!

2195
02:03:38,812 --> 02:03:39,937
-Come on, you duffer!
-I won't come!

2196
02:03:40,271 --> 02:03:42,312
Hey, come! Come!

2197
02:03:43,271 --> 02:03:47,146
Dad, your performance…
I bow to you, dad. Peaks! You nailed it!

2198
02:03:47,271 --> 02:03:49,729
Mom, come here. I never
expected this from you.

2199
02:03:49,812 --> 02:03:51,646
You are awesome. It's not normal.

2200
02:03:51,729 --> 02:03:54,396
As far as I know, this is the best
prank video on my YouTube channel.

2201
02:03:54,479 --> 02:03:56,979
We found a total duffer for our prank.

2202
02:03:57,187 --> 02:03:59,646
If he had waited a little longer,
I would have offered coconuts.

2203
02:03:59,896 --> 02:04:01,771
You should have offered coconuts.

2204
02:04:02,104 --> 02:04:04,646
The opportunity never knocks twice.

2205
02:04:08,521 --> 02:04:09,854
I'll kill them all.
Bloody buggers!

2206
02:04:10,146 --> 02:04:11,562
Shut up, you duffer.

2207
02:04:21,979 --> 02:04:25,187
Your son is the one who
committed the murder, isn't he?

2208
02:04:28,021 --> 02:04:29,521
Like some great father,

2209
02:04:29,979 --> 02:04:31,937
you say you'll go to jail in his place.

2210
02:04:32,187 --> 02:04:34,229
How can I let you go that easily?

2211
02:04:36,021 --> 02:04:39,354
I'll reveal the evidence
and send your son inside.

2212
02:04:41,229 --> 02:04:43,479
Once someone's labeled a criminal,

2213
02:04:43,562 --> 02:04:45,437
it's like dying a little every minute.

2214
02:04:47,437 --> 02:04:51,562
After seeing all this, he'll feel that
being inside is better than being outside.

2215
02:04:52,104 --> 02:04:53,437
He'll commit another crime.

2216
02:04:54,104 --> 02:04:55,729
This time, whether he goes into the jail,

2217
02:04:56,271 --> 02:04:58,187
or end up dead in an encounter.

2218
02:04:58,771 --> 02:05:02,437
To have a future, one
has to be alive, right?

2219
02:05:03,104 --> 02:05:04,979
Dad, shall we go for a ride?

2220
02:05:06,896 --> 02:05:08,104
I love you, Dad.

2221
02:05:19,437 --> 02:05:20,937
That's a minus.

2222
02:05:21,729 --> 02:05:23,062
You don't know how to play.

2223
02:05:30,146 --> 02:05:31,271
Here, Sriram.

2224
02:05:31,896 --> 02:05:33,979
My husband and my son…

2225
02:05:34,396 --> 02:05:36,146
…should be better than
anyone else in this town.

2226
02:05:41,104 --> 02:05:42,146
Sorry, Uttara.

2227
02:05:42,521 --> 02:05:44,521
That day, I couldn't give
you what you asked for.

2228
02:05:46,146 --> 02:05:47,604
But you never left me.

2229
02:05:52,979 --> 02:05:53,979
But I…

2230
02:05:54,479 --> 02:05:56,771
…promised to be with you until the end,

2231
02:05:58,979 --> 02:06:00,604
and now I'm leaving you midway.

2232
02:06:04,312 --> 02:06:06,812
I don't know if I was a good
husband to you or not…

2233
02:06:08,687 --> 02:06:10,979
…but you were a good wife to me.

2234
02:06:13,937 --> 02:06:14,854
More than that…

2235
02:06:16,729 --> 02:06:18,396
…you were a good mother to Mittu.

2236
02:06:22,062 --> 02:06:23,062
From now on…

2237
02:06:28,646 --> 02:06:29,937
you're like a father to him.

2238
02:06:36,021 --> 02:06:36,896
I love you.

2239
02:06:38,021 --> 02:06:39,104
Sorry, Uttara.

2240
02:06:52,312 --> 02:06:53,437
My name is Sriram.

2241
02:06:53,979 --> 02:06:55,979
I am the Panchayat Secretary
of Horsley Hills.

2242
02:06:56,687 --> 02:07:01,062
A few days ago, Kothakota SI Vikram
and I had a fight.

2243
02:07:03,646 --> 02:07:06,396
He held a grudge and came to my house.

2244
02:07:07,604 --> 02:07:09,187
He misbehaved with my family.

2245
02:07:09,812 --> 02:07:11,146
I shot him during that fight.

2246
02:07:13,396 --> 02:07:14,771
I also burned the body.

2247
02:07:16,979 --> 02:07:18,979
Please don't drag my family into this.

2248
02:07:19,854 --> 02:07:20,729
Please.

2249
02:07:23,562 --> 02:07:25,187
This is my dying declaration.

2250
02:08:09,979 --> 02:08:11,521
What is it, Sriram?
What brings you here?

2251
02:08:13,771 --> 02:08:15,729
Well, uh…

2252
02:08:17,604 --> 02:08:18,604
One minute, sir.

2253
02:08:28,229 --> 02:08:29,396
-What is it?
-Sir…

2254
02:08:30,104 --> 02:08:32,021
-Can I have some water?
-Yes, drink…Take it.

2255
02:08:34,396 --> 02:08:35,729
Yes, tell me, Sriram.

2256
02:08:35,896 --> 02:08:37,854
What is it?
You look tense.

2257
02:08:39,104 --> 02:08:42,104
Actually…
I've come to file a complaint, sir.

2258
02:08:42,521 --> 02:08:43,437
About what?

2259
02:08:43,562 --> 02:08:45,396
It's… my bag was stolen, sir.

2260
02:08:45,521 --> 02:08:46,979
Oh, a theft case?

2261
02:08:47,146 --> 02:08:48,021
What was in it?

2262
02:08:48,396 --> 02:08:49,854
-One crore rupees, sir.
-Crore…

2263
02:08:50,896 --> 02:08:53,229
One crore rupees?
How did you get that much money?

2264
02:08:53,604 --> 02:08:57,062
I… had some urgent work, so I
borrowed it from someone I know, sir.

2265
02:08:57,854 --> 02:08:59,396
What was so urgent?

2266
02:09:00,937 --> 02:09:03,521
Well… someone was blackmailed me, sir.

2267
02:09:03,896 --> 02:09:05,896
What? Blackmail?
Who?

2268
02:09:06,229 --> 02:09:07,229
I don't know, sir.

2269
02:09:07,354 --> 02:09:09,229
Then you should file a
complaint against him!

2270
02:09:09,312 --> 02:09:10,646
Why are you saying it's a theft case?

2271
02:09:12,896 --> 02:09:15,479
If I file a case, he's threatening
to demand two crores, sir.

2272
02:09:15,604 --> 02:09:17,271
One crore is better than two, right, sir?

2273
02:09:17,979 --> 02:09:20,104
How can you just give it to him?
We're here, aren't we?

2274
02:09:20,437 --> 02:09:21,937
You don't understand my pain, sir.

2275
02:09:22,229 --> 02:09:24,354
First, call that SI.
I'll explain it to him.

2276
02:09:24,437 --> 02:09:27,271
It's been two days since he came to
the station. We're also looking for him.

2277
02:09:28,021 --> 02:09:29,062
Don't look for him, sir.

2278
02:09:31,229 --> 02:09:32,354
He won't be found.

2279
02:09:32,479 --> 02:09:33,354
What do you mean?

2280
02:09:35,771 --> 02:09:36,646
I'm the one…

2281
02:09:37,646 --> 02:09:38,979
…who killed him.

2282
02:09:45,771 --> 02:09:46,646
Killed?

2283
02:09:46,729 --> 02:09:48,729
Have you gone mad, coming to
a police station and saying such things?

2284
02:10:00,396 --> 02:10:01,604
This is Vikram's gun.

2285
02:10:01,854 --> 02:10:03,104
I killed him with this.

2286
02:10:04,646 --> 02:10:05,646
Why did you kill him?

2287
02:10:06,021 --> 02:10:07,896
Well… you know, right sir?

2288
02:10:08,229 --> 02:10:11,729
That day the minister was visiting…
he and I had a big fight.

2289
02:10:12,646 --> 02:10:14,229
After that, he came to my house.

2290
02:10:14,396 --> 02:10:16,146
He misbehaved with my family.

2291
02:10:18,229 --> 02:10:19,729
In the ensuing fight, I shot him.

2292
02:10:20,604 --> 02:10:22,021
I also burned the body.

2293
02:10:24,479 --> 02:10:26,521
Uncle, I've been telling
you since that day!

2294
02:10:26,854 --> 02:10:28,521
I was suspicious of him,
but you didn't believe me!

2295
02:10:29,896 --> 02:10:32,812
You commit a huge crime,
then file a complaint about stolen money?

2296
02:10:33,854 --> 02:10:36,479
What are you trying to do, Sriram?
Just tell us what you want.

2297
02:10:37,271 --> 02:10:38,146
Nothing sir…

2298
02:10:39,854 --> 02:10:42,646
-I need a favor from you.
-What is it?

2299
02:10:43,187 --> 02:10:44,979
Since I came and surrendered myself…

2300
02:10:45,604 --> 02:10:47,354
I was hoping you could
reduce the punishment.

2301
02:10:47,479 --> 02:10:48,562
That's not in our hands.

2302
02:10:49,812 --> 02:10:51,479
Then what is in your hands, sir?

2303
02:10:52,521 --> 02:10:54,771
Right now throwing you
in a jail is in our hands.

2304
02:10:57,104 --> 02:10:58,021
In that case…

2305
02:10:58,562 --> 02:10:59,729
I didn't kill him, sir.

2306
02:10:59,937 --> 02:11:01,146
What are you talking about?

2307
02:11:01,354 --> 02:11:03,562
Didn't you just come here and
confess to the murder yourself?

2308
02:11:03,646 --> 02:11:05,104
Now you're saying you didn't kill him?

2309
02:11:05,604 --> 02:11:07,354
I'm telling you again, sir.

2310
02:11:08,104 --> 02:11:09,479
It wasn't me who killed him.

2311
02:11:10,021 --> 02:11:11,021
The killer was…

2312
02:11:13,229 --> 02:11:14,354
my son.

2313
02:11:17,271 --> 02:11:18,604
Are you playing with cops?

2314
02:11:19,687 --> 02:11:20,562
Yes, sir.

2315
02:11:21,021 --> 02:11:22,521
My son killed him while playing.

2316
02:11:22,604 --> 02:11:24,562
Sriram, whether you
killed him or your son did,

2317
02:11:24,646 --> 02:11:26,312
a case has to be filed
and submitted to the court.

2318
02:11:26,396 --> 02:11:28,396
Tell us what happened
so we can write the FIR!

2319
02:11:32,146 --> 02:11:33,271
I'll tell you, sir.

2320
02:11:33,812 --> 02:11:36,521
But before that I have a small doubt, sir.

2321
02:11:36,604 --> 02:11:37,521
What is it?

2322
02:11:38,187 --> 02:11:41,771
Well… is murder a bigger crime,

2323
02:11:42,437 --> 02:11:43,854
or is blackmail, sir?

2324
02:11:44,521 --> 02:11:45,562
Both are crimes.

2325
02:11:45,729 --> 02:11:47,229
I'm asking which one is bigger.

2326
02:11:48,062 --> 02:11:49,479
Murder, of course.

2327
02:11:49,812 --> 02:11:51,354
No… no, sir.

2328
02:11:52,312 --> 02:11:53,396
As far as I'm concerned…

2329
02:11:54,187 --> 02:11:55,937
blackmail is the bigger crime, sir.

2330
02:11:56,021 --> 02:11:56,896
How so?

2331
02:11:58,021 --> 02:11:58,896
Because…

2332
02:11:59,687 --> 02:12:01,271
it's only because he blackmailed me, sir…

2333
02:12:01,604 --> 02:12:03,521
that I discovered someone else
was the real killer.

2334
02:12:04,104 --> 02:12:05,229
What? Someone else?

2335
02:12:05,646 --> 02:12:06,604
Hey!

2336
02:12:08,354 --> 02:12:11,146
We're speaking to you respectfully
because you're a government employee.

2337
02:12:11,229 --> 02:12:12,396
Are you playing games with us?

2338
02:12:13,146 --> 02:12:14,062
No, no.

2339
02:12:14,729 --> 02:12:17,771
No, sir.
If my son and I had really fired this gun…

2340
02:12:18,354 --> 02:12:20,479
there should be fewer
bullets in the revolver, right?

2341
02:12:22,021 --> 02:12:23,354
But the magazine is full.

2342
02:12:25,271 --> 02:12:26,354
Which means…

2343
02:12:34,021 --> 02:12:35,104
The gun didn't fire.

2344
02:12:36,146 --> 02:12:37,229
I had a doubt.

2345
02:12:40,146 --> 02:12:43,396
It's so hard to even pull off…
then how could Mittu have loaded it?

2346
02:12:45,312 --> 02:12:48,604
I opened YouTube and searched,
"How to open a magazine?"

2347
02:12:52,354 --> 02:12:53,937
I found out how many bullets
a full magazine holds.

2348
02:12:54,979 --> 02:12:56,646
That's when I got some clarity.

2349
02:12:57,562 --> 02:13:00,937
Only then did I realize that
if the gun is locked… it won't fire.

2350
02:13:02,521 --> 02:13:04,729
My son didn't kill him!

2351
02:13:05,271 --> 02:13:08,104
My son didn't kill him!

2352
02:13:16,271 --> 02:13:18,687
He could have been shot with another gun.

2353
02:13:21,812 --> 02:13:23,604
How can I maintain the gun count, sir?

2354
02:13:24,104 --> 02:13:25,146
I'm not a…

2355
02:13:26,104 --> 02:13:27,562
policeman, sir.

2356
02:13:28,146 --> 02:13:29,354
Like you.

2357
02:13:30,896 --> 02:13:32,396
What, uncle?
Why are you talking politely with him?

2358
02:13:32,479 --> 02:13:34,062
Throw him in a cell and give
him our special treatment.

2359
02:13:34,146 --> 02:13:35,021
He'll spill the truth.

2360
02:13:35,687 --> 02:13:37,062
I'll make him talk.
Should I lock him up?

2361
02:13:37,271 --> 02:13:38,479
Wait, sir, wait, wait, wait.

2362
02:13:38,562 --> 02:13:40,729
Yes, you should throw me in the cell, sir.
You definitely will.

2363
02:13:41,396 --> 02:13:43,729
But before that, I need to
send a little message to your sir.

2364
02:13:44,229 --> 02:13:46,896
Sir, I sent it to your WhatsApp number.
Please check it once.

2365
02:13:47,896 --> 02:13:49,146
The funny thing is…

2366
02:13:49,854 --> 02:13:52,229
at that very moment,
I got a message from my son.

2367
02:13:52,562 --> 02:13:54,521
Hi Dad! When will you come?

2368
02:13:55,437 --> 02:13:57,146
Ayaan sent a Reel.

2369
02:13:57,396 --> 02:13:58,521
He says he did it better than me.

2370
02:13:58,896 --> 02:14:00,062
You watch it once and tell me.

2371
02:14:17,521 --> 02:14:18,604
What is it, Uncle?

2372
02:14:20,979 --> 02:14:21,896
You look at it.

2373
02:14:38,771 --> 02:14:41,646
One small piece of evidence
got you caught.

2374
02:15:06,021 --> 02:15:07,146
I'm the one who killed him.

2375
02:15:08,312 --> 02:15:10,854
I… killed him.

2376
02:15:26,646 --> 02:15:27,771
Move aside a little.

2377
02:15:28,271 --> 02:15:29,312
Move, sir.

2378
02:15:34,437 --> 02:15:35,354
Hey!

2379
02:15:36,021 --> 02:15:38,271
-Why are you sitting in my seat? Get up!
-Huh?

2380
02:15:38,896 --> 02:15:40,187
Why are you sitting in my seat?
Get up!

2381
02:15:41,562 --> 02:15:45,396
You couldn't even control your anger
for a second while sitting in your seat…

2382
02:15:46,979 --> 02:15:50,021
but he came to my house…
on my bed…

2383
02:15:50,271 --> 02:15:52,479
…and slept with my wife.

2384
02:15:52,562 --> 02:15:54,229
How was I supposed to bear that, sir?

2385
02:15:58,396 --> 02:15:59,437
Don't come again.

2386
02:15:59,646 --> 02:16:01,479
-My husband got suspicious about me.
-That's not it, baby.

2387
02:16:01,604 --> 02:16:02,646
-Listen to me…
-Go…

2388
02:16:02,729 --> 02:16:03,604
Go!

2389
02:16:04,562 --> 02:16:05,604
I made my decision.

2390
02:16:07,021 --> 02:16:08,937
I followed him, waiting for the
right chance to kill him.

2391
02:16:10,896 --> 02:16:12,771
With the information from Edukondalu,

2392
02:16:13,437 --> 02:16:16,562
he was on his way to the
MLA's PA's house for the gift bag…

2393
02:16:17,437 --> 02:16:19,646
He saw your wife in the house next door.

2394
02:16:21,062 --> 02:16:25,354
Because of his lust,
he followed you wife.

2395
02:16:25,812 --> 02:16:27,062
I thought I missed my chance.

2396
02:16:27,437 --> 02:16:30,729
But fortunately…the gun
ended up in your son's hands.

2397
02:16:32,312 --> 02:16:33,646
Outside, firecrackers were bursting.

2398
02:16:34,354 --> 02:16:35,812
In my hands, the revolver went off.

2399
02:16:38,937 --> 02:16:42,187
Without any effort from my side,
you walked right into this.

2400
02:16:42,437 --> 02:16:45,687
To hide the crime,
you crossed the town with the body.

2401
02:16:46,062 --> 02:16:48,687
To frame you for this murder…
I started my work.

2402
02:16:52,396 --> 02:16:55,396
Wherever possible, I planned
things to make you look suspicious…

2403
02:16:55,771 --> 02:16:57,354
and turned the story against you.

2404
02:16:59,312 --> 02:17:01,896
There's one more thing none of you know…

2405
02:17:02,604 --> 02:17:04,562
I killed my wife as well.

2406
02:17:09,229 --> 02:17:10,562
As for the blackmail…

2407
02:17:12,604 --> 02:17:14,521
These murders will
eventually come to light.

2408
02:17:15,062 --> 02:17:16,729
Before that, I have to leave the country.

2409
02:17:17,771 --> 02:17:19,104
And for that, I need money.

2410
02:17:19,521 --> 02:17:21,812
You can only threaten someone
who's already scared, right, sir?

2411
02:17:22,021 --> 02:17:23,229
So now what?

2412
02:17:24,604 --> 02:17:27,896
You're going to throw me
in a cell with this flimsy evidence?

2413
02:17:28,021 --> 02:17:31,979
Put your emotions aside for
a moment and think a little logically.

2414
02:17:32,104 --> 02:17:35,062
To prove that the bullet that
came from the gun I used…

2415
02:17:35,854 --> 02:17:38,771
is the one in the SI's head…

2416
02:17:45,354 --> 02:17:46,521
you need SI's body…

2417
02:17:49,021 --> 02:17:49,979
What, Sriram?

2418
02:17:50,646 --> 02:17:51,729
You need the body, right?

2419
02:17:52,771 --> 02:17:54,604
It must be burned down into ashes.

2420
02:18:01,229 --> 02:18:02,146
The body is right there.

2421
02:18:07,271 --> 02:18:08,854
The body is right there, Sudheer.

2422
02:18:13,937 --> 02:18:15,104
The body is right there.

2423
02:18:19,562 --> 02:18:21,312
My son didn't kill him.

2424
02:18:22,354 --> 02:18:23,271
Oh my God!

2425
02:18:26,062 --> 02:18:27,312
I have to tell Uttara.

2426
02:18:32,854 --> 02:18:34,729
In the relief of knowing
my son didn't kill him,

2427
02:18:35,146 --> 02:18:36,521
something else came to mind.

2428
02:18:36,604 --> 02:18:37,854
Oh my God!

2429
02:18:38,729 --> 02:18:39,896
Vikram's body…

2430
02:18:40,187 --> 02:18:42,979
I rushed to the crematorium for that body.

2431
02:18:43,104 --> 02:18:43,979
Brother!

2432
02:18:44,062 --> 02:18:46,979
The unclaimed bodies that were here
earlier… have you burned them?

2433
02:18:47,062 --> 02:18:48,437
I burned them. Why?

2434
02:18:49,479 --> 02:18:50,687
-You burned them?!
-Yes.

2435
02:18:50,771 --> 02:18:54,229
Amid that shock, I received
a call from MLA Thimmappa.

2436
02:18:54,312 --> 02:18:56,562
-Hello.
-Hey, Sriram.

2437
02:18:56,646 --> 02:18:59,187
Bring my gift bag and come here.

2438
02:18:59,646 --> 02:19:02,687
Your mother-in-law, your father-in-law,

2439
02:19:02,812 --> 02:19:05,229
and as a bonus, your brother-in-law…

2440
02:19:05,312 --> 02:19:07,271
are all here with me.

2441
02:19:08,937 --> 02:19:10,854
You take time until morning.

2442
02:19:10,937 --> 02:19:13,771
Give me my bag and take them away.

2443
02:19:16,479 --> 02:19:18,479
I felt trapped from all sides.

2444
02:19:20,271 --> 02:19:24,271
But… that's when God
gave me another chance.

2445
02:19:30,229 --> 02:19:33,729
I saw the unburnt body of SI Vikram.

2446
02:19:46,854 --> 02:19:49,271
When people have a problem,
they go to the police.

2447
02:19:49,729 --> 02:19:51,771
But if the police themselves are
the problem, who do we turn to, sir?

2448
02:19:54,354 --> 02:19:55,646
Enough now. Come on.

2449
02:19:55,812 --> 02:19:56,687
Let's go.

2450
02:19:59,312 --> 02:20:01,354
Whatever happened, Sriram,
what you did was still wrong.

2451
02:20:01,479 --> 02:20:02,479
It was a mistake, sir.

2452
02:20:03,479 --> 02:20:05,271
But for the sake of my family,
I had no choice, sir.

2453
02:20:05,771 --> 02:20:06,729
Please forgive me.

2454
02:20:08,062 --> 02:20:10,604
Okay. You must come
whenever we call you.

2455
02:20:10,687 --> 02:20:11,604
You can go.

2456
02:20:12,146 --> 02:20:13,021
-Hey, constable!
-Sir.

2457
02:20:14,396 --> 02:20:15,271
Okay, sir.

2458
02:20:17,771 --> 02:20:20,062
-Okay, sir.
-We've brought the body, dear.

2459
02:20:20,521 --> 02:20:21,562
What do we do now?

2460
02:20:22,979 --> 02:20:24,354
Don't try to think of anything new.

2461
02:20:25,896 --> 02:20:27,354
Just do exactly what I told you.

2462
02:20:28,312 --> 02:20:30,021
It's true that I took your car.

2463
02:20:30,104 --> 02:20:32,062
But there was no bag in it, sir.

2464
02:20:34,021 --> 02:20:36,312
However, I do have something you want.

2465
02:20:38,187 --> 02:20:39,187
Check your phone.

2466
02:20:42,854 --> 02:20:45,937
For the last time, if you have
something to say to your daughter,

2467
02:20:46,812 --> 02:20:47,771
now is the moment.

2468
02:20:48,479 --> 02:20:49,354
What is it?

2469
02:20:59,062 --> 02:21:00,771
-Leave them. Send them away.
-Okay, boss.

2470
02:21:10,437 --> 02:21:12,354
You missed one small logic, MLA sir.

2471
02:21:12,437 --> 02:21:14,604
If you're this tense,

2472
02:21:15,146 --> 02:21:18,062
it must be something
that could cause you trouble.

2473
02:21:19,562 --> 02:21:21,396
You've known me for years.

2474
02:21:22,021 --> 02:21:24,229
If I had found something that serious,

2475
02:21:25,437 --> 02:21:28,104
you would have been behind bars
the very next minute.

2476
02:21:30,646 --> 02:21:32,854
Actually, I didn't put
that gift bag in the car.

2477
02:21:33,562 --> 02:21:36,562
Yes. Generally, when we handle
these kinds of illegal transactions,

2478
02:21:37,104 --> 02:21:38,687
I put the bag in my car's trunk

2479
02:21:38,771 --> 02:21:41,521
and leave for a trip with my family
the same day to avoid raising suspicion.

2480
02:21:41,896 --> 02:21:44,562
But that day, I needed the money,
so I took the bag with me.

2481
02:21:46,687 --> 02:21:50,812
I assumed the crime would be blamed on
whoever came for the money.

2482
02:21:51,396 --> 02:21:52,854
Unexpectedly, he got arrested,

2483
02:21:52,937 --> 02:21:55,771
SI Vikram came to your house
instead of mine looking for the money,

2484
02:21:56,229 --> 02:21:58,229
and then he died.
Everything happened one after the other.

2485
02:21:58,312 --> 02:21:59,437
I'm really sorry, Sriram.

2486
02:22:00,021 --> 02:22:01,729
Sorry. Really sorry.

2487
02:22:06,312 --> 02:22:07,271
It's alright, sir.

2488
02:22:07,854 --> 02:22:09,604
-Eat, son.
-How much will you eat?

2489
02:22:12,062 --> 02:22:13,146
If you eat any more, you'll die.

2490
02:22:16,437 --> 02:22:17,521
That's okay, Dad.

2491
02:22:19,896 --> 02:22:21,396
Boost is the secret of my energy!

2492
02:22:26,312 --> 02:22:27,354
So, what now?

2493
02:22:29,646 --> 02:22:30,812
I'm hungry too.

2494
02:22:32,187 --> 02:22:33,271
I haven't eaten in three days.

2495
02:22:40,771 --> 02:22:41,646
Go away.

2496
02:22:42,562 --> 02:22:43,437
Okay, come.
